\id MRK - Akawaio New Testament Translation Project 
\h MA' 
\toc1 Sises Ekareei Ma' Nʉmenuka'pʉ 
\toc2 Ma' 
\toc3 Ma' 
\mt2 Sises Ekareei 
\mt1 Ma' 
\mt2 Nʉmenuka'pʉ 
\imt1 Ekamanin 
\ip \bk Sises Ekareei Ma' Nʉmenuka'pʉ\bk* epiya'tɨ, “Serɨ, serɨ wakʉ itekare Papa Mumu, Sises Kʉrai pɨ',” tukai'. Sises usene ka'pon iku'nin, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉmeruntɨrʉ kenan pe. Imeruntɨrʉ usene enupan nɨto' iya yau, makoi a'kwarʉ entaino yau, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ka'pon amʉ' makooi pɨ' isentu'ma. Sises usaurokʉ tʉpɨ' Ka'pon, Papa winon pe, iye'sa' rʉ'pʉ tʉuko'manto' tʉse'na ka'pon amʉ' mo'kanin pe makoi apai. 
\ip \bk Ma'\bk* uya Sises pantomʉ ekama to'sarɨ rɨ, pana'pan yau, Sises nʉkupʉ'pʉ kuru pɨ', imaimu ton mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ enupan nɨto' iya ton entai. To'ken nɨ Isaan Pa'tes mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Sises epa'taisima'pʉ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ i'tupɨtʉ pɨ' Makoi esi'pʉ tʉpo, imenukanin uya inke pʉra rɨ Sises e'tʉrawasoma'pʉ rʉ'pʉ epi'tɨn pɨ', enupan pɨ' anʉmʉ. Iko'mamʉ kaisarɨ rɨ, Sises pɨkɨron kon uya ito'ka'nʉkʉ'pʉ wakʉ pe parɨ, e'tane iteyaton non ena'pʉ miyarɨ rɨ ɨsɨ pe. Iu'matʉ pe ekamanin airɨ ekamasa' iya iye'ku'sa' rʉ'pʉ serɨ non po Sises uko'manto' iu'matʉ suntaakaai yau, kurusu' pona ipokapɨtʉ'pʉ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iye'mʉ'sa'ka'pʉ terikʉ'pʉ apai kuru. 
\ip Asa'rɨ na'ne' iu'ma'to' yau'ne, iwa'kʉ'pɨ'sa' na'ne' pɨ', tʉron nɨ rɨ, \bk Ma'\bk* pen nɨ nʉmenuka'pʉ tapɨ'pɨtʉ. 
\iot Iyawon Ekamanin 
\io1 Sises ekareei epiya'tɨ (1:1-13) 
\io1 Annau Sises e'tʉrawasoma'pʉ Kiyarari po (1:14—9:50) 
\io1 Kiyarari ponsi'kɨ Surusiran pona (10:1-52) 
\io1 Iu'matʉ suntaakaai Surusiran po mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ipiyau (11:1—15:47) 
\io1 Sises e'mʉ'sa'ka'pʉ terikʉ'pʉ apai (16:1-8) 
\io1 Iye'mʉ'sa'kasa' Itepuru usenpoikapɨtʉ'pʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iyenuku'pʉ (16:9-20) 
\c 1  
\s1 Isaan Pa'tes Ekareei 
\r (Ma'siu 3:1-12; Ʉru' 3:1-18; Isaan 1:19-28) 
\p  
\v 1 Serɨ, serɨ wakʉ itekare epiya'tɨ Papa Mumu,\f + \fr 1:1 \ft Tʉron nɨ ton imenukasa' yau, \fq Papa Mumu \ft tawon pʉra iyesi.\f* Sises Kʉrai pɨ'.  
\v 2 Pu'kena' Aisaya karetaai yau iye'menukasa' na'ne': 
\q1 “Umaimu ekamanin ennoko uya mɨrɨ arawɨrɨ, 
\q2 ɨye'ma konekanin pe,”\f + \fr 1:2 \ft Mara'kai 3:1\f* 
\m tawon. 
\q1  
\v 3 “Rɨmono' tau ka'pon ukɨ'pɨ'nʉnpɨtʉ, 
\q1 ‘Itepuru e'ma ikonekatɨ'; 
\q2 to'sa rɨ ite'ma ikonekatɨ',’”\f + \fr 1:3 \ft Aisaya 40:3\f* 
\m tawon.  
\v 4 Mɨrɨ kasa si Isaan uyee'pʉ, pa'taisiman pɨ' rɨmono'ta nono yau mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ makoi apai era'tɨn epa'taisimato' makoi pɨ' usentu'man ekareei ekama pɨ'.\f + \fr 1:4 \ft Tʉron nɨ ton imenukasa' yau, \fq Isaan Pa'tes usenpoika'pʉ rɨmono' tau itekare ekama pɨ', \ft tawon esi.\f* 
\v 5 Tanporon kon nɨ Isutiya mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ eke pata Surusiran winon kon nɨ utɨ'pʉ ipiya'. Tʉmakooi kon ekama pɨ', mɨrɨpan kon pa'taisima'pʉ iya Isotan tuna tʉu'tɨsen kau. 
\p  
\v 6 Isaan pon esi'pʉ kiyamerʉ i'po' konekasa', o' pi'pɨ konekasa' esi'pʉ ipokʉrʉʉi pe iworo'pai pɨ'. Kairau amʉ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ teusan e'ku pɨ' tenta'nasen pe iyesi'pʉ.\x - \xo 1:6 \xt 2 Kin Amʉ' 1:8\x* 
\v 7 Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ se si esi'pʉ mɨrɨ itekareei pe: “Uye'ma'pʉ pe iyepʉ mɨrɨ ka'pon meruntɨ kuru uyentaino, tʉu'tɨi' isapatooi euka uya pokena' pen nɨ.  
\v 8 Apa'taisima uya 'nokon serɨ tuna ke, e'tane kʉrɨ rɨ uya nin si apa'taisima kon mɨrɨ Wakʉ A'kwarʉ ke,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\s1 Sises Esi'pʉ Epa'taisiman Pɨ', Se'tan Esi'pʉ I'tupɨtʉ Pɨ' 
\r (Ma'siu 3:13—4:11; Ʉru' 3:21-22; 4:1-13) 
\p  
\v 9 Mɨrɨ a'tai, Sises uyee'pʉ Nasare', Kiyarari yawon winɨ, mɨrɨpan pa'taisima'pʉ Isaan uya Isotan kau.  
\v 10 Sises ekanwaka koro'tau tuna kapai, ka' uta'koka e'se'ne' pe ene'pʉ iya, mɨrɨpan uya Ita'kwarʉ u'tɨ wako'wa kasa ene'pʉ tʉpona.  
\v 11 Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ main uyee'pʉ Epʉn awonsi'kɨ, “Umu ɨmɨrɨ, uni'nʉnkanʉ; ɨpɨ' pori' pe e'ai' ipan pe,” tawon.\x - \xo 1:11 \xt Iseneses 22:2; Eren 2:7; Aisaya 42:1; Ma'siu 12:18; Ma' 9:7\x*\fig “Umu ɨmɨrɨ, uni'nʉnkanʉ; ɨpɨ' pori' pe e'ai' ipan pe!”|src="CN01656B.tif" size="span" loc="MRK 1:9-11" copy="David C. Cook" ref="1:11" \fig* 
\p  
\v 12 Inke pʉra rɨ, Ita'kwarʉ uya ennoko'pʉ rɨmono' ta'.  
\v 13 Rɨmono' tau iyesi'pʉ 40 kaisa rɨ wʉi, Se'tan\f + \fr 1:13 \fq Se'tan\ft —Makoi ese' isakon, \fq Papa eseru ewaruma'tɨnin \ft ta e'kwa pe.\f* esi'pʉ i'tupɨtʉ pɨ'. Mɨrɨ yau rɨ kanan ene amʉ' pokon pe iyesi'pʉ, mɨrɨpan ene pɨ' inserʉ amʉ' esi'pʉ. 
\s1 Wapiyaro' Kon Tʉpoitorʉ Pe Te'ton Kon Kɨ'ma'pʉ Sises Uya 
\r (Ma'siu 4:12-22; Ʉru' 4:14-15; 5:1-11) 
\p  
\v 14 Isaan a'sisa' to' uya tʉpo pariki'si ta', Kiyarari pona Sises utɨ'pʉ, wakʉ Papa ekareei ekama pɨ'.  
\v 15 “Iweyu e'seposa' man, Papa e'to' esa' wannɨ pe man a'ko pe! Amakooi kon apai era'tɨtɨ', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ itekare apurɨtɨ'!” ta'pʉ iya.\x - \xo 1:15 \xt Ma'siu 3:2\x* 
\p  
\v 16 Sises usarɨ koro'tau parau ku'pɨri Kiyarari piyawɨrɨ, asa'ron kon moro' a'sinin nan ka'pon amʉ' ene'pʉ iya, Saiman, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iyakon Anturu pokon, tʉpunwerʉ kon yai moro' amʉ' a'si to' uya esi'pʉ.  
\v 17 Sises uya ta'pʉ to' pɨ', “Upɨkɨrɨ ɨsi'tɨ'. Ɨkonekato' kon pe uya ka'pon amʉ' a'sinin nan pe,” ta'pʉ iya.  
\v 18 Mɨrɨ pe rɨ, tʉpunwerʉ kon tʉnɨnse to' utɨ'pʉ ipɨkɨrɨ. 
\p  
\v 19 Ɨnnɨ iwa rʉ'kwɨ itɨsa' a'tai, Isens ene'pʉ iya, Sepiti mu mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Isaan, iyakon kanau yau, tʉpunwerʉ kon konepɨtʉ pɨ'.  
\v 20 Oko pe pʉra rɨ, to' kɨ'ma'pʉ iya, mɨrɨpan kon uya tʉkʉipʉnʉ kon mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ aka'ne' pe anʉnsa' kon ipoitorʉ ton pokon pe tʉnɨnse kanau yau, to' utɨ'pʉ ipɨkɨrɨ. 
\s1 Makoi A'kwarʉ Enpa'ka'pʉ Sises Uya 
\r (Ʉru' 4:31-37) 
\p  
\v 21 To' utɨ'pʉ Ka'paneyan pona; Sapa' uye'sa' a'tai, Sises utɨ'pʉ Esuwerʉ amʉ' usenupato' iwʉ' ta'. Mɨrɨ yau, to' enupa pɨ' iyepiya'tɨ'pʉ.  
\v 22 Ka'pon amʉ' usewansiuka'pʉ enupan nɨto' iya pɨ', apʉne pʉra tenupa iya 'nokon pɨ' tʉmeruntɨrʉkenan pe kuru rɨ, Main pɨ' enupanin nan kasa pʉra.\x - \xo 1:22 \xt Ma'siu 7:28-29\x* 
\v 23 Mɨrɨ koro'tau, ka'pon, makoi\f + \fr 1:23 \fq makoi, \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra \fq ɨri, \ft Kiri' maimu yau; v. 26-27 yau nɨrɨ.\f* a'kwarʉ yen pe te'sen mɨrɨ yau Esuwerʉ amʉ' usenupato' iwʉ' tau, ukɨ'pɨ'nʉmʉ'pʉ,  
\v 24 “Sises, Nasare' pon, ɨ'rɨ pe ina ku'se'na ɨuye'sa'? Ina pe' ma'tanʉ'se'na ɨuye'sa'? Kɨnyi'tuyai' ɨmɨrɨ kʉrɨ rɨ—Wakʉ Ye' Papa Iwano'!” ta'pʉ iya ipɨ'. 
\p  
\v 25 “E'pana e'kɨ! Epa'kakɨ iyapai!” ta'pʉ Sises uya e'se'ne' pe. 
\p  
\v 26 Makoi a'kwarʉ uya e'se'ne' pe ka'pon i'ki'ma'pʉ, mɨrɨpan epa'ka'pʉ iyapai tʉupirorʉnse.  
\v 27 Ka'pon amʉ' usewansiuka'pʉ, mɨrɨpan kon usekama'popɨtʉ'pʉ tiwano' kon pe, “Ɨ'rɨ si serɨ? Emenna' usenupan nɨto'—meruntɨ a'kɨron! Makoi a'kwarʉ ton nɨ apiyo'manin, mɨrɨpan kon esi imaimu awɨrɨ!” ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\p  
\v 28 Itekareei utɨ'pʉ inke pʉra kuru rɨ siya rɨ Kiyarari nono poro. 
\s1 Tu'kan Kon Nɨ Epi'tɨpɨtʉ'pʉ Sises Uya 
\r (Ma'siu 8:14-17; Ʉru' 4:38-41) 
\p  
\v 29 Tepa'kasa' kon a'tai Esuwerʉ amʉ' usenupato' iwʉ' tapai, to' utɨ'pʉ Saiman mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Anturu pata'se' ya'. Isens mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Isaan pokon utɨ'pʉ to' a'kɨrɨ.  
\v 30 Saiman ewo'pʉ esi'pʉ e'kɨɨi'man pɨ', te'kwe' tau. Inke pʉra rɨ Sises uye'sa' a'tai, to' uya ekama'pʉ ipɨ'.  
\v 31 Sises utɨ'pʉ ipiya', itemiyatʉ pɨ' ta'sii' i'mʉ'sa'ka'pʉ iya. Iye'kɨɨi'mato' ereuta'pʉ, mɨrɨpan uya to' mʉta'napa'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 32 Pata uko'mansa' a'tai, wʉi enu pata'pʉ pe, ka'pon amʉ' uya tanporo rɨ takuru'kena' nan mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ makoi a'kwarʉ yen ton nee'pʉ Sises piya'.  
\v 33 Tanporo rɨ mɨrɨ pata yau te'san ka'pon amʉ' amʉra'pʉ mʉra'ta na'.  
\v 34 Sises uya tu'kan kon nɨ takuru'kena' nan epi'tɨpɨtʉ'pʉ to' eparan apai'ne, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ makoi a'kwarʉ ton nɨ enno'pɨtʉ'pʉ iya. Makoi a'kwarʉ ton usaurokʉ i'se pʉra rɨ iyesi'pʉ, apʉne pʉra to' uya ti'tu wenai. 
\s1 Sises Ɨpʉrema'pʉ Tʉ'kenan Pata Yau 
\r (Ʉru' 4:42-44) 
\p  
\v 35 Awanakʉi' kuru, ewarupɨ pe rɨ marɨ pata e'tane, Sises e'mʉ'sa'ka'pʉ, mɨrɨpan utɨ'pʉ ɨutɨ tapai tʉ'kenan pata ya' ɨpʉremase'na.  
\v 36 E'tane Saiman mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ itonpa ton utɨ'pʉ iwarinpase'na.  
\v 37 To' uya eposa' a'tai, “Tanporon kon man awarinpa pɨ'!” ta'pʉ to' uya ipɨ'. 
\p  
\v 38 Sises uya to' eikʉ'pʉ, “Tʉron nɨ airɨ eke iwa ton a'ko pa'nan pata ton ya' utɨnpai'nokon. Mɨrɨ yau'ne kanan itekare ekamato' pe uya. Mɨrɨto' pe uye'sa' serɨ,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 39 Mɨrɨpan utɨ'pʉ siya rɨ Kiyarari poro itekare ekama pɨ' Esuwerʉ amʉ' usenupato' iwʉ' ton tau, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ makoi a'kwarʉ ton nɨ enno'pɨtʉ'pʉ iya.\x - \xo 1:39 \xt Ma'siu 4:23; 9:35\x* 
\s1 Erekʉ'pan Ka'pon Epi'tɨ'pʉ Sises Uya 
\r (Ma'siu 8:1-4; Ʉru' 5:12-16) 
\p  
\v 40 Erekʉ'pan\f + \fr 1:40 \fq Erekʉ'pan, \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra \fq Leper, \ft Enkeri'si pe. Kiri' maimu yau utapurɨpɨtʉ'pʉ tu'kan nɨ pi'pɨ eparan ese' pe, \fq leprosy \ft kuru pen nɨ pɨ'.\f* ka'pon uyee'pʉ Sises piya'. Tese'mu po esii'ma iyeta'kwanʉmʉ'pʉ ipɨ', “Ɨnku'pai ɨwesi yau, wakʉ pe ukupʉ auya,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 41 Sises usentu'ma'pʉ\f + \fr 1:41 \ft Tʉron nɨ ton imenukasa' yau, \fq usakorota'pʉ \ft tawon esi.\f* ipɨ'. Temiyatʉ ɨnka'pʉ iya, mɨrɨpan uya a'pɨtʉ'pʉ. “Ɨnku'pai rɨ e'ai'. Wakʉ pe e'kɨ!” ta'pʉ iya ipɨ'.  
\v 42 Mɨrɨ a'tai rɨ, ka'pon erekʉ usepi'tɨ'pʉ, mɨrɨpan ena'pʉ wakʉ pe rɨ.  
\v 43 Sises uya inke pʉra ennoko'pʉ ipanama tʉpo se tukai',  
\v 44 “Ɨnʉ' pɨ' rɨ serɨ kʉsekamai, e'tane enta ɨsenpoikata Papa ena' use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin ena', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨuse'mato' pe te'sen, Mosi' uya tasa' na'ne' awɨrɨ mʉtʉrʉi', ɨyekorʉkasa' ekamanin pe to' pɨ',” ta'pʉ iya.\x - \xo 1:44 \xt Ripaiti'kas 14:1-32\x* 
\p  
\v 45 E'tane kʉrɨ rɨ ka'pon utɨ'pʉ siya rɨ itekareei ekamase. Mɨrɨ moron nʉ'pʉ pe Sises epa'ka poken pʉra rɨ iyesi'pʉ eke iwa pata ton ya'ne, e'tane rɨ ka'pon amʉ' uye'pɨtʉ'pʉ mɨ'tapai'ne rɨ ipiya'. 
\c 2  
\s1 Ipu'tɨka'sa' Ka'pon Epi'tɨ'pʉ Sises Uya 
\r (Ma'siu 9:1-8; Ʉru' 5:17-26) 
\p  
\v 1 Emennʉ'pʉ po iwa rɨ, Sises enna'po'pʉ Ka'paneyan pona. Mɨrɨ a'tai, tʉpata'se' ya' iyenna'posa' man tawon useta'pʉ.  
\v 2 Tu'ke rɨ ka'pon amʉ' amʉra'pʉ, pata oton pʉra rɨ pata tʉku'se mʉra'ta airɨ'ne rɨ. Sises esi'pʉ itekare ekama pɨ' to' pɨ'.  
\v 3 Mɨrɨ a'tai, asakɨrɨ'nan kon ka'pon amʉ' uya ipu'tɨka'sa' ka'pon nee'pʉ ipiya'.  
\v 4 Apʉne pʉra anpisin pe ka'pon amʉ' esi pɨ' itʉrʉ tʉuya'nokon poken pʉra Sises piya', iteuta koneka'pʉ to' uya ɨutɨ nakapu yai Sises epoi, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ aka tʉkon po, ka'pon ipu'tɨka'sa' nu'tɨ'pʉ to' uya iyapon po rɨ.  
\v 5 Sises uya to' uya apurɨto' ene'pʉ, mɨrɨpan uya ipu'tɨka'sa' ka'pon pɨ' ta'pʉ, “Mooi, amakooi pɨ' usentu'masa' man,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 6 Mɨrɨ yau tereutai' te'san, Main pɨ' enupanin nan usenuminka'pʉ tiwano' kon pe,  
\v 7 “Ɨ'rɨ pe iyesi pɨ' mɨrɨ kasa Papa sapema pe rɨ isaurokʉ? Ɨnʉ' rɨ sa'ne makoi pɨ' tʉusentu'masen pʉra rɨ iyesi mɨrɨ ko, Papa rɨken!” ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\p  
\v 8 Mɨrɨ a'tai rɨ, Sises uya ta'kwarʉ yau i'tu'pʉ to' usenuminka tewan kon yau, mɨrɨpan uya ta'pʉ to' pɨ', “Ɨ'rɨ pe iyesi pɨ' mɨrɨ kasa ɨusenuminka kon?  
\v 9 Nai esi sa'man pe pʉra iwa pʉse rɨ ipu'tɨka'sa' pɨ' tato'; ‘Amakooi pɨ' usentu'masa' man,’ ta, mɨrɨ pe pʉra, ‘Te'mʉ'sa'kai' ayapon tanʉnse enta,’ ta?  
\v 10 Serɨ pe enpoika uya si serɨ non po, Ka'pon, Papa winon piyau meruntɨ esi makoi pɨ' usentu'man nɨto',” ta'pʉ iya, mɨrɨpan uya ipu'tɨka'sa' ka'pon pɨ' ta'pʉ,  
\v 11 “Ta uya ɨpɨ', e'mʉ'sa'ka', ayapon anʉnkɨ, enna'po' apata'se' ya'!” ta'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 12 To' uya rɨ enpɨ'tane ka'pon e'mʉ'sa'ka'pʉ, tapon anʉmʉ'pʉ iya, mɨrɨpan utɨ'pʉ. Ipan pe rɨ to' usewansiuka'pʉ, mɨrɨpan kon uya Papa apurɨpɨtʉ'pʉ, “Serɨ waraino ensa' uya'nokon pʉra rɨ man!” tai'ma. \fig “E'mʉ'sa'ka', ayapon anʉnkɨ, enna'po' apata'se' ya'!”|src="CN01689B.tif" size="col" loc="MRK 2:1-12" copy="David C. Cook" ref="2:11" \fig* 
\s1 Ripai Kɨ'ma'pʉ Sises Uya Tʉpoitorʉ Pe 
\r (Ma'siu 9:9-13; Ʉru' 5:27-32) 
\p  
\v 13 Sises enna'pokaa'pʉ kanan parau ku'pɨri e'pi pona. Anpisin pe ka'pon amʉ' uyee'pʉ ipiya', mɨrɨpan kon enupa pɨ' iye'sara'tɨ'pʉ.  
\v 14 Isarɨ koro'tau, pʉrata amʉranʉ'nin, Ripai, Arʉ'piyas mu ene'pʉ iya, iyereutasa' pʉrata amʉranʉ'to' iwʉ' tau. Sises uya ta'pʉ ipɨ', “Uya'kɨrɨ ɨsi'kɨ,” mɨrɨpan Ripai e'mʉ'sa'ka'pʉ, itɨ'pʉ iya'kɨrɨ. 
\p  
\v 15 Sises esi koro'tau enta'nan pɨ' Ripai iwʉ' tau tu'kan kon nɨ pʉrata amʉranʉ'nin nan mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉmakooikena' nan esi'pʉ enta'nan pɨ' ipokon pe, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ipoitorʉ ton pokon pe rɨ, apʉne pʉra tu'ke rɨ ipɨkɨrɨ to' esi ke.  
\v 16 Main pɨ' enupanin nan tonpa ton, Pari'si amʉ' pe te'san uya Sises enta'na ene'pʉ pʉrata amʉranʉ'nin nan mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉmakooikena' nan pokon pe, mɨrɨpan kon uya ipoitorʉ ton ekama'po'pʉ, “Ɨ'rɨ pe iyesi pɨ' kamoro rupɨ pokon pe iyenta'na?” ta'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 17 Sises uya to' eta'pʉ, mɨrɨpan kon eikʉ'pʉ iya, “Atu' pe te'san ka'pon amʉ' esi mɨrɨ ta'ta i'se pʉra rɨ, e'tane kamoro takuru'ke te'san nɨken esi i'se. Uye'sa' serɨ ipokena' ton nɨ ka'pon amʉ' kɨ'mase'na pen, e'tane tʉmakooikena' nan nɨken,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\s1 Ɨ'rɨ Pe Iyesi Pɨ' Useruman? 
\r (Ma'siu 9:14-17; Ʉru' 5:33-39) 
\p  
\v 18 Isaan Pa'tes mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Pari'si amʉ' poitorʉ ton useruma esi'pʉ tenta'nai' pʉra. Tʉron kon ka'pon amʉ' uyee'pʉ Sises piya' ekama'pose'na, “Ɨ'rɨ pe iyesi pɨ' Isaan Pa'tes poitorʉ ton mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Pari'si amʉ' poitorʉ ton useruma tenta'nai' pʉra, e'tane ɨpoitorʉ ton useruma pʉra rɨ iyesi?” ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\p  
\v 19 Sises uya to' eikʉ'pʉ, “Nai kasa warawo' temari'masen nʉkɨ'ma'san useruma tenta'nai' pʉra tʉpiyau'nokon nɨ iye'tane? To' useruma pʉra iyesi tʉpiyau'nokon iye'tane.  
\v 20 E'tane iweyu e'sepoto' oton warawo' temari'masen emo'kato' oton to' piyapai; mɨrɨ wʉi a'tai nin si, to' useruma mɨrɨ tenta'nai' pʉra. 
\p  
\v 21 “Ɨnʉ' uya rɨ emenna' pon ke ipooi'pɨ pon a'si'tɨ pʉra rɨ iyesi mɨrɨ. Mɨrɨ kasa iyesi yau, emenna' pon uya ipooi'pɨ pon karaka eke pe rɨ iteuta tʉku'se.  
\v 22 Ɨnʉ' uya rɨ emenna' waain entɨ pʉra rɨ iyesi mɨrɨ ipooi'pɨ iten ya'. Mɨrɨ kasa iyesi yau, asa'rɨ rɨ nin si ima'ta mɨrɨ. Emenna' iten esi emenna' waain yen pe,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\s1 Sapa' Eseru Ekama'popɨtʉ 
\r (Ma'siu 12:1-8; Ʉru' 6:1-5) 
\p  
\v 23 Tʉron nɨ Sapa' a'tai, Sises utɨ esi'pʉ a'nai' e'kwa nawɨrɨ. Tʉutɨi'ma'nokon ipoitorʉ ton uya a'nai' e'suruupɨ'sa' i'kwɨ'pɨtʉ'pʉ.\x - \xo 2:23 \xt Isu'taronomi 23:25\x* 
\v 24 Pari'si amʉ' uya ta'pʉ ipɨ', “Apʉne enkɨ, ɨ'rɨ pe iyesi pɨ' Main uya tʉku'sen pen Sapa' a'tai tasa' rʉ'pʉ kupʉ to' uya?” ta'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 25 Sises uya to' eikʉ'pʉ, “Etanin nan pen pe' ɨmɨrɨ'nokon Tepi' nʉkupʉ'pʉ tʉpoitorʉ ton pokon pe, iwan pe tesi kon pɨ' tenta'nato' kon i'se tesi kon a'tai?\x - \xo 2:25 \xt 1 Sanwerʉ 21:1-6\x* 
\v 26 Mɨrɨpan utɨ'pʉ Papa iwʉ' ta', mɨrɨpan enta'na'pʉ ipʉremasa' pʉreti pɨ'. Serɨ e'kupʉ'pʉ Apiya'ta, Papa ena' use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan epuru a'tai. Use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan nɨken nɨkunʉ Main uya tasa' awɨrɨ. E'tane Tepi' enta'na'pʉ ipɨ', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉtonpa ton nɨ nɨrɨ repapɨtʉ'pʉ iya,” ta'pʉ iya.\x - \xo 2:26 \xt Ripaiti'kas 24:9\x* 
\p  
\v 27 Mɨrɨpan Sises uya ta'pʉ, “Sapa' ekonekasa' ka'pon iwano' pe, ka'pon ekonekasa' pen Sapa' iwano' pe.  
\v 28 Mɨrɨ uriya', Ka'pon, Papa winon esi Sapa' Epuru pe rɨ,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\c 3  
\s1 Ka'pon Iyaipʉtasa' Itemiya 
\r (Ma'siu 12:9-14; Ʉru' 6:6-11) 
\p  
\v 1 Tʉron nɨ a'tai Sises utɨ'pʉ Esuwerʉ amʉ' usenupato' iwʉ' ta'. Mɨrɨ yau, ka'pon iyaipʉtasa' amʉrasa' itemiyatʉ esi'pʉ.  
\v 2 Tʉron kon esi'pʉ Sises eseru'tɨto' tʉuya'nokon iwenai kupʉ iya ene i'se, mɨrɨpan kon uya a'ko pe esii'ma enpɨtʉ'pʉ, Sapa' a'tai pe' epi'tɨ iya tukai'.  
\v 3 Sises uya ta'pʉ ka'pon iyaipʉtasa' amʉrasa' itemiyatʉ pɨ', “E'mʉ'sa'ka' tanporon kon rau,” ta'pʉ iya.  
\v 4 Mɨrɨpan uya ka'pon amʉ' ekama'po'pʉ, “Nai esi Main, Mosi' winon awɨrɨ Sapa' a'tai tʉku'sen pe: wakʉ kupʉ, mɨrɨ pe pʉra ɨri kupʉ katɨ? Ka'pon pika'tɨ ima'ta namai', mɨrɨ pe pʉra iwɨnɨ katɨ?” ta'pʉ iya. E'tane e'pana to' esi'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 5 Sises usakorota uya to' enpɨtʉ'pʉ, ipan pe rɨ ɨpokoitai'ma rɨ marɨ, apʉne pʉra sa'man pe rɨ to' ewan esi pɨ', mɨrɨpan uya ta'pʉ ka'pon pɨ', “Ɨyemiyatʉ ɨnka'!” Ɨnka'pʉ iya, mɨrɨpan emiyatʉ enna'po'pʉ tesi'pʉ ya'.  
\v 6 Mɨrɨ a'tai, Pari'si amʉ' uya tʉusenupato' kon iwʉ' nɨmɨ'pʉ, mɨrɨpan kon e'seporo'pʉ kin pe te'sen, Era' tonpa ton pokon pe, mɨrɨpan kon ekoneka'pʉ Sises wɨto' pe tʉuya'nokon pɨ'. 
\s1 Anpisin Esi'pʉ Parau Ku'pɨri E'pi Po 
\p  
\v 7 Sises mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ipoitorʉ ton utɨ'pʉ parau ku'pɨri ka'. Tu'ke rɨ anpisin Kiyarari winon kon utɨ'pʉ ipɨkɨrɨ.  
\v 8 Pʉsamoro uyee'pʉ Isutiya winɨ, Surusiran winɨ, Itumiya winɨ, Isotan ratoi nono winɨ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Taya mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Saitan nono winɨ'ne. Anpisin ton nɨ uyee'pʉ Sises piya', apʉne pʉra inkupʉnʉ etasa' tʉuya'nokon pɨ'.  
\v 9 Apʉne pʉra anpisin pe rɨ to' esi pɨ', Sises uya tʉpoitorʉ ton auro'ka'pʉ kanau epoto' pe to' uya tekanwa'tɨto' ya' ka'pon amʉ' uya tu'ke rɨ tʉu'na'tɨ namai'.  
\v 10 Tu'kan kon nɨ epi'tɨsa' iya pɨ', tanporon kon nɨ takuru'kena' nan uyee'pʉ tʉuta'tu'mapɨ'se rɨ a'pɨ'se'na.\x - \xo 3:10 \xt Ma' 4:1; Ʉru' 5:1-3\x* 
\v 11 Makoi\f + \fr 3:11 \fq Makoi, \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra \fq Ɨri, \ft Kiri' maimu yau; v. 30 yau nɨrɨ.\f* a'kwarʉ yen ton uya ensa' a'tai, to' uta'mo'kapɨtʉ'pʉ irakʉi', mɨrɨpan kon upirorʉnpɨtʉ'pʉ, “Ɨmɨrɨ rɨ kʉrɨ Papa Mumu!” ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\p  
\v 12 Sises uya e'se'ne' pe makoi a'kwarʉ yen ton panama'pʉ, kʉrɨ rɨ kʉrɨ rɨ ta to' uya namai' tʉpɨ'. 
\s1 Sises Uya Tʉpoitorʉ Ton Anʉmʉ'pʉ 
\r (Ma'siu 10:1-4; Ʉru' 6:12-16) 
\p  
\v 13 Sises utɨ'pʉ wʉ' pona rɨ, mɨrɨpan uya kamo i'se te'to' ton kɨ'ma'pʉ, mɨrɨpan kon uyee'pʉ ipiya',  
\v 14 mɨrɨpan kon anʉmʉ'pʉ iya 12 kaisa rɨ. To' koneka'pʉ iya itekare ekamai' enno'sa' kon pe, tʉpiyau to' e'to' pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ to' enno'to' pe tʉuya itekare ekamase'na,  
\v 15 tʉmeruntɨrʉ ke to' e'to' pe makoi a'kwarʉ enpa'kapɨ'nin nan pe. 
\p  
\v 16 Pʉsamoro si inanʉmʉ'san 12 kaisaron kon: Saiman (Pi'ta tukai' inese'tɨ'pʉ);  
\v 17 Isens mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Isaan, Sepiti munkɨ amʉ' (Powanoses tukai' to' ese'tɨ'pʉ iya, Korʉme Munkɨ ta e'kwa pe);  
\v 18 Anturu, Piri', Pa'taramiu, Ma'siu, Tamas, Isens Arʉ'piyas mu, Tatiyas, Saiman Usera' tukai' tesa'sen,\f + \fr 3:18 \fq Usera'\ft —Roman amʉ' enapai temo'ka kon i'sero'.\f* 
\v 19 Isutas Eskariya', eparankanin pe iyesi'pʉ na'ne'. \fig Sises uya tʉpoitorʉ ton anʉmʉ'pʉ 12 kaisa rɨ.|src="CN01699B.tif" size="span" loc="MRK 3:13-19" copy="David C. Cook" ref="3:14" \fig* 
\s1 Sises Mɨrɨ Awonsi'kɨ Pirɨsipupʉ 
\r (Ma'siu 12:22-32; Ʉru' 11:14-23; 12:10) 
\p  
\v 20 Sises ewomʉ'pʉ ɨutɨ ta'. Anpisin nɨ kanan amʉrakaa'pʉ Sises mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ipoitorʉ ton enta'nato' a'tai pʉra rɨ.  
\v 21 Serɨ etasa' itonpa ton uya a'tai, ikan to' utɨ'pʉ, apʉne pʉra ka'pon amʉ' uya, “Itano'masa',” ta pɨ'. 
\p  
\v 22 Tʉron kon Main pɨ' enupanin nan Surusiran winɨ iye'sa' kon uya ta'pʉ, “Pirɨsipupʉ\f + \fr 3:22 \fq Pirɨsipupʉ \ft - \fq Ɨutɨ epuru \ft ta e'kwa pe, Makoi ese' isakon.\f* esi mɨrɨ iyau. Makoi amʉ' epuru winɨ makoi a'kwarʉ ton enpa'kapɨtʉ iya mɨrɨ,” ta'pʉ.\x - \xo 3:22 \xt Ma'siu 9:34; 10:25\x* 
\p  
\v 23 Mɨrɨ uriya', Sises uya ka'pon amʉ' kɨ'ma'pʉ tʉpiya'. Mɨrɨ yau, panton ekama'pʉ iya to' pɨ': “Nai kasa Se'tan\f + \fr 3:23 \fq Se'tan\ft —Makoi ese' isakon, \fq Papa eseru ewaruma'tɨnin \ft ta e'kwa pe; v. 26 yau nɨrɨ.\f* nɨrɨ enpa'ka Se'tan uya tukai'?  
\v 24 Esa' wannɨ ton epantakapɨ'sa' yau, tiwano' pe rɨ ɨsewa'nomai' to' uko'mamʉ pen nɨ mɨrɨ.  
\v 25 Ɨsiwʉ' tau te'san epantakapɨ'sa' pe iyesi yau, tiwano' kon pe ɨsewa'nomai' kamoro uko'mamʉ pen nɨ mɨrɨ.  
\v 26 Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tiwano' pe rɨ Se'tan usewa'noma yau mɨrɨpan epantakapɨ'sa', moro iko'mamʉ pen nɨ mɨrɨ; iu'ma'to' rɨ e'seposa'. 
\p  
\v 27 “Ɨnʉ' rɨ ewomʉ pʉra iyesi mɨrɨ pana'pan ka'pon iwʉ' ta' tanporo itapuruui e'ma'tɨse'na, wapiya auronpɨ'sa' iya a'tai rɨken; mɨrɨ a'tai nin si, itimamin arɨ iya itiwʉ' tapai. 
\p  
\v 28 “I'napairon ekama uya ɨpɨ'nokon, tanporon nɨ ka'pon amʉ' makooi, isapema pe rɨ to' usauro'sa' rʉ'pʉ pɨ'\f + \fr 3:28 \ft Tʉron nɨ imenukasa' ton, \fq isapema pe rɨ to' usauro'sa' rʉ'pʉ pɨ' Papa pɨ', \ft tawon esi.\f* usentu'man.  
\v 29 E'tane ɨnʉ' rɨ kʉrɨ isapema pe Wakʉ A'kwarʉ pɨ' isauro'sa' pɨ' usentu'man pʉra rɨ iyesi mɨrɨ, apʉne pʉra siyaro' pe rɨ iye'makoimasa' mɨrɨ,” ta'pʉ iya.\x - \xo 3:29 \xt Ʉru' 12:10\x* 
\p  
\v 30 Sises uya serɨ ta'pʉ, tʉron kon uya, “Makoi a'kwarʉ esi iyau,” tasa' pɨ'. 
\s1 Sises San Mɨrɨ Awonsi'kɨ Iyakon Non 
\r (Ma'siu 12:46-50; Ʉru' 8:19-21) 
\p  
\v 31 Mɨrɨ a'tai, Sises san mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iyakon non uyee'pʉ. Te'soto'pɨ'se pʉroroi po ikɨ'manin ennoko'pʉ to' uya.  
\v 32 Anpisin ton nɨ ereutapɨ'sa' esi'pʉ Sises woi, mɨrɨpan kon uya ipana'tɨ'pʉ, “Asan mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ayakon non esi pʉroroi po awarinpa pɨ',” ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\p  
\v 33 Sises uya to' ekama'po'pʉ, “Ɨnʉ' si usan? Ɨnʉ' yan si uyakon non?” ta'pʉ iya.  
\v 34 To' si ene'pʉ iya, ka'pon amʉ' ereutapɨ'sa' tʉwoi, mɨrɨpan uya ta'pʉ, “Pʉsamoro usanon mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ uyakon non.  
\v 35 Ɨnʉ' rɨ Papa e'to' i'se ku'nin esi mɨrɨ uyakon pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ uparusi pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ usan pe,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\c 4  
\s1 Umɨ Pɨ' Te'sen Pantomʉ 
\r (Ma'siu 13:1-23; Ʉru' 8:4-15) 
\p  
\v 1 Sises kanan e'sara'tɨkaa'pʉ to' enupa pɨ' parau ku'pɨri piyau. Anpisin ton ka'pon amʉ' iwoi iyamʉrasa' kon esi'pʉ tu'ke rɨ. Mɨrɨ pɨ', iyekanwa'tɨ'pʉ kanau ya' ereutai' parau ku'pɨri kau, tanporo ka'pon amʉ' e'tane a'mun po, tuna e'pi po.\x - \xo 4:1 \xt Ʉru' 5:1-3\x* 
\v 2 Tu'kan pɨ' rɨ to' enupa'pʉ iya panton yai. To' enupa tʉuya yau, ta'pʉ iya to' pɨ': 
\p  
\v 3 “Apʉne etatɨ'! Umɨ pɨ' te'sen utɨ'pʉ kiyari ye' pɨnse'na tʉpa'karakai'.  
\v 4 Ipa'karaka iya koro'tau, tʉron nɨ ton uta'pokʉ'pʉ asanta ta'. Toron amʉ' uyee'pʉ mɨrɨpan kon uya ɨku'pʉ.  
\v 5 Tʉron nɨ ton uta'pokʉ'pʉ tɨ' pe te'sen ya', eke pe pʉra te'sen non ya'. Inke pʉra iya'ta'pʉ, apʉne pʉra i'nau pʉra non esi ke.  
\v 6 E'tane wʉi enu enu'sa' a'tai, a'ne' pe ipuru'pʉ iya mɨrɨpan aipʉta'pʉ, apʉne pʉra imi' ton utɨpɨ'sa' pʉra iyesi wenai.  
\v 7 Tʉron nɨ ton ite' ton uta'pokʉ'pʉ tikʉkenan nʉ'ta'. Iya'ta'pʉ, mɨrɨpan e'tane ɨwɨtanʉkʉ'pʉ iya, mɨrɨpan epeta'pʉ pen nɨ.  
\v 8 Mɨrɨ e'tane rɨ, tʉron nɨ ton uta'pokʉ'pʉ wakʉ non ya', mɨrɨpan uwa'ta'pʉ, mɨrɨpan epeta'pʉ tʉron nɨ ton esi'pʉ 30 kaisa rɨ ite'kwa iteperu, tʉron nɨ 60, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ 100 kaisarɨ rɨ ite'kwa e'to' airɨ inpɨmɨ'pʉ entai rɨ,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 9 Mɨrɨ a'tai Sises uya ta'pʉ, “Kʉrɨ tʉpana ke na'ne' etato' ike, tɨwɨ netai,” ta'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 10 Sises esi koro'tau tikin sarɨ, isaurokʉ etanin nʉ'san uyee'pʉ ipoitorʉ ton pokon pe ekama'pose'na, ɨ'rɨ ta iya e'kwa pe iyesi tukai'.  
\v 11 To' pɨ' ta'pʉ iya, “Ama' aino Papa e'to' esa' wannɨ pe e'tʉsa' ɨyena'nokon. E'tane kamoro mɨ airon kon pɨ' tanporon nɨ usekama panton yai, 
\q1  
\v 12 “‘to' uya rɨ enpɨtʉ mɨrɨ e'tane wakʉ pe to' uya ene pen nɨ, 
\q2 to' uya rɨ eta mɨrɨ ito'ka'nʉkʉi'ma pʉra rɨ. 
\q1 Mɨrɨ kupʉ to' uya pe iyesi yau, to' era'tɨ nesii'no Papa winɨkʉi', mɨrɨpan kon pɨ' nin nʉsentu'mai'no.’\f + \fr 4:12 \ft Aisaya 6:9-10\f* 
\m tasa' iya.” 
\p  
\v 13 Mɨrɨ a'tai, Sises uya ta'pʉ to' pɨ', “Serɨ pe' panton to'ka'nʉkʉ auya'nokon pʉra rɨ iyesi? Ɨ'rɨ kasa ken si tʉron nɨ panton to'ka'nʉkʉ kon pa?  
\v 14 Umɨ pɨ' te'sen uya Papa Maimu pa'karaka.  
\v 15 Tʉron kon ka'pon amʉ' esi ite' ipa'karakasa' uta'po'sa' asanta ta' kasa. Eta to' uya pe rɨ, Se'tan\f + \fr 4:15 \fq Se'tan\ft —Makoi ese' isakon, \fq Papa eseru ewaruma'tɨnin \ft ta e'kwa pe.\f* uyepʉ Main mo'kase'na to' ya' ipa'karakasa'.  
\v 16 Tʉron kon ka'pon amʉ' esi ite' ton tɨ' pona ita'po'sa' kasa. Main eta tʉuya'nokon a'tai, inke pʉra rɨ to' uya anʉmʉ tepori'ma kon pe.  
\v 17 E'tane to' mi' pʉra to' esi, inke to' uko'mamʉ pʉra iyesi. Ɨ'rɨ rɨ anpokʉmanin mɨrɨ pe pʉra kota'manin uye'sa' a'tai main uriya', inke pʉra to' e'nonka ipiyapai.  
\v 18 Mɨrɨ e'tane rɨ, tʉron kon ka'pon amʉ' esi mɨrɨ ite' tikʉkenan nʉ'ta' ipa'karakasa' kasa, main etanin nan,  
\v 19 e'tane tʉuko'manto' kon pɨ' tʉusewankamasan, ipʉrataaike' pe e'nɨto' nenku'tɨnʉ ton, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉron nɨ ton nɨ i'se to' e'to' uya main ɨwɨtanʉkʉ. Mɨrɨ uya nin si iyepeta pʉra ikupʉ.  
\v 20 Tʉron kon nin si esi mɨrɨ ite' wakʉ non ya' ipa'karakasa' kasa. To' uya main eta, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ to' uya rɨ anʉmʉ, mɨrɨpan kon epeta 30, 60, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ 100 kaisarɨ rɨ ite'kwa ipa'karakasa' rʉ'pʉ entai rɨ,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\s1 Raan'pu Pʉsau O'non 
\r (Ʉru' 8:16-18) 
\p  
\v 21 Ta'pʉ iya to' pɨ', “Ɨnʉ' rɨ pe' raan'pu ewonnʉ'nin pʉsau o'koi' itʉto' pe tʉuya, mɨrɨ pe pʉra e'nʉn nɨto' apon o'koi' rɨ? E'tane ru'ku, itapon pona pe' itʉnin pen ɨmɨrɨ?\x - \xo 4:21 \xt Ma'siu 5:15; Ʉru' 11:33\x* 
\v 22 Apʉne pʉra onansa' pe te'sen e'nɨponkato' pe rɨ iyesi; iwapu'tɨsa' pe te'sen epa'ka kɨpo'pona.\x - \xo 4:22 \xt Ma'siu 10:26; Ʉru' 12:2\x* 
\v 23 Kʉrɨ tʉpana ke na'ne' etato' ike, tɨwɨ netai!” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 24 Ta'pʉ iya kanan to' pɨ', “Ɨnetanʉ kon pɨ' wakʉ pe ɨsenuminkatɨ'. I'tuto' auya yai pe rɨ ɨnkupʉ'pʉ yai ɨyena' i'tu mɨrɨ—mɨrɨ entai rɨ.\x - \xo 4:24 \xt Ma'siu 7:2; Ʉru' 6:38\x* 
\v 25 Ɨnʉ' rɨ itesa' pe te'sen repa mɨrɨ miyarɨ rɨ. Ɨnʉ' rɨ ɨ'rɨ esa' pen nɨ enapai imo'ka mɨrɨ, itenawon nʉ'kwɨ rɨ,” ta'pʉ iya.\x - \xo 4:25 \xt Ma'siu 13:12; 25:29; Ʉru' 19:26\x* 
\s1 Ta'tasen Itena'pɨ Pantomʉ 
\p  
\v 26 Sises uya kanan takaa'pʉ, “Papa e'to' esa' wannɨ pe esi mɨrɨ ka'pon kiyari ye' pɨnnin tʉpa'karakai' tʉmainarʉ yau kasa.  
\v 27 Iye'nʉntane rɨ ewarupɨ nau, ipakasa' rɨ e'tane wʉi nai, kiyari ye' rɨ a'ta mɨrɨ, ɨ'rɨ kasa iye'sa' tukai' i'tu iya pʉra rɨ iyesi.  
\v 28 Non uya rɨ iya'tato' pe ikupʉ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iyepetato' pe rɨ nɨrɨ ikupʉ iya: wapiya ite' pe te'ton epa'ka; mɨrɨ tʉpo, i'pai, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ nin si iyɨ ton utaka.  
\v 29 Iyakʉ'pʉsa' a'tai nin si, iye'sara'tɨ mɨrɨ e'tʉrawasoman pɨ' a'tɨto' tʉuya tʉmariyarʉ, si'kʉrʉ tato' ke, apʉne pʉra anʉnto' weyu e'seposa' pɨ',” ta'pʉ iya.\x - \xo 4:29 \xt Isowerʉ 3:13\x* 
\s1 Mosta' Itese' Kiyari Ye' Ena'pɨ Pantomʉ 
\r (Ma'siu 13:31-32, 34; Ʉru' 13:18-19) 
\p  
\v 30 Takaa'pʉ iya kanan, “Ɨ'rɨ kasa Papa e'to' esa' wannɨ pe esi ta? Ɨ'rɨ rupɨ panton ekama, ekamanin pe?  
\v 31 Mosta' ena'pɨ, aiko rʉ'kwɨ kuru kasa iyesi, ɨnpɨmɨnʉ non ya'.  
\v 32 E'tane ipɨnsa' a'tai, iya'ta mɨrɨ eke pe rɨ tʉron nɨ ye' ton umɨ yawon entai rɨ. Eke ton pe rɨ ipanta ton esi toron amʉ' rɨ esi iti'nʉ'kenanʉ yau,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 33 Sises uya tekareei ekama'pʉ ka'pon amʉ' pɨ' tu'kan nɨ serɨ warai'nan panton yai'ne, to' uya ito'ka'nʉkʉ poken.  
\v 34 Panton tapurɨi' pʉra to' auro'ka iya poken pʉra rɨ iyesi'pʉ. E'tane tʉpoitorʉ ton pokon pe tesi a'tai tikin sarɨ, mɨrɨ ta iya e'kwa pe iyesi tukai' ekama'pʉ iya to' pɨ'. 
\s1 Sipa'sipa Ereutanʉkʉ'pʉ Sises Uya 
\r (Ma'siu 8:23-27; Ʉru' 8:22-25) 
\p  
\v 35 Mɨrɨ ko'mamiri pe rɨ, Sises uya, “Iratoi pona utɨnpai'nokon,” ta'pʉ tʉpoitorʉ ton pɨ'.  
\v 36 Anpisin ton ka'pon amʉ' nɨmɨ'pʉ to' uya. Sises e'to' iyau kanau ya' ipoitorʉ ton ekanwa'tɨ'pʉ, mɨrɨpan kon uya arɨ'pʉ. Tʉron nɨ ton nɨ kanau amʉ' esi'pʉ moro.  
\v 37 Pana' pe rɨ a'setun uyee'pʉ, sipa'sipa uya eke pe tuna anuku'pʉ kanau yau, isemʉ'nʉkʉ poken nɨ tʉku'se.  
\v 38 Sises esi'pʉ e'nʉn nɨ pɨ' iyaure yau, eke'nan tapon po. Ipoitorʉ ton uya enpaka'pʉ, mɨrɨpan pɨ', “Ti'sa, ina pe' aputa pɨ' ɨusewankama pʉra rɨ iyesi mɨrɨ?” ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\p  
\v 39 Sises e'mʉ'sa'kasa' uya a'setun eseremekʉ'pʉ, “E'paka'kɨ!” mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ sipa'sipa pɨ', “E'tʉtʉika'!” ta'pʉ iya. Mɨrɨ a'tai rɨ, a'setun ereuta'pʉ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wakʉ pe rɨ pata ena'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 40 Tʉpoitorʉ ton pɨ' Sises uya ta'pʉ, “Ɨ'rɨ pɨ' ɨyenari'nʉmʉ kon? Anapurɨnʉ kon pʉra rɨ marɨ pe' iyesi mɨrɨ?” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 41 E'tane to' etʉipɨ'sa' esi'pʉ, “Ɨnʉ' rɨ si pʉse rɨ ka'pon?” tukai' to' usekama'popɨtʉ'pʉ. “A'setun mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ sipa'sipa rɨ e'to' imaimu awɨrɨ!” ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\c 5  
\s1 Makoi A'kwarʉ Yen Ka'pon Epi'tɨ'pʉ Sises Uya 
\r (Ma'siu 8:28-34; Ʉru' 8:26-39) 
\p  
\v 1 Kerasin\f + \fr 5:1 \ft Tʉron nɨ ton inmenukasa' uya \fq Katarens \ft ta; tʉron nɨ ton inmenukasa' uya \fq Kerʉkesens \ft ta.\f* amʉ' nono pona to' utɨ'pʉ, parau ku'pɨri ratoi pon kon.  
\v 2 Sises ekanwakasa' koro'tau, ka'pon uruwai' apai iyepa'kasa' uya eporo'pʉ. Pʉse rɨ ka'pon yau makoi\f + \fr 5:2 \fq makoi, \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra \fq ɨri, \ft Kiri' maimu yau; v. 8, 13 yau rɨ nɨrɨ.\f* a'kwarʉ esi'pʉ,  
\v 3 mɨrɨpan uko'mansa' esi'pʉ uruwai' koro'tau, ɨnʉ' uya rɨ tauronpɨ'se enkurunpa poken pʉra rɨ iyenaka'sa' esi'pʉ, i'sen ke rɨ auronpɨtʉ poken pʉra rɨ.  
\v 4 Inke rɨ i'ta ton mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ itemiyatʉ ton auronpɨtʉ'pʉ to' uya esi'pʉ i'sen amʉ' ke, e'tane rɨ mɨrɨ ton nɨ i'kɨrɨpɨtʉ'pʉ iya, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wa'ka pun nɨ ti'ta pɨ' te'sen a'morʉpɨtʉ'pʉ iya. Ɨnʉ' uya ereutanʉkʉ poken pʉra rɨ, ipan pe rɨ pana' pe iyesi'pʉ.  
\v 5 Ewarupɨ' tau mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wʉi nai rɨ usarɨn pɨ' iyesi'pʉ uruwai' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wʉ' poro'ne rɨ, ukɨ'pɨ'nʉnpɨ' nɨ pɨ' rɨ, tiwano' pe rɨ uta'tɨpɨ' nɨ pɨ' tɨ' ke. 
\p  
\v 6 Ɨnnonsi'kɨ Sises ensa' tʉuya a'tai, iyeka'tumʉ'pʉ, mɨrɨpan e'sekunka'pʉ irau.  
\v 7 Mɨrɨpan ukɨ'pɨ'nʉmʉ'pʉ eke pe rɨ, “Sises, eke Papa Mumu, ɨ'rɨ pe ukupʉ i'se me'an? Papa pɨ', ‘Ikota'ma uya pen,’ ka'kɨ!” ta'pʉ iya.  
\v 8 Serɨ ta'pʉ iya, apʉne pʉra Sises uya makoi a'kwarʉ pɨ', “Pʉse ka'pon yapai epa'kakɨ!” tasa' pɨ'. 
\p  
\v 9 “Ɨnʉ' ɨyese'?” ta'pʉ Sises uya ipɨ'. 
\p “Anpisin ton kuwayau amʉ' uyese',” tukai' eikʉ'pʉ iya.  
\v 10 Ipan pe rɨ Sises pawana'tɨ pɨ' iyesi'pʉ mɨrɨ pata yapai ɨri a'kwarʉ ton ennoko iya namai'. 
\p  
\v 11 A'ko pe rɨ tu'kan kon nɨ peiruku amʉ' esi'pʉ enta'nan pɨ' i'kʉrʉ po.  
\v 12 Sises pawana'tɨ'pʉ ɨri a'kwarʉ ton uya peiruku amʉ' ya' tenno'to' kon pe iya.  
\v 13 To' nin si utɨto' pe ikupʉ'pʉ iya mɨrɨ. Ɨri a'kwarʉ ton nin si utɨ'pʉ mɨrɨ ka'pon yapai peiruku amʉ' ya'. Tanporo rɨ nin si, 2,000 e'to' airon kon peiruku amʉ' e'tʉrʉ'kwa'pʉ, mɨrɨpan kon aputa'pʉ parau ku'pɨri ka'. 
\p  
\v 14 To' pa'sima pɨ' te'san ka'pon amʉ' eka'tumʉ'pʉ pata pona itekareei ekamase'na, umɨ yau'ne rɨ te'san pana'tɨ'pʉ to' uya. Iye'ku'sa' rʉ'pʉ ense'na ka'pon amʉ' utɨ'pʉ.  
\v 15 To' uyee'pʉ Sises piya', mɨrɨpan kon uya kʉrɨ rɨ anpisin kuwayau makoi a'kwarʉ yen pe te'sen ka'pon ene'pʉ iyepontɨsa', iyereutasa' esi'pʉ, wakʉ pe iya'kwarʉ. Tanporo enari'ke' pe to' ena'pʉ mɨrɨ pɨ'.  
\v 16 Kamoro ennin nʉ'san uya ka'pon amʉ' pana'tɨ'pʉ iye'ku'sa' makoi a'kwarʉ yen ka'pon pɨ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ peiruku amʉ' pɨ' rɨ nɨrɨ.  
\v 17 Mɨrɨpan kon uya Sises ekama'po'pʉ itɨto' pe tʉnono kon apai. 
\p  
\v 18 Sises ekanwa'tɨ koro'tau kanau ya', makoi a'kwarʉ yen nʉ'pʉ ka'pon uya ekama'po'pʉ, “Aya'kɨrɨ utɨi'ya,” ta'pʉ iya.  
\v 19 E'tane Sises esi'pʉ itɨ i'se pʉra, e'tane, “Enna'pokɨ apata ya', ɨtonpa ton koro'ta'. Eke pe rɨ Itepuru nʉkupʉ'pʉ ɨpɨ' isentu'masa' ekamata,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 20 Mɨrɨpan utɨ'pʉ tanporo Te'ka'pores\f + \fr 5:20 \fq Te'ka'pores—10 Kaisaron Eke Pata Ton \ft ta e'kwa pe iyesi.\f* poro, Sises nʉkupʉ'pʉ tʉpɨ' ekama pɨ', mɨrɨ pɨ' tanporon kon usewansiuka'pʉ. \fig Sises ensa' tʉuya a'tai, iyeka'tumʉ'pʉ ipiya'.|src="CN01709B.tif" size="col" loc="MRK 5:1-20" copy="David C. Cook" ref="5:6" \fig* 
\s1 Iyeri'sa' Uri'san Mʉre, Takuru'kenan Uri'san 
\r (Ma'siu 9:18-26; Ʉru' 8:40-56) 
\p  
\v 21 Sises enna'po'pʉ iye'kwɨrɨtʉ'pʉ parau ku'pɨri ratoi pona. Mɨrɨ yau parau ku'pɨri ka'ta po, anpisin pe rɨ to' amʉra'pʉ iwoi.  
\v 22 Isairas, Esuwerʉ amʉ' usenupato' iwʉ' epuru uyee'pʉ, mɨrɨpan Sises ensa' tʉuya a'tai ita'mo'ka'pʉ i'ta piya'.  
\v 23 Mɨrɨpan ipan pe rɨ ipawana'tɨ'pʉ iya, “Aiko rʉ'kwɨ uyensi man takuru'ke, iyeri'kapʉ rɨ. Apʉne ɨsi'kɨ, ɨyemiyatʉ inonkatanʉ'kɨ ipona, mɨrɨpan usepi'tɨto' pe iyerikʉ namai',” ta'pʉ iya.  
\v 24 Mɨrɨpan Sises e'sara'tɨ'pʉ iya'kɨrɨ. Mɨrɨ a'tai, tu'kan kon nɨ ka'pon amʉ' utɨ'pʉ iya'kɨrɨ, to' uya iwontɨ'pʉ sen winɨ'ne rɨ. 
\p  
\v 25 Mɨrɨ yau, uri'san esi'pʉ 12 kaisa rɨ wʉipiya mʉn ennoko pɨ' iko'mansa'.  
\v 26 Tu'kan kon nɨ ta'ta amʉ' uya epi'tɨ tane, tʉpʉrataai rɨ enno'tane iya to' e'ma pɨ', e'tane tʉusepi'tɨ pe ekama tane iya, miyarɨ rɨ ipan pe rɨ iyena'pʉ.\x - \xo 5:26 \xt Topayas 2:10\x* 
\v 27 Mɨrɨpan uya rʉ'kwɨ Sises eta'pʉ, iyee'pʉ anpisin ton koro'tau ite'ma'pʉ pe.  
\v 28 “Ipon nʉ'kwɨ rɨ a'pɨ'sa' uya yau, usepi'tɨ rɨ mɨrɨ,” ta'pʉ iya ti'nau rʉ'kwɨ rɨ. 
\p  
\v 29 Ipon a'pɨtʉ'pʉ iya, mɨrɨpan mʉn tʉutɨsen ereuta'pʉ mɨrɨ a'tai rɨ. E'ne' pe iye'to' anpokʉmanin usepi'tɨ'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 30 Mɨrɨ a'tai rɨ, Sises uya tʉmeruntɨrʉ epa'ka'pʉ i'tu'pʉ, mɨrɨpan era'tɨpɨtʉ'pʉ anpisin koro'tau, mɨrɨpan uya ta'pʉ, “Ɨnʉ' upon a'pɨtʉi?” tai'ma. 
\p  
\v 31 Ipoitorʉ ton uya eikʉ'pʉ, “Ene auya pʉra pe' nai ka'pon amʉ' uya ɨwontɨsa'? Ɨ'rɨ pe iyesi pɨ', ‘Ɨnʉ' uya'pɨtʉi?’ ta auya?”  
\v 32 E'tane rɨ Sises uya tenu tʉpɨtʉ'pʉ, ɨnʉ' uya iku'sa' tukai'. 
\p  
\v 33 Mɨrɨpan uri'san uya i'tu'pʉ tʉpɨ' iye'ku'sa', mɨrɨpan uyee'pʉ e'tɨtɨtɨ'kai'ma rɨ tenari'nʉmʉ ke. Ita'mo'ka'pʉ i'ta piya', mɨrɨpan uya tanporo rɨ i'napairon ekama'pʉ ipɨ', tʉpɨ' iye'ku'sa' rʉ'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 34 Sises uya ta'pʉ ipɨ', “Ma'non, anapurɨnʉ uya rɨ ɨkonekasa' mɨrɨ wakʉ pe. Enta si tʉusewankamai' pʉra, ɨusepi'tɨsa' si mɨrɨ ɨyewankamanin apai,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 35 Mɨrɨ koro'tau, Isairas pana'tɨnin nan uyee'pʉ itiwʉ' tawonsi'kɨ, mɨrɨpan kon uya ta'pʉ, “Ɨyensi eri'ka'sa' man. Ti'sa rɨ kʉsanpokʉmai,” ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\p  
\v 36 Sises esi'pʉ to' maimu ɨnetapai pʉra rɨ, e'tane ta'pʉ iya ipɨ', “Kenari'nʉmʉi, e'tane apurɨkɨ rɨken,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 37 Mɨrɨpan ɨnʉ' rɨ utɨ i'se pʉra iyesi'pʉ ta'kɨrɨ, Pi'ta, Isens mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iyakon Isaan nɨken.  
\v 38 To' uyee'pʉ itepuru iwʉ' ta', mɨrɨ yau Sises uya tʉutano'masan eke pe rɨ ene'pʉ, pokoi pe rɨ tʉukɨ'pɨ'nʉnpɨ'se rɨ tʉukaransan eta'pʉ.  
\v 39 Mɨrɨpan ewomʉ'pʉ, ta'pʉ iya to' pɨ', “Ɨ'rɨ pe iyesi pɨ' tanporo rɨ autano'ma kon serɨ? Ɨ'rɨ pɨ' aukaramʉ kon? Mʉre eri'sa' pen, iye'nʉmʉ rɨken,” ta'pʉ iya.  
\v 40 Mɨrɨpan kon e'sara'tɨ'pʉ uta'kɨrɨn pɨ' ipɨ'. 
\p Tanporo to' enpa'ka'pʉ iya, mʉre kʉipʉnʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ isan mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ osorʉwawon kon nɨken tʉpoitorʉ ton pokon pe iyewomʉ'pʉ mʉre eri'sa' pata'se' airɨ.  
\v 41 Mɨrɨpan uya i'mʉ'sa'ka'pʉ itemiyatʉ pɨ' ta'sii', “Tari'ta kun!” ta'pʉ iya (“Uri'san mʉre, e'mʉ'sa'ka', ta uya ɨpɨ',” ta tʉuya e'kwa pe).  
\v 42 Mɨrɨ a'tai rɨ, iye'mʉ'sa'ka'pʉ, mɨrɨpan e'sara'tɨ'pʉ usarɨn pɨ' (12 kaisaron iwʉipiyaai pe iyesi'pʉ). Serɨ e'ku'sa' pɨ' ipan pe to' usewansiuka'pʉ.  
\v 43 Sises uya ipan pe to' pɨ' ta'pʉ, “Kʉsekamatʉu ɨnʉ' yan pɨ' rɨ. Irepatɨ' ɨ'rɨ rʉ'kwɨ rɨ iyenta'nato' ipɨ' ke,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\c 6  
\s1 Sises Ewaruma'tɨ'pʉ Nasare' Pon Kon Uya 
\r (Ma'siu 13:53-58; Ʉru' 4:16-30) 
\p  
\v 1 Sises uya mɨrɨ pata nɨmɨ'pʉ, iyenna'po'pʉ tʉpata'se' ya', ipoitorʉ ton nɨ itonpa pe.  
\v 2 Sapa' e'seposa' a'tai, to' enupa pɨ' iye'sara'tɨ'pʉ Esuwerʉ amʉ' usenupato' iwʉ' tau. Tu'ke rɨ ka'pon amʉ' esi'pʉ mɨrɨ yau, mɨrɨpan eta tʉuya'nokon a'tai, tanporon kon nɨ usewansiuka'pʉ. “Nai yau serɨ ton eporo'pʉ pʉse rɨ ka'pon uya?” tukai' to' usekama'popɨtʉ'pʉ. “Ɨ'rɨ rɨ pu'ketʉ ke irepasa' pe iyesi? Ɨ'rɨ kasa rɨ eke rɨ Papa tʉrawasooi kupʉ iya?  
\v 3 Kiya'pinta pen pe' pʉse rɨ? Meri mʉre; Isens, Isoses, Isutas mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Saiman pokon rui? Serɨ yau pe' upiyau'nokon iparusi ton pʉra nai?” ta'pʉ to' uya. Mɨrɨpan kon ɨkɨnʉmʉ'pʉ ipɨ'. 
\p  
\v 4 Sises uya ta'pʉ to' pɨ', “Ipata'se' yau rɨken, itonpa ton koro'tau mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ itiwʉ' rɨ tau pu'kena' nama pʉra iyesi,” ta'pʉ iya.\x - \xo 6:4 \xt Isaan 4:44\x* 
\v 5 Eke Papa tʉrawasooi kupʉ iya poken pʉra rɨ iyesi'pʉ mɨrɨ yau, e'tane rɨ temiyatʉ rɨken nonkapɨtʉ'pʉ iya tu'kan kon pen ka'pon amʉ' takuru'kena' nan pona, mɨrɨpan kon epi'tɨpɨtʉ'pʉ iya.  
\v 6 Ipan pe rɨ to' pɨ' isewansiukapɨtʉ'pʉ, apʉne pʉra apurɨto' to' uya pʉra iyesi pɨ'. 
\s1 Sises Uya 12 Kaisaron Kon Tʉpoitorʉ Ton Ennoko'pʉ 
\r (Ma'siu 10:5-15; Ʉru' 9:1-6) 
\p Mɨrɨpan Sises utɨpɨtʉ'pʉ eke iwa ton pata ton kaisa rɨ'ne, ka'pon amʉ' enupapɨtʉ pɨ'.  
\v 7 Tʉpoitorʉ ton, 12 kaisaron kon tʉkɨ'mai' tʉpiya', to' enno'pɨtʉ'pʉ iya asa'rɨ'ne, mɨrɨpan kon repa'pʉ iya to' meruntɨrʉ ke, makoi a'kwarʉ entai to' e'to' pe.  
\v 8 Serɨ ton ke to' auro'ka'pʉ iya, “Ɨ'rɨ rɨ kʉsatʉu aya'kɨrɨ'nokon ɨutɨ kon koro'tau, teke'sen nɨken—tʉwenantu ke pʉra rɨ, tʉpaikii ke pʉra rɨ, pʉrata pʉra rɨ ɨpokʉrʉʉi kon yau mʉtɨtʉi'.  
\v 9 Sapato yau rɨ e'tɨ'; tu'ke ipona ɨpon kon pʉro'pon yau ke'tʉu,” ta'pʉ iya to' pɨ'.  
\v 10 To' auro'ka'pʉ iya kanan, “To' uya ɨyereutanʉ'sa' kon na'ne' airɨ rɨ, mɨrɨ rɨ ɨutɨ tau me'tʉi' pata nɨmɨ auya'nokon pona rɨ.  
\v 11 Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ pata uya ɨyereutanʉ'sa' kon pʉra iyesi yau, mɨrɨ pe pʉra ɨyetapai'nokon pʉra rɨ iyesi yau, to' nɨmɨ auya'nokon a'tai a'ta kon mʉtɨutɨpɨ'tʉi'. Serɨ uya rɨ to' pana'tɨ mɨrɨ Papa uya to' kota'mato' oton ekamanin pe,”\x - \xo 6:11 \xt Ʉru' 10:4-11; Inkupʉ'pʉ 13:51\x* ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 12 Mɨrɨpan kon utɨ'pʉ ka'pon amʉ' pɨ' itekare ekamase'na, to' era'tɨto' pe tʉmakooi kon apai.  
\v 13 Mɨrɨpan tu'ke rɨ makoi a'kwarʉ enpa'kapɨtʉ'pʉ to' uya, mɨrɨpan kon uya tu'kan kon nɨ takuru'kena' nan karapaimapɨtʉ'pʉ to' epi'tɨpɨtʉ'pʉ to' uya.\x - \xo 6:13 \xt Isens 5:14\x* 
\s1 Isaan Pa'tes Uma'tasa' 
\r (Ma'siu 14:1-12; Ʉru' 9:7-9) 
\p  
\v 14 Kin Era' uya serɨ eta'pʉ, apʉne pʉra Sises ese' enasa' esi'pʉ wakʉ pe kuru ti'tusen pe. Tʉron kon\f + \fr 6:14 \ft Tʉron nɨ imenukasa', \fq Kʉrɨ rɨ, \ft tawon esi.\f* uya, “Isaan Pa'tes rɨ e'mʉ'sa'kasa' mɨrɨ terikʉ'pʉ apai; mɨrɨ wenai, eke Papa tʉrawasooi kupʉ iya mɨrɨ,” ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\p  
\v 15 Tʉron kon uya, “Iraisa kʉrɨ rɨ,” ta'pʉ. 
\p Tʉron kon uya rɨ kanan, “Pu'kena' kʉrɨ rɨ, penaro' kon pu'kena' amʉ' esi'pʉ waraino,” ta'pʉ.\x - \xo 6:15 \xt Ma'siu 16:14; Ma' 8:28; Ʉru' 9:19\x* 
\p  
\v 16 Era' uya etasa' a'tai, “Isaan Pa'tes sa'ne kʉrɨ rɨ ko! I'pai unakʉtʉ'pʉ, e'tane ito'pansa' terikʉ'pʉ apai!” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 17 Apʉne pʉra Era' uya rɨ Isaan a'sito' pe ikupʉ'pʉ. Auronpɨ'to' pe to' uya ikupʉ'pʉ iya, mɨrɨpan tʉto' pe pariki'si ta'. Era' uya serɨ kupʉ'pʉ Eratiyas wenai, tʉnmari'ma'pʉ takon Piri' no'pʉ pe rɨ iye'tane.  
\v 18 Isaan Pa'tes e'pɨtʉ'pʉ Era' auro'ka pɨ', “Main awɨrɨ ɨwesi pe pʉra iyesi mɨrɨ ayakon no'pʉ anʉnsa' auya na'ne',” ta'pʉ iya ipɨ'.\x - \xo 6:18 \xt Ʉru' 3:19-20\x* 
\p  
\v 19 Mɨrɨ uya Eratiyas ɨkɨnʉnpasa' esi'pʉ Isaan nɨ ɨnwɨpai, e'tane ikupʉ iya poken pʉra iyesi'pʉ,  
\v 20 apʉne pʉra Era' esi'pʉ Isaan namanin pe, iwapu pe iyesi'pʉ i'tu tʉuya ke, ipokena' pe, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wakʉ pe. Isaurokʉ eta tʉuya a'tai, ekamʉra rɨ iyenapɨ'pɨtʉ'pʉ mɨrɨ rɨ e'tane imaimu ɨnetapai iyesi'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 21 Mɨrɨ yau nin si, iweyu e'sepokaa'pʉ mɨrɨ. Tentu'pʉ weyu rʉ'pʉ a'tai, Era' uya enta'nan kupʉ'pʉ eke ton itepuru ton, soisa amʉ' epuru ton, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ eke ton Kiyarari pata yawon kon ewe'to' iya.  
\v 22 Eratiyas mʉre uye'sa' a'tai amanʉnse'na, imanʉmʉ uya wakʉ pe rɨ Era' kupʉ'pʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ inkɨ'ma'san nɨrɨ. Mɨrɨ pɨ', kin uya ta'pʉ uri'san pɨ', “I'se ɨwe'to' pɨ' rɨ uyekama'pokɨ ɨrepa uya mɨrɨ ike,” ta'pʉ iya.  
\v 23 Eke pe rɨ auro'ka'pʉ iya tʉnku'ton pɨ', “Ɨnekama'po'pʉ ke rɨ ɨrepa uya, a'sa'mʉyai itesa' pe e'to' pata ke rɨ,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 24 Mɨrɨ pɨ' uri'san epa'ka'pʉ tʉsan ekama'pose'na. “Ɨ'rɨ kuru rɨ ekama'po uya serɨ?” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p “Isaan Pa'tes i'pai rʉ'pʉ ekama'po',” tukai' eikʉ'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 25 Mɨrɨ a'tai rɨ, tʉusenutɨi' uri'san enna'po'pʉ kin piya', “Urepa auya i'se e'ai' serɨ pe Isaan Pa'tes i'pai rʉ'pʉ ke parapi po!” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 26 Kin upokoita'pʉ tʉusaurokʉ'pʉ pɨ' ipan pe, e'tane, apʉne pʉra ikupʉ uya kuru tasa' tʉuya rʉ'pʉ pɨ' tʉnkɨ'ma'san pana airɨ, inurunpa iya poken pʉra iyesi'pʉ.  
\v 27 Mɨrɨpan uya inke pʉra i'pairʉkanin ennoko'pʉ, Isaan i'pai rʉ'pʉ ne'to' pe iya. Itɨ'pʉ pariki'si ta', mɨrɨpan uya Isaan i'pairʉka'pʉ.  
\v 28 Mɨrɨpan uya inee'pʉ parapi po, mɨrɨpan uya itʉrʉ'pʉ uri'san ena', mɨrɨpan uya itʉrʉ'pʉ tʉsan ena'.  
\v 29 Mɨrɨ tetai', Isaan poitorʉ rʉ'san uyee'pʉ, mɨrɨpan kon uya itekepu arɨ'pʉ, iu'na'tɨto' pe tʉuya'nokon tɨ' akasa' uruwai' pe ya'. 
\s1 5,000 Kaisaron Kon Ewekʉ'pʉ Sises Uya 
\r (Ma'siu 14:13-21; Ʉru' 9:10-17; Isaan 6:1-14) 
\p  
\v 30 Enno'sa' kon enna'posa' amʉra'pʉ Sises woi, mɨrɨpan kon uya tanporo tʉnkupʉ'pʉ kon mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ to' enupa'pʉ tʉuya'nokon nɨ ekama'pʉ.  
\v 31 Mɨrɨ yau, tu'ke rɨ ka'pon amʉ' uye'pɨtʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ to' utɨpɨtʉ esi'pʉ, Sises mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ipoitorʉ ton enta'nato' a'tai pʉra rɨ iyesi'pʉ. Mɨrɨ uriya', to' pɨ' ta'pʉ iya, “Utɨnpai'nokon mɨ airɨ rɨ tʉ'kena'pɨ yau e'nɨ poken mɨrɨ koro'tau ɨumoronkapʉ kon pa,” ta'pʉ iya.  
\v 32 Mɨrɨpan kon e'sara'tɨ'pʉ utɨn pɨ' kanau yau tʉ'kena'pɨ pata ya'. 
\p  
\v 33 Tu'kan kon nɨ ka'pon amʉ' uya to' ene'pʉ, to' i'tu'pʉ to' uya kamoro pe. Mɨrɨpan kon eka'tumʉ'pʉ tanporo pata ton apai'ne irawɨrɨ a'mun poro, mɨrɨpan kon uya pata eporo'pʉ to' rawɨrɨ. 
\p  
\v 34 Sises ekanwakasa' uya tu'ke anpisin pe ka'pon amʉ' ensa' a'tai, ipan pe rɨ to' pɨ' isentu'ma'pʉ, apʉne pʉra to' esi'pʉ karimeru amʉ' esi tʉpa'simanin ke pʉra kasa. Mɨrɨpan kon enupa pɨ' iye'sara'tɨ'pʉ tu'kan pɨ' rɨ. 
\p  
\v 35 Pata uko'mansa' a'tai, ipoitorʉ ton uyee'pʉ ipiya', mɨrɨpan kon uya, “Pata uko'manka'sa' kuru rɨ man, ɨnnon sa'ne serɨ pata ko,” ta'pʉ.  
\v 36 “Ka'pon amʉ' enno'kɨ a'ko pan parɨ umɨ ton mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ eke iwa ton pata amʉ' ya'ne, tiwano' kon pe tenta'nato' kon ipɨ' e'mato' pe to' uya,” ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\p  
\v 37 E'tane to' eikʉ'pʉ iya, “Ɨmɨrɨ'nokon pe rʉ'kwɨ rɨ to' irepatɨ' to' enta'nato' ike ke,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p Ta'pʉ to' uya ipɨ', “Mɨrɨ uya 8 kaisa rɨ kapʉi ka'pon e'tʉrawasomasa' epe'pʉ\f + \fr 6:37 \fq 8 kaisa rɨ kapʉi ka'pon e'tʉrawasomasa' epe'pʉ\ft —200 tenariyas itese' Kiri' maimu yau. Tikin nɨ pʉrata pun esi tikin nɨ wʉi yau tʉrawaso pɨ' isenupasa' pen e'mato' ike. (Apʉne Ma'siu 20:2 enkɨ.)\f* mo'ka mɨrɨ! Mɨrɨ kaisa rɨ ken pe' ennoko pʉreti pɨ' to' ewe'to' pe?” ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\p  
\v 38 Sises uya to' ekama'po'pʉ, “Ɨ'rɨ kaisa rɨ rʉ'kwɨ pʉreti nai ɨpiyau'nokon? Apʉne entantɨ',” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p To' uya ensa' a'tai, “5 kaisaron nʉ'kwɨ pʉreti mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ asa'ron kon nʉ'kwɨ moro' amʉ' man,” ta'pʉ to' uya ipɨ'. 
\p  
\v 39 Sises uya ta'pʉ tʉpoitorʉ ton pɨ', “Ka'pon amʉ' amʉranʉ'pɨ'tɨ' tamu'kuru' ke'ne mɨrɨpan kon ereutapɨ'to' pe wana' pona,” ta'pʉ iya.  
\v 40 Ka'pon amʉ' ereutapɨtʉ'pʉ tamu'kuru' ke'ne 100 kaisa rɨ'ne mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ 50 kaisa rɨ'ne. 
\p  
\v 41 Mɨrɨpan Sises uya 5 kaisaron itekiino pʉreti mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ asa'ron kon nʉ'kwɨ moro' amʉ' anʉmʉ'pʉ. Ka'ta' tenu tʉtʉse tenki ta'pʉ iya Papa pɨ', i'kwɨ'pɨtʉ'pʉ iya. Itʉrʉ'pʉ iya tʉpoitorʉ ton uya ekanto' pe ka'pon amʉ' ena'. Mɨrɨ kasa rɨ marɨ asa'ron kon nʉ'kwɨ moro' amʉ' kupʉ'pʉ iya to' kaisa rɨ to' e'to' pe. 
\p  
\v 42 Tanporon kon nɨ enta'na'pʉ ta'wetapɨ'se,  
\v 43 mɨrɨpan ipoitorʉ ton uya 12 kaisa rɨ pa'siki'ti pʉreti mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ moro' amʉ' tonpa'pʉ e'nonkasa' anuku'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 44 Warawoti'si amʉ' pʉreti pɨ' iyenta'nasa' kon tu'kanoro esi'pʉ 5,000 kaisa rɨ. 
\s1 Sises Usarɨ'pʉ Tuna Po 
\r (Ma'siu 14:22-33; Isaan 6:15-21) 
\p  
\v 45 Inke pʉra tʉpoitorʉ ton ekanwa'tɨto' pe kanau ya' ikuu'pʉ iya, to' utɨto' pe tʉrawɨrɨ Pe'saita pona, anpisin enno'tane tʉuya.  
\v 46 To' nɨmɨ tʉpo, wʉ' pona itɨ'pʉ ɨpʉremai'. 
\p  
\v 47 Mɨrɨ a'tai ko'mamʉ pe pata enaka'tane, kanau esi'pʉ parau ku'pɨri aporo' po. Mɨrɨ koro'tau, Sises esi'pʉ tikin sarɨ a'mun po.  
\v 48 Tʉpoitorʉ ton utanpokʉma ene'pʉ iya, tʉkanwa kon i'kura i'se, apʉne pʉra a'setun uya to' kota'ma esi'pʉ to' winɨkʉi' tʉuyepʉ ke. Awanakʉi', 3 a'kʉra' mɨrɨ pe pʉra 6 a'kʉra' rɨ to' piya' iyee'pʉ parau ku'pɨri pʉro'po. To' rɨ entaka iya esi'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 49 E'tane parau ku'pɨri pʉro'po isarɨ ene tʉuya'nokon a'tai, a'kwarʉ'pʉ pe to' uya ekama'pʉ, mɨrɨpan kon upirorʉnpɨtʉ'pʉ,  
\v 50 apʉne pʉra tanporo ensa' tʉuya'nokon pɨ', mɨrɨpan kon etʉipɨtʉ'pʉ ipan pe. 
\p Inke pʉra Sises uya ta'pʉ to' pɨ', “Meruntɨ pe e'tɨ'! Urɨ rɨ. Ketʉipɨ'tʉu,” ta'pʉ iya.  
\v 51 Mɨrɨ a'tai rɨ, iyekanwa'tɨ'pʉ kanau ya' to' piya'. Mɨrɨ a'tai rɨ, a'setun ereuta'pʉ, mɨrɨpan poitorʉ ton usewansiuka'pʉ,  
\v 52 apʉne pʉra to' uya ito'ka'nʉ'sa' pʉra iyesi'pʉ ɨ'rɨ kuru ta e'kwa pe pʉreti esi tukai'; to' ewan nɨ usa'mantasa' esi'pʉ. 
\s1 Takuru'kena' Nan Epi'tɨpɨtʉ'pʉ Sises Uya 
\r (Ma'siu 14:34-36) 
\p  
\v 53 To' ɨ'kwɨrɨ'sa' a'tai, to' e'te'ka'pʉ Kenesare' airɨ, mɨrɨpan kon uya tʉkanwa kon ewa'tɨ'pʉ mɨrɨ yau.  
\v 54 To' ekanwaka pe rɨ, ka'pon amʉ' uya Sises i'tusa' esi'pʉ.  
\v 55 Mɨrɨpan kon eka'tunpɨtʉ'pʉ, tanporo mɨrɨ pata nono yau'ne, mɨrɨpan kon uya takuru'kena' nan epɨrinpɨ'sa' te'kwe' kon po nee'pʉ ipiya', mɨrɨ airɨ iyesi tukai' etasa' tʉuya'nokon airɨ.  
\v 56 Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Sises utɨpɨ'to' airɨ'ne—eke iwa ton pata amʉ', umɨ amʉ' awɨrɨ'ne rɨ—mɨrɨpan ka'pon amʉ' uya takuru'kena' nan apɨtʉ'pʉ kʉrʉpo'po pɨ' e'nɨto' pata'se' ya', mɨrɨpan kon uya ipan pe ipawana'tɨ'pʉ takuru'kena' nan uya ipon e'pi a'pɨ'to' pe, mɨrɨpan tanporon kon a'pɨ'nin nʉ'san usepi'tɨpɨtʉ'pʉ. 
\c 7  
\s1 Wakʉ Mɨrɨ Awonsi'kɨ Wakʉ Pen 
\r (Ma'siu 15:1-9) 
\p  
\v 1 Pari'si amʉ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Main pɨ' enupanin nan iye'sa' kon Surusiran winɨ amʉrasa' esi'pʉ Sises woi,  
\v 2 mɨrɨpan kon uya tʉron kon ipoitorʉ ton enta'na ene'pʉ ɨri, ikorʉkasa' pen temiyatʉ kon ke. 
\p  
\v 3 (Pari'si amʉ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Esuwerʉ amʉ' kamoro tenta'nasan pen temiyatʉ kon korʉkasa' tʉuya'nokon pʉra iye'tane tepuru kon eseru awɨrɨ.  
\v 4 Ɨ'rɨ rɨ kʉrʉpo'po iwʉ' tapai ine'sa' pɨ', to' enta'na pen wapiya kuru ikorʉkasa' tʉuya'nokon a'tai rɨken to' enta'na,\f + \fr 7:4 \ft Tʉron nɨ imenukasa', \fq Ɨ'rɨ rɨ pɨ' to' enta'na pʉra iyesi kʉrʉpo'po iwʉ' tapai tʉuye'sa' kon tʉpo wapiya tekorʉkasa' kon a'tai rɨken to' enta'na, \ft tawon esi.\f* mɨrɨpan kon uya tenupa'pʉ kon nɨ kupʉ iye'to' awɨrɨ Papa enu yau, tʉkokʉ kon, terin kon, ka'pa konekasa' tʉ'sawʉ kon, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ te'kwe' kon amʉ' rɨ korʉka.\f + \fr 7:4 \ft Tʉron nɨ imenukasa' ton yau, \fq te'kwe' kon amʉ' rɨ, \ft tawon pʉra iyesi.\f*) 
\p  
\v 5 Mɨrɨ pɨ' Pari'si amʉ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Main pɨ' enupanin nan uya Sises ekama'po'pʉ, “Ɨ'rɨ pe iyesi pɨ' ɨpoitorʉ ton esi pʉra iyesi uyepuru kon eseru rʉ'pʉ awɨrɨ, e'tane ɨri rɨ temiyatʉ kon ke to' enta'na?” ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\p  
\v 6 Sises uya to' eikʉ'pʉ, “Ipoken nɨ Aisaya usaurokʉ'pʉ ɨpɨ'nokon, wakʉ pe te'ku'san pɨ'; iye'menukasa' na'ne': 
\q1 “‘Pʉsamoro uya tʉnta kon ke rɨken unama; 
\q2 e'tane ɨnnɨ rɨ to' ewan esi upiyapai. 
\q1  
\v 7 To' ɨpʉrema upɨ' ɨ'rɨ epoton kon kasa rɨ; 
\q2 to' usenupato' esi ka'pon amʉ' uya to' enupa'pʉ iyawɨrɨ to' e'to'.’\f + \fr 7:7 \ft Aisaya 29:13\f* 
\m tukai'.  
\v 8 Ɨmɨrɨ'nokon uya Papa uya ayapiyontɨto' kon apurɨ pʉra iyesi, e'tane ka'pon uya ɨyenupato' kon apurɨ auya'nokon nɨken,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 9 Mɨrɨpan uya ta'pʉ to' pɨ', “Teseru ke kuru ɨwesi kon Papa Maimu nonka kon pa, ɨyeseru kon awɨrɨ ɨwesi kon pa!  
\v 10 Mosi' uya tasa', ‘Ɨkʉipʉnʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ asan inamakɨ,’\f + \fr 7:10 \ft E'sotas 20:12; Isu'taronomi 5:16\f* mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ, ‘Ɨnʉ' rɨ tʉkʉipʉnʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉsan nɨ pa'nʉ'nin wɨto' pe iyesi.’\f + \fr 7:10 \ft E'sotas 21:17; Ripaiti'kas 20:9\f* 
\v 11 E'tane ta auya'nokon, ka'pon uya tʉkʉipʉnʉ mɨrɨ pe pʉra tʉsan pɨ' ta pe iyesi yau, ‘Ɨ'rɨ rɨ ɨpika'tɨnin pe uwinɨ ɨneporonʉ pan e'tane Kapan pe man’ (Papa ena' iye'tʉka'sa' man ta e'kwa pe),  
\v 12 mɨrɨ si ɨ'rɨ rɨ kupʉ iya poken pʉra tʉkʉipʉnʉ mɨrɨ pe pʉra tʉsan iwano' pe ikupʉ auya'nokon.  
\v 13 Mɨrɨ kasa si ipʉra Papa Maimu kupʉ auya'nokon ɨyeseru kon mɨn winɨ rɨ iyɨ'kwɨrɨ'pɨ'sa' ke. Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tu'ke rɨ ɨnkupʉnʉ kon man serɨ warai'nan,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\s1 Ɨri Pe Ka'pon Ku'nin 
\r (Ma'siu 15:10-20) 
\p  
\v 14 Sises uya anpisin ton nɨ kɨ'makaa'pʉ kanan tʉpiya', mɨrɨpan uya ta'pʉ to' pɨ', “Apʉne uyetatɨ', tanporo ɨmɨrɨ'nokon, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ se ito'ka'nʉ'tɨ'.  
\v 15 Mɨrɨ yau ɨ'rɨ rɨ tewonsen pʉra iyesi mɨrɨ ka'pon ya' kɨpo'ponsi'kɨ ɨri pe iku'se'na, e'tane ka'pon apai iyepa'kasa' uya ɨri pe ikupʉ,”\f + \fr 7:15 \ft Tʉron nɨ imenukasa' ton uya v. 16 ke iponantɨsa' se kasa: \fv 16 \fv*\fq Mɨrɨpan tʉpana ke ɨwesi kon a'tai etatɨ'. \ft (Apʉne Ma' 4:23 enkɨ.)\f* ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 17 Mɨrɨpan uya anpisin ton nɨ nɨmɨ'pʉ, itɨ'pʉ ɨutɨ ta', mɨrɨpan ipoitorʉ ton uya ekama'po'pʉ serɨ panton pɨ'.  
\v 18 “Ito'ka'nʉ'nin nan pe pʉra rɨ pe' ɨwesi kon? Ene auya'nokon pʉra pe' iyesi, ɨ'rɨ rɨ kɨpo'ponsi'kɨ tewonsen ka'pon ya' uya, ɨri pe ikupʉ pʉra iyesi?  
\v 19 Apʉne pʉra itɨ pen mɨrɨ itewan ya' e'tane itɨ mɨrɨ iwenu'pɨ ya', mɨrɨpan epa'ka ipun apai,” ta'pʉ iya. (Sises uya serɨ ta'pʉ, tanporo rɨ sa'ne kiyari esi mɨrɨ ko enta'nan nɨto' ipɨ' pe, ta tʉuya e'kwa pe.) 
\p  
\v 20 Mɨrɨpan uya rɨ ta'pʉ, “Nepa'kayai'ne' ka'pon yapai uya nin ikupʉ mɨrɨ ɨri pe.  
\v 21 Apʉne pʉra ka'pon amʉ' ewan yapai ɨri isenuminkato' epa'ka, tekumasen pe, ama' e' pe, te'wɨsen pe,  
\v 22 iyemari'masa' ekumankanin pe, mentaino pe, e'wɨpaino, enku'tɨnin ye' pe, ɨri ku'nin pe rɨ, tɨkɨntai', teseru'tɨi' ka'pon pɨ' tʉusauro'sen pe, mɨ pe rɨ te'ku'sen pe, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ita'kwarʉ pʉra te'sen pe.  
\v 23 Tanporo serɨ ton makoi eseru ton epa'kasa' ka'pon apai uya ɨri pe rɨ ikupʉ,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\s1 Uri'san Mʉre Epi'tɨ'pʉ Sises Uya 
\r (Ma'siu 15:21-28) 
\p  
\v 24 Sises uya mɨrɨ pata nɨmɨ'pʉ pata Taya itese' pʉ'kʉ pona,\f + \fr 7:24 \ft Tu'kan nɨ wapiya iwa imenukasa' ton uya: \fq Taya mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Saitan, \ft ta.\f* mɨrɨpan ewomʉ'pʉ ɨutɨ ta', ɨnʉ' uya rɨ ti'tu i'se pʉra rɨ iyesi'pʉ, mɨrɨ yau iyesi tukai', e'tane iye'so'namʉ poken pʉra rɨ iyesi'pʉ.  
\v 25 Inke pʉra rɨ etasa' tʉuya a'tai, aiko rʉ'kwɨ makoi\f + \fr 7:25 \fq makoi, \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra \fq ɨri, \ft Kiri' maimu yau.\f* a'kwarʉ yen imʉre uri'san uyee'pʉ i'ta piya' ata'mo'kai'.  
\v 26 Pʉse rɨ uri'san esi'pʉ ka'kʉran pe, tʉron nɨ pata winon, iyentusa' Poni'siya, Siriya yawon yau, mɨrɨpan uya Sises pawana'tɨ'pʉ ɨri a'kwarʉ enpa'kato' pe iya tʉmʉre yapai. 
\p  
\v 27 “Wapiya mʉre amʉ' nenta'nakapʉi tanporo i'se te'to' kon pe, apʉne pʉra ipoken pʉra iyesi mʉre amʉ' yu pʉreti eno'ma to' ikʉn non pero amʉ' ena',” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 28 “Ewai', Epuru, e'tane pero amʉ' tepʉrʉ o'non kon nɨ mʉre amʉ' i'kiyari punu'pɨ pɨ' tenta'nasan ko,” ta'pʉ uri'san uya. 
\p  
\v 29 Sises uya ta'pʉ ipɨ', “Mɨrɨ kasa uyei'sa' auya pɨ', enna'pokɨ pata pona; ɨri a'kwarʉ utɨkaa'pʉ man ɨmʉre yapai,” ta'pʉ iya.  
\v 30 Mɨrɨpan si enna'pokaa'pʉ pata pona, mɨrɨpan uya tʉmʉre e'pɨrinkasa' te'kwe' po eporo'pʉ, ɨri a'kwarʉ rɨ si epa'kakaa'pʉ esi'pʉ iyapai. 
\s1 Ipana Pʉn, Imaimu Pʉn Ka'pon Epi'tɨ'pʉ Sises Uya 
\p  
\v 31 Sises utɨ'pʉ pata Taya pʉ'kʉ poi, mɨrɨpan utɨ'pʉ Saitan poro parau ku'pɨri Kiyarari poro, itɨ esi'pʉ Te'ka'pores\f + \fr 7:31 \fq Te'ka'pores \ft ta mɨrɨ \fq 10 kaisaron eke ton pata amʉ' \ft ta e'kwa pe.\f* nono awɨrɨ'ne rɨ.  
\v 32 Tʉron kon ka'pon amʉ' uya ipana pʉn, tʉusauro'sen pen ka'pon nee'pʉ, mɨrɨpan kon uya Sises ekama'po'pʉ temiyatʉ tʉto' pe iya ipona. 
\p  
\v 33 Mɨrɨpan arɨ'pʉ iya anpisin ton piyapai tikin sarɨ, temiyatʉ muku'pɨ tʉrʉ'pʉ iya ipana ya', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iyeta'ta'pʉ, mɨrɨpan uya iyani a'pɨtʉ'pʉ.  
\v 34 Mɨrɨpan Sises uya tenu tʉrʉ'pʉ ka' winɨkʉi', mɨrɨpan uya e'se'ne' pe teruparu enpa'ka pe ta'pʉ iya ka'pon pɨ', “E'pa'ta!” (“Ata'koka'!” ta e'kwa pe).  
\v 35 Mɨrɨ a'tai rɨ, ipana uta'koka'pʉ, iyani ekoneka'pʉ, mɨrɨpan usaurokʉ'pʉ ɨ'rɨ anpokʉmanin pʉra rɨ. 
\p  
\v 36 Mɨrɨpan kon nɨ panama'pʉ iya, ipɨ' to' usauro'pɨtʉ namai' ɨnʉ' yan pokon pe rɨ, e'tane miyarɨ rɨ to' apiyo'ma tane iya, miyarɨ rɨ to' uya ekama'pʉ.  
\v 37 Mɨrɨpan tanporon kon nɨ etanin nʉ'san usewansiuka'pʉ ipan pe rɨ: “Ɨ'rɨ kasa wakʉ pe rɨ tanporon nɨ kupʉ iya. Ipana pʉn koneka iya etanin pe; imaimu pʉn koneka iya tʉusauro'sen pe!” ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\c 8  
\s1 4,000 Kaisaron Kon Ewekʉ'pʉ Sises Uya 
\r (Ma'siu 15:32-39) 
\p  
\v 1 Inke kuru pʉra rɨ mɨrɨ tʉpo, tʉron kon kanan anpisin ton amʉrakaa'pʉ. To' enta'nato' ipɨ' pʉra iyesi pɨ', Sises uya tʉpoitorʉ ton kɨ'ma'pʉ tʉpiya', mɨrɨpan uya ta'pʉ,  
\v 2 “Usentu'mayai' pʉsamoro ka'pon amʉ' pɨ', apʉne pʉra uya'kɨrɨ to' e'sa' pɨ' osorʉwau wʉi, mɨrɨpan kon enta'nato' ipɨ' pʉra rɨ si iyesi.  
\v 3 To' enno'sa' uya a'tai to' tewe'se pʉra pata pona to' nin utɨpɨtʉ mɨrɨ yai tʉutɨ kon koro'tau apʉne pʉra tʉron kon uye'sa' ɨnnɨ rɨ,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 4 Ipoitorʉ ton uya ekama'po'pʉ, “Nai yau rɨ tʉ'kenan yau pʉsamoro ka'pon amʉ' ewe'to' ike eporo serɨ?” ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\p  
\v 5 “Ɨ'rɨ kaisa rɨ pʉreti nai ɨpiyau'nokon?” ta'pʉ Sises uya. 
\p To' uya eikʉ'pʉ, “7 kaisa rɨ rɨken,” ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\p  
\v 6 Anpisin ton apiyo'ma'pʉ iya to' ereutapɨ'to' pe non pona, mɨrɨpan 7 kaisaron nʉ'kwɨ rɨken itekiino pʉreti anʉmʉ'pʉ iya, tenki ta'pʉ iya Papa pɨ', mɨrɨpan i'kwɨ'pɨtʉ'pʉ iya. Itʉrʉ'pʉ iya tʉpoitorʉ ton ena', to' uya ekanto' pe anpisin ton ena', mɨrɨpan nɨ kupʉ'pʉ ipoitorʉ ton uya.  
\v 7 To' piyau kanan aiko ton nʉ'kwɨ tu'kan kon pen moro' amʉ' esi'pʉ. Mɨrɨ pɨ' tenki ta'pʉ Sises uya, mɨrɨpan kon ekanto' pe tʉpoitorʉ ton uya kanan ikupʉ'pʉ iya.  
\v 8-9 Tanporon kon enta'na'pʉ ta'wetapɨ'se, mɨrɨ yau 4,000 kaisa rɨ ka'pon amʉ' esi'pʉ, mɨrɨpan ipoitorʉ ton uya ipʉ'kʉ rʉ'san iye'nonkasa' rʉ'pʉ entɨ'pʉ 7 kaisaron pa'siki'ti tʉpe'ke'ne. Sises uya nin si ka'pon amʉ' ennoko'pʉ mɨrɨ,  
\v 10 mɨrɨpan ekanwa'tɨ'pʉ kanau ya' mɨrɨ a'tai rɨ tʉpoitorʉ ton pokon pe, mɨrɨpan kon utɨ'pʉ Tarʉmanu'ta nono pʉ'kʉ pona. 
\s1 I'tuto' Ipɨkɨrɨ Ekama'po'pʉ 
\r (Ma'siu 12:38-42; 16:1-4) 
\p  
\v 11 Pari'si amʉ' uyee'pʉ mɨrɨpan kon e'sara'tɨ'pʉ Sises ekama'popɨtʉ pɨ'. I'tupɨtʉ pe to' uya ekama'po'pʉ i'tuto' ipɨkɨrɨ Epʉn winon pɨ'.\x - \xo 8:11 \xt Ma'siu 12:38; Ʉru' 11:16\x* 
\v 12 Sises uya e'se'ne' pe teruparu enpa'ka'pʉ, mɨrɨpan uya ta'pʉ, “Ɨ'rɨ pe iyesi pɨ' serɨ a'taino kon uya eke Papa tʉrawasooi, ui'tuto' tʉuya'nokon ipɨkɨrɨ ekama'po? I'napairon ekama uya ɨpɨ'nokon; mɨrɨ waraino i'tuto' ipɨkɨrɨ tʉrʉ pen nɨ,” ta'pʉ iya.\x - \xo 8:12 \xt Ma'siu 12:39; Ʉru' 11:29\x* 
\v 13 Mɨrɨpan kon tʉnɨnse iyenna'po'pʉ kanau ya', mɨrɨpan e'kwɨrɨtʉ'pʉ iratoi pona. 
\s1 Pari'si Amʉ' Mɨrɨ Awonsi'kɨ Era' Uya Pʉrowa A'sarutanʉ'to' Ike 
\r (Ma'siu 16:5-12) 
\p  
\v 14 Ipoitorʉ ton upu'tɨkaa'pʉ esi'pʉ tu'ke pʉreti arɨ to' uya pʉra, tikin nɨ rɨken to' piyau iyesi'pʉ kanau yau.  
\v 15 “Ti'tui' e'tɨ'; tense e'tɨ' Pari'si amʉ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Era' uya pʉrowa a'sarutanʉ'to' ike pɨ',” tukai' to' panama'pʉ iya.\x - \xo 8:15 \xt Ʉru' 12:1\x* 
\p  
\v 16 To' e'sara'tɨ'pʉ usauro'nɨ pɨ' tiwano' kon pe. “Apʉne pʉra pʉreti pʉra iyesi pɨ' isaurokʉ mɨrɨ,” ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\p  
\v 17 To' usauro'to' i'tu tʉuya pɨ' to' ekama'po'pʉ iya, “Ɨ'rɨ pɨ' ausaurokʉ kon pʉreti pʉra ɨwesi kon pɨ'? Ene auya'nokon pʉra rɨ pe', mɨrɨ pe pʉra ito'ka'nʉkʉ auya'nokon pʉra rɨ pe' iyesi? Ɨyewan kon nɨ usa'manta?  
\v 18 Tenu ke rɨ pe' ɨwe'tane'nokon ene auya'nokon pʉra iyesi? Tʉpana ke rɨ, e'tane eta auya'nokon pʉra rɨ? Ɨyenu kon yau pʉra nai?\x - \xo 8:18 \xt Iseremaya 5:21; Isi'kiyerʉ 12:2; Ma' 4:12\x* 
\v 19 5 kaisaron pʉreti si'kwɨ'pɨ'taine' a'tai 5,000 kaisaron kon ka'pon amʉ' iwano' pe, ɨ'rɨ kaisa rɨ pa'siki'ti amʉ' tʉpe'tɨpɨ'se ipʉ'kʉ rʉ'san mentɨta'tʉi?” ta'pʉ iya to' pɨ'. 
\p “12 kaisa rɨ,” ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\p  
\v 20 “Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ 7 kaisaron pʉreti si'kwɨ'pɨ'taine' a'tai 4,000 kaisaron kon ka'pon amʉ' iwano' pe, ɨ'rɨ kaisa rɨ pa'siki'ti amʉ' tʉpe'tɨpɨ'se ipʉ'kʉ rʉ'san e'nonkasa' mentɨta'tʉi?” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p “7 kaisa rɨ,” tukai' to' uya eikʉ'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 21 Ta'pʉ iya to' pɨ', “Ito'ka'nʉkʉ auya'nokon pʉra rɨ marɨ pe' iyesi?” ta'pʉ iya. 
\s1 Tenku'nan Epi'tɨ'pʉ Sises Uya Pe'saita Po 
\p  
\v 22 To' uyee'pʉ Pe'saita pona, mɨrɨ yau ka'pon amʉ' uya tenku'nan ka'pon nee'pʉ Sises piya', mɨrɨpan kon uya ipawana'tɨ'pʉ a'pɨ'to' pe iya.  
\v 23 Sises uya tenku'nan arɨ'pʉ itemiyatʉ pɨ' ta'sii' eke iwa pata yapai, mɨrɨpan enu ya' teta'tapɨtʉ tʉpo, temiyatʉ tʉrʉ'pʉ iya ipona, mɨrɨpan uya ekama'po'pʉ, “Ɨ'rɨ rɨ pe' menyan?” ta'pʉ iya ipɨ'. 
\p  
\v 24 Mɨrɨpan uya tenu tʉrʉ'pʉ ka'ta', mɨrɨpan uya ta'pʉ, “Ewai', ka'pon amʉ' senyai', e'tane to' usene yʉi amʉ' usarɨ kasa rɨ,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 25 Sises uya kanan temiyatʉ tʉkaa'pʉ itenu pona. Serɨ a'tai kuru si, wakʉ pe itenu ena'pʉ mɨrɨ, mɨrɨpan uya tanporon nɨ ene'pʉ wakʉ pe.  
\v 26 Sises uya ennoko'pʉ ipata'se' ya', “Kenna'poi eke iwa pata pona,” ta'pʉ iya ipɨ'. 
\s1 Pi'ta Uya Sises Ekama'pʉ 
\r (Ma'siu 16:13-20; Ʉru' 9:18-21) 
\p  
\v 27 Mɨrɨpan Sises mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ipoitorʉ ton utɨ'pʉ eke iwa ton pata Sisariya Piri'pai oino' nan pona. Asanta tau to' ekama'po'pʉ iya, “Ɨnʉ' pe esi tukai' ka'pon amʉ' nʉsauro'an?” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 28 To' uya entakanoma'pʉ, “Tʉron kon uya Isaan Pa'tes pe ɨwesi ta; tʉron kon uya Iraisa pe ɨwesi ta; tʉron kon uya kuru rɨ kanan pu'kena' amʉ' tonpa ta,” ta'pʉ to' uya.\x - \xo 8:28 \xt Ma' 6:14-15; Ʉru' 9:7-8\x* 
\p  
\v 29 “E'tane si ɨmɨrɨ'nokon, ɨnʉ' pe ken si esi mʉkayatʉu?” ta'pʉ iya to' pɨ'. 
\p Pi'ta uya eikʉ'pʉ, “Ɨmɨrɨ kʉrɨ rɨ Kʉrai\f + \fr 8:29 \fq Kʉrai \ft (Kiri' maimu yau); mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq Me'saya \ft (Ipuru maimu yau), asa'rɨ rɨ marɨ iyesi, \fq Papa Nanʉmʉ'pʉ \ft ta e'kwa pe.\f*!” tukai'.\x - \xo 8:29 \xt Isaan 6:68-69\x* 
\p  
\v 30 Sises uya to' panama'pʉ ɨnʉ' pɨ' rɨ to' uya tekama namai'. 
\s1 Tʉuma'tato' Ekama'pʉ Sises Uya 
\r (Ma'siu 16:21-28; Ʉru' 9:22-27) 
\p  
\v 31 To' enupa pɨ' iye'sara'tɨ'pʉ, Ka'pon, Papa winon uya e'ne' moronkato' oton eke pe rɨ, mɨrɨpan ewaruma'tɨto' oton Esuwerʉ amʉ' epuru ton uya rɨ, use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton amʉ' uya rɨ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Main pɨ' enupanin nan uya rɨ nɨrɨ, mɨrɨpan wɨto' oton, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iye'mʉ'sa'kato' oton osorʉwau wʉi tʉpo tukai'.  
\v 32 Serɨ ekama'pʉ iya wakʉ pe kuru rɨ to' pɨ', mɨrɨpan arɨ'pʉ Pi'ta uya esereme'se'na.  
\v 33 E'tane Sises era'tɨsa' a'tai tʉpoitorʉ ton ense'na, mɨrɨpan uya Pi'ta eseremekʉ'pʉ, “Upiyapai enta, Se'tan!”\f + \fr 8:33 \fq Se'tan\ft —Makoi ese' isakon, \fq Papa eseru ewaruma'tɨnin \ft ta e'kwa pe.\f* ta'pʉ iya. “Ɨusenuminkato' esi ka'pon usenuminkato' pe, Papa usenuminkato' kasa pʉra rɨ,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 34 Mɨrɨpan uya anpisin ton kɨ'ma'pʉ tʉpoitorʉ ton pokon pe tʉpiya', “Ɨnʉ' rɨ uyepʉ pe iyesi yau uye'ma'pʉ pe, tɨwɨ tʉpɨ' rɨ tʉupu'tɨka'se, tʉkurusukuui tanʉnse nʉyepʉi upɨkɨrɨ.\x - \xo 8:34 \xt Ma'siu 10:38; Ʉru' 14:27\x* 
\v 35 Apʉne pʉra ɨnʉ' rɨ kʉrɨ tʉuko'manto'\f + \fr 8:35 \ft Serɨ Kiri' maimu yau, \fq ta'kwarʉ \ft ta e'kwa pe, mɨrɨ pe pʉra \fq uko'manto' \ft ta e'kwa pe; v. 36 yau nɨrɨ.\f* ɨnnonkapai pʉra na'ne' uya tʉuko'manto' rɨ nonka mɨrɨ, e'tane ɨnʉ' rɨ tʉuko'manto' nonka pɨ' na'ne' upɨkɨrɨ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wakʉ itekare pɨkɨrɨ uya inonka pen mɨrɨ.\x - \xo 8:35 \xt Ma'siu 10:39; Ʉru' 17:33; Isaan 12:25\x* 
\v 36 Wakʉ pe pe' ka'pon esi tanporo non pon eponin ta'kwarʉ nonkai'ma? Kane ku!  
\v 37 Mɨrɨ pe pʉra, ɨ'rɨ tʉrʉ iya ta'kwarʉ entakano' pe?  
\v 38 Ɨnʉ' rɨ ɨpiyɨtʉ yau upɨ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ umaimu ton pɨ', serɨ iyemari'masa' ekumankanin nan mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨri ton serɨ a'taino kon weyu a'tai'ne, Ka'pon, Papa winon nɨrɨ ɨpiyɨtʉ mɨrɨ ipɨ', tʉuyepʉ a'tai tʉkʉipʉnʉ meruntɨrʉ yau mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wakʉ ton nɨ inserʉ amʉ' pokon pe,” ta'pʉ Sises uya. 
\c 9  
\p  
\v 1 Mɨrɨpan uya ta'pʉ to' pɨ', “I'napairon ekama uya ɨpɨ'nokon, serɨ yau iye'soto'pɨ'sa' na'ne' nan tonpa ton eri'to' oton pen nɨ Papa e'to' esa' wannɨ pe uyepʉ meruntɨ pe ene tʉuya'nokon rawɨrɨ,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\s1 Sises Uta'kwaka'pʉ 
\r (Ma'siu 17:1-13; Ʉru' 9:28-36) 
\p  
\v 2 6 kaisa rɨ wʉi tʉpo, Sises uya Pi'ta, Isens mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Isaan pokon arɨ'pʉ ta'kɨrɨ. To' arɨ'pʉ iya ka'tawon nɨ wʉ' pona tʉ'kenan yau to' e'to' pe. Mɨrɨ yau to' esi koro'tau, isensima'pʉ.  
\v 3 Ipon ena'pʉ sirɨn pe aimu'ne, ipan pe rɨ aimu'ne ɨnʉ' rɨ serɨ non pon uya ikorʉkasa' uya aimu'nakasa' entai rɨ.  
\v 4 Mɨrɨpan mɨrɨ yau Iraisa mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Mosi' pokon usenpoika'pʉ to' rakʉi', Sises auro'ka pɨ' to' esi'pʉ.  
\v 5 Pi'ta uya ta'pʉ Sises pɨ', “Rapai,\f + \fr 9:5 \fq Rapai, Ti'sa \ft ta e'kwa pe\f* wakʉ rɨ pan pe rɨ serɨ yau ina man. Tɨwɨ osorʉwau ɨiwʉ' kon oton amɨi ina — tikin nɨ ɨiwʉ' pe, Mosi' iwʉ' pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Iraisa iwʉ' pe.”  
\v 6 (Mɨrɨ ta tʉuya tukai' i'tu iya pʉra rɨ iyesi'pʉ, apʉne pʉra kʉrɨ rɨ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉron kon etʉipɨ'sa' esi'pʉ mɨrɨ pɨ'.) 
\p  
\v 7 Mɨrɨ a'tai, kapuru' usenpoika'pʉ, mɨrɨpan uya to' nɨpontɨ'pʉ. Main uyee'pʉ kapuru' apai, “Umu pʉse rɨ, Uni'nʉnkanʉ. Imaimu etatɨ'!” tawon.\x - \xo 9:7 \xt Ma'siu 3:17; Ma' 1:11; Ʉru' 3:22; 2 Pi'ta 1:17-18\x* 
\p  
\v 8 Mɨ awɨrɨ tenu kon tʉpɨ'tane to' uya, ɨnʉ' pʉra rɨ iyesi'pʉ. Sises rɨken esi'pʉ to' piyau. 
\p  
\v 9 Wʉ' ponsi'kɨ tʉu'tɨ kon koro'tau, Sises uya ta'pʉ to' pɨ', “Ɨnʉ' pɨ' rɨ ɨnene'pʉ kon kʉsekamatʉu, Ka'pon, Papa winon eri'sa' e'mʉ'sa'ka pʉ'kʉ pona rɨ,” ta'pʉ iya.  
\v 10 Imaimu awɨrɨ to' esi'pʉ, e'tane tiwano' kon pe to' usekama'popɨtʉ'pʉ mɨrɨ pɨ', ɨ'rɨ ta e'kwa pe, “eri'nɨsa' e'mʉ'sa'ka pʉ'kʉ pona rɨ,” ta esi tukai'. 
\p  
\v 11 Mɨrɨpan kon uya ekama'po'pʉ, “Ɨ'rɨ pe ken iyesi pɨ' Main pɨ' enupanin nan uya Iraisa kuru uye'to' oton wapiya ta?” ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\p  
\v 12 To' entakanoma'pʉ iya, “I'napairɨ rɨ Iraisa uyepʉ wapiya tanporon nɨ konekai' iyesi'pʉ ya'. Ɨ'rɨto' pe iye'menukasa' Ka'pon, Papa winon ekota'mato' oton ipan pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ewaruma'tɨto' oton ta?\x - \xo 9:12 \xt Saira' 48:10\x* 
\v 13 E'tane nin si ekama uya ɨpɨ'nokon, Iraisa uye'ka'sa', mɨrɨpan pɨ' i'se te'to' kon ku'sa' to' uya ipɨ' iye'menukasa' na'ne' kasa rɨ,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\s1 Warawo' Mʉre Epi'tɨ'pʉ Sises Uya 
\r (Ma'siu 17:14-21; Ʉru' 9:37-43a) 
\p  
\v 14 Ipoitorʉ ton tonpa ton piya' to' uye'sa' a'tai, anpisin ton nɨ ka'pon amʉ' ene'pʉ to' uya to' oi. Main pɨ' enupanin nan e'sei'pɨtʉ esi'pʉ to' pokon pe.  
\v 15 Sises ensa' tanporon kon ka'pon amʉ' uya a'tai, ipan pe rɨ to' usewansiuka'pʉ, mɨrɨpan kon eka'tumʉ'pʉ ipiya', “Miyarɨ” ka'se'na ipɨ'.  
\v 16 Tʉpoitorʉ ton ekama'po'pʉ Sises uya, “Ɨ'rɨ pɨ' to' pokon pe ɨye'sei'pɨtʉ kon?” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 17 Anpisin ton koro'tawon ka'pon uya eikʉ'pʉ, “Ti'sa, umu ne'sa' uya ɨpiya', apʉne pʉra ɨri a'kwarʉ esi iyau, mɨrɨpan uya imaimu'kasa'.  
\v 18 Mɨrɨ ɨri a'kwarʉ e'sara'tɨ a'tai, eno'ma iya non pona. Inta a'koronta, tʉyɨ kɨtɨtɨi'ma iya, mɨrɨpan e'sitɨnka. Ɨpoitorʉ ton ekama'po'pʉ uya to' uya enpa'kato' pe, e'tane to' uya ikupʉ poken pʉra iyesi'pʉ,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 19 “Ɨri sɨ, apurɨnin nan pen nɨ serɨ a'taino kon! Ɨ'rɨ pʉ'kʉ pona rɨ ɨpiyau'nokon esi? Ɨ'rɨ pʉ'kʉ pona aya'kɨrɨ'nokon esi? Ine'tɨ' upiya',” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 20 To' uya inee'pʉ ipiya'. Ɨri a'kwarʉ uya Sises ensa' a'tai, inke pʉra warawo' mʉre ennoko'pʉ iya yai. Ita'mo'ka'pʉ non pona, mɨrɨpan e'rakairakaima'pʉ, inta a'koronta'pʉ.  
\v 21 “Ɨ'rɨ a'tai serɨ kasa iyesi e'sara'tɨ'pʉ?” ta'pʉ Sises uya ikʉipʉnʉ pɨ'. 
\p “Mʉre pe iyesi'pʉ si'kɨrɨ rɨ,” ta'pʉ iya.  
\v 22 “Inke rɨ iwɨnɨ i'se iye'pɨ'sa' mɨrɨ teno'mapɨ'se apo' ya' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tuna ka'. Ina pɨ' ɨsentu'ma', ina ipika'tɨ', ikupʉ auya poken iyesi yau,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 23 “Ɨ'rɨ ta auya e'kwa pe iyesi, ‘Ikupʉ auya poken iyesi yau,’ mʉkayai'ne'? Tanporon nɨ e'kupʉ apurɨnin nan pɨ',” ta'pʉ Sises uya. 
\p  
\v 24 Inke pʉra warawo' mʉre kʉipʉnʉ uya tʉukɨ'pɨ'nʉmʉ pe, “Apurɨ uya rɨ; upika'tɨkɨ apurɨnin pe pʉra e'to' entai enato' pe!” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 25 Sises uya anpisin uyepʉ a'ko pe tʉpiya' ene a'tai, ɨri a'kwarʉ\f + \fr 9:25 \fq ɨri a'kwarʉ, \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra \fq makoi a'kwarʉ\f* eseremekʉ'pʉ iya, “Ipana pʉn mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ imaimu pʉn a'kwarʉ, kʉrɨ rɨ warawo' mʉre apai epa'kakɨ. Mɨrɨ tʉpo, iya' kanan kewomʉi,” ta'pʉ iya ipɨ'. 
\p  
\v 26 Ɨri a'kwarʉ upirorʉmʉ'pʉ, mɨrɨpan uya warawo' mʉre ennoko'pʉ yai ipan pe, mɨrɨpan epa'ka'pʉ. Warawo' mʉre esi'pʉ eke' kasa, mɨrɨpan tu'kan kon uya, “Iyeri'sa',” ta'pʉ.  
\v 27 E'tane Sises uya warawo' mʉre anʉmʉ'pʉ itemiyatʉ pɨ', mɨrɨpan e'mʉ'sa'ka'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 28 Sises ewomʉ'pʉ tʉpo, ipoitorʉ ton uya ekama'po'pʉ ama'ai, “Ɨ'rɨ pe ken si iyesi pɨ' ina uya enpa'ka pʉra iyesi?” ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\p  
\v 29 “Ɨ'rɨ pen nɨ, ɨpʉreman\f + \fr 9:29 \ft Tʉron nɨ imenukasa' yau, \fq ɨpʉreman mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ useruman \ft tawon esi.\f* uya rɨken serɨ rupɨ enpa'ka,” ta'pʉ Sises uya. 
\s1 Sises Kanan Usauro'kaa'pʉ Teri'to' Pɨ' 
\r (Ma'siu 17:22-23; Ʉru' 9:43b-45) 
\p  
\v 30 Mɨrɨ pata nɨmɨ'pʉ to' uya, mɨrɨpan kon utɨ'pʉ Kiyarari poro. Sises esi'pʉ mɨrɨ yau tesi tukai' ɨnʉ' uya rɨ ti'tu i'se pʉra,  
\v 31 apʉne pʉra tʉpoitorʉ ton enupa tʉuya pɨ'. Ta'pʉ iya to' pɨ', “Ka'pon, Papa winon eparankato' oton ka'pon amʉ' ena'. To' uya iwɨto' oton, e'tane itosorʉwano wʉi pata'pʉ pe iye'mʉ'sa'kato' oton,” ta'pʉ iya.  
\v 32 E'tane to' uya ito'ka'nʉkʉ pʉra rɨ iyesi'pʉ, ɨ'rɨ ta iya e'kwa pe iyesi tukai', mɨrɨpan kon enari'nʉmʉ'pʉ mɨrɨ pɨ' ɨnekama'popai pʉra. 
\s1 Ɨnʉ' Esi Eke Pe Kuru? 
\r (Ma'siu 18:1-5; Ʉru' 9:46-48) 
\p  
\v 33 To' utɨ'pʉ Ka'paneyan pona. Tewomʉ tʉpo, Sises uya tʉpoitorʉ ton ekama'po'pʉ, “Ɨ'rɨ pɨ' me'sei'pɨ'tʉune' asanta tau?” ta'pʉ iya.  
\v 34 E'tane to' uya eikʉ pʉra iyesi'pʉ, apʉne pʉra asanta tau ɨnʉ' esi eke pe kuru tukai' to' e'sei'pɨtʉ esi'pʉ.\x - \xo 9:34 \xt Ʉru' 22:24\x* 
\p  
\v 35 Sises ereuta'pʉ, mɨrɨpan uya 12 kaisaron kon tʉpoitorʉ ton kɨ'ma'pʉ, “Wapiya e'pai na'ne' e'to' pe iyesi, iu'matʉ yau mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tanporon kon poitorʉ pe iye'to' pe iyesi,” ta'pʉ iya.\x - \xo 9:35 \xt Ma'siu 20:26-27; 23:11; Ma' 10:43-44; Ʉru' 22:26\x* 
\p  
\v 36 Temekon tʉtʉse iwoi mʉre ta'sii' isoto'ka'pʉ iya to' koro'tau, mɨrɨpan uya ta'pʉ to' pɨ',  
\v 37 “Ɨnʉ' uya rɨ pʉsamoro mʉre amʉ' tonpa ereutanʉkʉ pe iyesi yau uyese' yau, urɨ rɨ ereutanʉkʉ iya pe iyesi; mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨnʉ' uya rɨ urɨ ereutanʉkʉ pe iyesi yau, urɨ rɨken ereutanʉkʉ iya pen mɨrɨ, kʉrɨ uyenno'nin nʉ'pʉ kanan ereutanʉkʉ iya pe iyesi,” ta'pʉ iya.\x - \xo 9:37 \xt Ma'siu 10:40; Ʉru' 10:16; Isaan 13:20\x* 
\s1 Ɨnʉ' Rɨ Uyewa'nomanin Kon Pen Esi Uwenaino' Kon Pe 
\r (Ʉru' 9:49-50) 
\p  
\v 38 “Ti'sa,” ta'pʉ Isaan uya, “Ka'pon ene'pʉ ina uya ɨyese' yau makoi a'kwarʉ ton enpa'kapɨ'nin. Iyereutato' pe ina uya ikupʉ'pʉ, apʉne pʉra urɨ'nokon tonpa pe pʉra iyesi pɨ',” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 39 Sises uya ta'pʉ to' pɨ', “Kʉsereutanʉ'tʉu, apʉne pʉra ɨnʉ' rɨ eke Papa tʉrawasooi ku'nin nʉ'pʉ uyese' yau usaurokʉ poken pʉra iyesi mɨrɨ tʉpo ɨri pe upɨ'.  
\v 40 Uyewa'noma iya 'nokon pʉra na'ne' esi mɨrɨ uwenaino' kon pe rɨ.\x - \xo 9:40 \xt Ma'siu 12:30; Ʉru' 11:23\x* 
\v 41 I'napairon ekama uya ɨpɨ'nokon, ɨnʉ' rɨ tuna ke ɨwo'payai'ne'nokon uyese' yau apʉne pʉra Kʉrai\f + \fr 9:41 \fq Kʉrai \ft (Kiri' maimu yau); mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq Me'saya \ft (Ipuru maimu yau), asa'rɨ rɨ marɨ iyesi, \fq Papa Nanʉmʉ'pʉ \ft ta e'kwa pe.\f* iwano' pe ɨwesi kon pɨ', tepe'pʉ nonka iya pen kuru rɨ mɨrɨ.\x - \xo 9:41 \xt Ma'siu 10:42\x* 
\s1 Ka'pon Amʉ' Umakoita Emapu'tɨ 
\r (Ma'siu 18:6-9; Ʉru' 17:1-2) 
\p  
\v 42 “Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨnʉ' uya rɨ pʉsamoro uyapurɨnin nan aiko ton nʉ'kwɨ tonpa e'makoima emapu'tɨsa' yau, wakʉ iwa pe rɨ iyesi parau ka' eno'ma eke rɨ a'nai' e'pato' ike ewa'tɨsa' i'mʉ pɨ' esa' pe.  
\v 43 Ɨyemiyatʉ uya ɨye'makoima emapu'tɨ pe iyesi yau, a'tɨkɨ. Wakʉ iwa pe rɨ iyesi itemiyatʉ pʉra esii'ma tɨwɨrɨ rɨ uko'man nɨto' ya' ɨyepa'ka a'tai, tanporo temiyatʉ ke ekota'man nɨto' ya' ɨutɨ entai, apo' usenkʉ'to' pen nɨ ya'.\f + \fr 9:43 \ft Tʉron nɨ imenukasa' ton uya v. 44 ke iponantɨsa' se kasa: \fq Mɨrɨ yau, ‘to' weruweei erikʉ pen nɨ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ apo' usenkʉ'nʉkʉ pen nɨ.’\f*\x - \xo 9:43 \xt Ma'siu 5:30\x* 
\v 45 Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ a'ta uya ɨye'makoima emapu'tɨ pe iyesi yau, a'tɨkɨ. Wakʉ iwa pe rɨ iyesi i'ta pʉra esii'ma tɨwɨrɨ rɨ uko'man nɨto' ya' ɨyepa'ka a'tai, ti'ta ke ɨyeno'ma entai ya'mu pʉn ekota'man nɨto' ya'.\f + \fr 9:45 \ft Tʉron nɨ imenukasa' ton uya v. 46 ke iponantɨsa' se kasa: \fq Mɨrɨ yau, ‘to' weruweei erikʉ pen nɨ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ apo' usenkʉ'nʉkʉ pen nɨ.’\f* 
\v 47 Ɨyenu uya ɨye'makoima emapu'tɨ pe iyesi yau, imo'kakɨ. Wakʉ iwa pe rɨ iyesi mɨrɨ tikin nɨ itenu tɨwɨrɨ rɨ uko'man nɨto' ya' ɨyepa'ka a'tai, asa'rɨ itenu ɨyeno'ma entai ya'mu pʉn ekota'man nɨto' ya'.  
\v 48 Mɨrɨ yau, 
\q1 “‘to' weruweei erikʉ pen nɨ, 
\q2 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ apo' usenkʉ'nʉkʉ pen nɨ.’\f + \fr 9:48 \ft Aisaya 66:24\f* 
\m  
\v 49 Tanporon kon nɨ e'ne'ne'ma mɨrɨ apo' ke. 
\p  
\v 50 “Waiyo esi wakʉ, e'tane ine'ne' pe pʉra iyenasa' yau, nai kasa ken si ine'ne' pe kanan iye'to' pe iku'kapʉ auya? Waiyo iku'tɨ' ayau'nokon, tʉusewankamai' pʉra ɨko'mantɨ' ɨtonpa kon amʉ' pokon pe,” ta'pʉ iya.\x - \xo 9:50 \xt Ma'siu 5:13; Ʉru' 14:34-35\x* 
\c 10  
\s1 No'pʉ Nonkato' Ekareei Ekama'pʉ Sises Uya 
\r (Ma'siu 19:1-12; Ʉru' 16:18) 
\p  
\v 1 Mɨrɨ a'tai, Sises uya mɨrɨ pata nɨmɨ'pʉ, mɨrɨpan utɨ'pʉ Isutiya nono pe te'sen ya' tuna Isotan ratoi pon anpisin pe rɨ kanan ka'pon amʉ' uye'kaa'pʉ ipiya', mɨrɨpan kon enupa'pʉ iya, teseru yau rɨ. 
\p  
\v 2 Pari'si amʉ' tonpa ton uyee'pʉ ipiya', mɨrɨpan kon uya i'tupɨtʉ'pʉ ekama'popɨtʉ tʉuya'nokon winɨ, “Main awɨrɨ rɨ e'nɨ pe rɨ pe' iyesi ka'pon uya tʉno'pʉ nonka a'tai?” ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\p  
\v 3 Sises uya to' eikʉ'pʉ to' ekama'po pe, “Ɨ'rɨ tawon ken Main tʉrʉ'pʉ Mosi' uya ɨyena'nokon?” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 4 To' uya eikʉ'pʉ, “Mosi' uya itʉsa' ka'pon uya e'nonkan nɨto' karetaai tʉmenukai' tʉno'pʉ enno'to' pe tasa' iya,” ta'pʉ to' uya.\x - \xo 10:4 \xt Isu'taronomi 24:1-4; Ma'siu 5:31\x* 
\p  
\v 5 Sises uya ta'pʉ to' pɨ', “Mosi' uya serɨ main menuka'pʉ, apʉne pʉra sa'man pe rɨ ɨyewan kon esi pɨ'.  
\v 6 E'tane iye'kapʉ epiya'tɨ yau, ‘Papa uya warawo' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ uri'san kaa'pʉ,’\f + \fr 10:6 \ft Iseneses 1:27; 5:2\f* tasa' iya.  
\v 7 ‘Mɨrɨ wenai, warawo' uya tʉkʉipʉnʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉsan nɨnto' esi, mɨrɨpan uta'sikʉ tʉno'pʉ ya',\f + \fr 10:7 \ft Tʉron nɨ imenukasa' ton, \fq mɨrɨpan kon uta'sikʉ tʉno'pʉ ya', \ft tawon pʉra iyesi.\f* 
\v 8 mɨrɨpan asa'ron kon ena tikin nɨ ipun,’\f + \fr 10:8 \ft Iseneses 2:24\f* tasa' iya. Asa'rɨ to' esi pen, e'tane tikin nɨ to' esi.  
\v 9 Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', Papa na'sikʉ'san ɨsipona mo'ka ka'pon uya kʉse'nin,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 10 To' enna'posa' a'tai ɨutɨ ta', ipoitorʉ ton uya serɨ pɨ' ekama'po'pʉ.  
\v 11 Eikʉ'pʉ iya, “Ɨnʉ' rɨ tʉno'pʉ nonkayai'ne' mɨrɨpan uya tʉron nɨ uri'san mari'ma ekuma pe iyesi tʉno'pʉ piyapai.  
\v 12 Mɨrɨpan tʉtaan'pʉ nonka iya pe iyesi yau mɨrɨpan uya tʉron nɨ warawo' mari'ma yau, iyekuma pe rɨ iyesi mɨrɨ,” ta'pʉ iya.\x - \xo 10:12 \xt Ma'siu 5:32; 1 Koren 7:10-11\x* 
\s1 Mʉre Amʉ' Pʉrema'pʉ Sises Uya 
\r (Ma'siu 19:13-15; Ʉru' 18:15-17) 
\p  
\v 13 Ka'pon amʉ' uya mʉre amʉ' nee'pʉ Sises piya' to' a'pɨ'to' pe iya, e'tane ipoitorʉ ton uya to' eseremekʉ'pʉ.  
\v 14 Sises uya ensa' a'tai, isakorota'pʉ, mɨrɨpan uya ta'pʉ tʉpoitorʉ ton pɨ', “Tɨwɨ mʉre amʉ' nʉyepʉi upiya'. To' kʉsereutanʉ'tʉu, apʉne pʉra Papa e'to' esa' wannɨ pe esi pʉsamoro waraino kon iwano' pe.  
\v 15 I'napairon ekama uya ɨpɨ'nokon, ɨnʉ' rɨ kʉrɨ Papa e'to' esa' wannɨ pe eporo iya pʉra na'ne' mʉre kasa te'se ewonto' oton pen nɨ ya',” ta'pʉ iya.\x - \xo 10:15 \xt Ma'siu 18:3\x* 
\v 16 Mʉre amʉ' anʉmʉ'pʉ iya temekon pona, mɨrɨpan kon pona temiyatʉ tʉtʉse to' pʉrema'pʉ iya. 
\s1 Imaminke' Moineri'pɨ 
\r (Ma'siu 19:16-30; Ʉru' 18:18-30) 
\p  
\v 17 Utɨn pɨ' Sises e'sara'tɨ koro'tau, ka'pon eka'tunsa' uyee'pʉ, mɨrɨpan e'sekunka'pʉ irau, mɨrɨpan uya ekama'po'pʉ, “Wakʉ, Ti'sa, ɨ'rɨ kuru ku'to' uya esi tɨwɨrɨ uko'man nɨto' epoto' pe uya?” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 18 “Ɨ'rɨ pe iyesi pɨ' Wakʉ tukai' uyesakʉ auya?” tukai' Sises uya eikʉ'pʉ. “Ɨnʉ' wakʉ pʉra rɨ iyesi, e'tane Papa rɨken.  
\v 19 Mosi' nʉmenuka'pʉ i'tu auya: ‘Ɨnʉ' rɨ kʉ'wɨnɨi, iyemari'masa' uri'san kʉsekumankai, ama' pe kesii, kasi pe ka'pon pɨ' kasaurokʉi, enku'tɨnin pe kesii, ɨkʉipʉnʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ asan inamakɨ,’\f + \fr 10:19 \ft E'sotas 20:12; Isu'taronomi 5:16-20\f* tawon,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 20 “Ti'sa, tanporo rɨ serɨ ton awɨrɨ e'sa' man mʉre' esi'pʉ si'kɨrɨ rɨ,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 21 Sises uya ene'pʉ i'nʉnka pe, “Tikin nan nɨken e'nonkasa' man. Tanporo ɨpiyau na'ne' ikʉrʉpo'pomata, mɨrɨpan epe'pʉ tʉrʉ pa entu'manin nan ena'. Mɨrɨ a'tai nin si, imaminke' pe ɨwesi mɨrɨ Epʉn po. Mɨrɨ ku'sa' auya tʉpo, upɨkɨrɨ ɨuyepʉ pa,” ta'pʉ iya ipɨ'. 
\p  
\v 22 Mɨrɨ eta iya a'tai, ika'nɨ' pʉra rɨ itemʉ' ena'pʉ. Pokoi pe itɨ'pʉ, apʉne pʉra eke pe kuru itimamin esi'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 23 Sises uya tenu tʉpɨtʉ'pʉ, mɨrɨpan uya ta'pʉ tʉpoitorʉ ton pɨ', “Sa'man pe kuru rɨ iyesi, imaminke' ton epa'ka poken pʉra Papa e'to' esa' wannɨ pe ya'!” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 24 Ipoitorʉ ton usewansiuka'pʉ imaimu pɨ'. E'tane Sises uya takaa'pʉ kanan, “Mʉre amʉ', sa'man pe kuru rɨ iyesi Papa e'to' esa' wannɨ pe ya' epa'kan poken pʉra.  
\v 25 Sa'man pe pʉra rɨ kiyamerʉ epa'ka akusa enu euta awɨrɨ, imaminke' epa'ka Papa e'to' esa' wannɨ pe ya' entai,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 26 Ipan pe miyarɨ rɨ mɨrɨ pɨ' ipoitorʉ ton usewansiuka'pʉ, mɨrɨpan kon usekama'popɨtʉ'pʉ, “Ɨnʉ' kuru ken si epika'tɨ?” tukai'. 
\p  
\v 27 To' enei'ma Sises uya ta'pʉ to' pɨ', “Ka'pon pona sa'man pe iyesi, e'tane Papa pona tanporo sa'man pe pʉra iyesi,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 28 Pi'ta uya ta'pʉ ipɨ', “Tanporon nɨ sa'ne nɨnsa' ina uya ɨpɨkɨrɨ tʉutɨto' kon pe,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 29 “I'napairon ekama uya ɨpɨ'nokon,” ta'pʉ Sises uya, “ɨnʉ' rɨ kʉrɨ tʉpata'se', takon non, tʉparusi ton, tʉsan, tʉkʉipʉnʉ, tʉmunkɨ amʉ' mɨrɨ pe pʉra tʉmainarʉ nɨnsa' iya na'ne', urɨ pɨkɨrɨ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wakʉ itekare pɨkɨrɨ, uya  
\v 30 eke pe rɨ tepe'pʉ eporo mɨrɨ, serɨ pe na'ne' entai rɨ — tʉpata'se', takon non, tʉparusi ton, tʉsanon, tʉmunkɨ amʉ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉmainarʉ rɨ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ewa'noman nɨ nɨrɨ — mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ serɨ enta', tɨwɨ rɨ uko'man nɨto' eporo iya.  
\v 31 Tu'kan kon nɨ wapiya na'ne' nan e'to' oton iu'matʉ pe, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iu'matʉ pe iye'sa' kon nin si e'to' oton wapiya te'ton kon pe,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\s1 Itosorʉwano Pe Sises Kanan Usauro'kaa'pʉ Teri'to' Pɨ' 
\r (Ma'siu 20:17-19; Ʉru' 18:31-34) 
\p  
\v 32 To' utɨ koro'tau Surusiran pona, Sises to' rawɨrɨ, ipoitorʉ ton usewansiukasa' esi'pʉ, to' pɨkɨrɨ te'san enari'nʉntane. Sises uya kanan tʉpoitorʉ ton pantaka'pʉ, mɨrɨpan uya tʉpɨ' te'ku'ton ekama'pʉ to' pɨ'.  
\v 33 “Utɨ'nokon serɨ Surusiran pona. Mɨrɨ yau Ka'pon, Papa winon eparankato' oton use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Main pɨ' enupanin nan ena', to' uya eno'mato' oton ima'tato' ya', mɨrɨpan tʉto' oton to' uya Esuwerʉ amʉ' pen ena'.  
\v 34 Kamoro uya nin si isapema mɨrɨ, to' eta'tapɨtʉ ipona, to' uya ari'po'pɨtʉ; mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ to' uya iwɨnɨ. Osorʉwau wʉi pata'pʉ pe, iye'mʉ'sa'kato' oton,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\s1 Isens Mɨrɨ Awonsi'kɨ Isaan Nekama'ponʉ 
\r (Ma'siu 20:20-28) 
\p  
\v 35 Mɨrɨ a'tai, Isens mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Isaan, Sepiti munkɨ amʉ' uyee'pʉ ipiya', “Ti'sa, ɨ'rɨ rɨ ina nekama'poyai'ne' ɨpɨ' kupʉ auya i'se ina man ina iwano' pe,” ta'pʉ to' uya ipɨ'. 
\p  
\v 36 “Ɨ'rɨ ken kupʉ uya i'se me'atʉu ɨiwano' kon pe?” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 37 “Tɨwɨ tikin nɨ ɨyenwo'netʉ winɨ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ akamisi winɨ ina nereutai ayapon po ɨyereutasa' a'tai kʉrore po,” ta'pʉ to' uya ipɨ'. 
\p  
\v 38 “Ɨ'rɨ pɨ' uyekama'po auya'nokon tukai' i'tu auya'nokon pʉra rɨ iyesi,” ta'pʉ Sises uya. “Sensiyai'ne' ken pe' ensi auya'nokon, mɨrɨ pe pʉra ɨyepa'taisima kon ken pe' epa'taisimayai'ne' ike ke?” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 39 “Ina uya rɨ ikupʉ,” ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\p Sises uya ta'pʉ to' pɨ', “I'napairɨ rɨ unensinʉ rɨ ensi auya'nokon, ɨyepa'taisima kon nɨ epa'taisimayai'ne' ke.  
\v 40 E'tane ereutapai me'atʉi'ne' uyenwo'netʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ukamisi winɨ kupʉ uya poken pʉra iyesi. Serɨ esi mɨrɨ kamo to' ku'sa' na'ne' nan Papa uya rɨ pata'se' pe iyesi,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 41 Kamo 10 kaisaron kon uya serɨ etasa' a'tai, Isens mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Isaan pokon pɨ' to' usakorota'pʉ.  
\v 42 Sises uya tanporo to' amʉranʉkʉ'pʉ, mɨrɨpan uya ta'pʉ to' pɨ', “I'tu auya'nokon nɨ kamo itepuru pe na'ne' nan nɨ esi mɨrɨ Esuwerʉ amʉ' pen epuru pe, mɨrɨpan eke ton uya tʉmerunitɨrʉ kon apurɨ to' pɨ'.  
\v 43 E'tane mɨrɨ kasa ɨwesi kon pen. E'tane ru'ku, ɨnʉ' rɨ esi yau eke pe enapai ɨ'koro'tau'nokon e'to' pe iyesi ɨpoitorʉ kon pe,  
\v 44 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨnʉ' rɨ esi yau wapiyaro' e' pe e'pai, tɨwɨ nesii tanporon kon apiyo' pe.  
\v 45 Apʉne pʉra Ka'pon, Papa winon uye'sa' mɨrɨ tapiyo' pe e'nɨto' pe pen, e'tane apiyo' pe e'se'na, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉuko'manto' tʉse'na tu'kan kon ka'pon amʉ' epe' pe,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\s1 Tenku'nan Epi'tɨ'pʉ Sises Uya 
\r (Ma'siu 20:29-34; Ʉru' 18:35-43) 
\p  
\v 46 Iseri'ko pona to' uyee'pʉ. Sises mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ipoitorʉ ton mɨrɨ tʉpo anpisin ton ka'pon amʉ' uya mɨrɨ eke pata nɨmɨ koro'tau, tenku'nan ka'pon, Pa'timeyas itese' ereutasa' esi'pʉ asanta ka'ta po eta'kwanʉn nɨ pɨ' (Timeyas mumu pe te'sen).  
\v 47 Sises kʉrɨ rɨ Nasare' pon tawon etasa' tʉuya a'tai, ukɨ'pɨ'nʉnpɨ' nɨ pɨ' iye'sara'tɨ'pʉ, “Sises, Tepi' pa rʉ'pʉ, upɨ' ɨsentu'makɨ!” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 48 Tu'kan kon uya rɨ eseremekʉ'pʉ e'pana iye'to' pe, e'tane rɨ miyarɨ rɨ ikɨ'pɨ'nʉnpɨtʉ'pʉ, “Tepi' pa rʉ'pʉ, upɨ' ɨsentu'makɨ!” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 49 Sises e'takʉ'ka'pʉ, mɨrɨpan uya, “Ikɨ'matɨ',” ta'pʉ. 
\p Mɨrɨpan kon uya nin si ikɨ'ma'pʉ, “Epori'ma'! E'mʉ'sa'ka'! Ɨkɨ'ma iya,” ta'pʉ to' uya ipɨ'.  
\v 50 Tʉpon pʉro'pon nin si eno'ma'pʉ iya mɨrɨ, te'sanʉmʉ pe iye'mʉ'sa'ka'pʉ, mɨrɨpan uyee'pʉ Sises piya'. 
\p  
\v 51 “Ɨ'rɨ kupʉ uya i'se me'an ɨiwano' pe?” ta'pʉ Sises uya ipɨ'. 
\p Tenku'nan ka'pon uya, “Rapai,\f + \fr 10:51 \fq Rapai, Ti'sa \ft ta e'kwa pe\f* ennin pe kanan e'pai e'ai',” ta'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 52 “Enta, anapurɨnʉ uya ɨyepi'tɨsa' man,” ta'pʉ Sises uya ipɨ'. Inke pʉra rɨ, ennin pe iyena'pʉ, mɨrɨpan nin si utɨ'pʉ mɨrɨ asanta tawɨrɨ Sises pɨkɨrɨ. 
\c 11  
\s1 Sises Epa'ka'pʉ Surusiran Pona 
\r (Ma'siu 21:1-11; Ʉru' 19:28-40; Isaan 12:12-19) 
\p  
\v 1 Surusiran eporo to' uya koro'tau, Pe'pake mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Pe'tani ya' si to' uye'ka'sa' Are' Wʉpʉ pon, Sises uya asa'ron kon tʉpoitorʉ ton ennoko'pʉ  
\v 2 tai'ma to' pɨ', “Entantɨ' ɨyentau'nokon na'ne' eke iwa pata ya', iya' ɨyepa'ka kon pe rɨ, mɨrɨ yau eporo auya'nokon mɨrɨ isa'ka'si mʉre ewa'tɨsa', ɨnʉ' utɨ'pʉ ipo pen nɨ. Teukai' mʉne'tʉi' serɨ ya'.  
\v 3 Ɨnʉ' uya rɨ ɨyekama'po kon yau, ‘Ɨ'rɨto' pe mɨrɨ kupʉ auya'nokon?’ tukai', ‘Itepuru esi i'se inke pʉra inna'poto' pe tʉuya rɨ,’ mʉkatʉi' ipɨ',” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 4 Mɨrɨpan kon utɨsa' uya isa'ka'si mʉre eporo'pʉ pʉroroi po asanta tau ewa'tɨsa' mʉra'ta piyau. Euka pɨ' to' esi koro'tau,  
\v 5 mɨrɨ yau iye'soto'pɨ'sa' kon ka'pon amʉ' uya, “Ɨ'rɨ kupʉ auya'nokon, kʉrɨ rɨ isa'ka'si mʉre meukayatʉi'ne'?” ta'pʉ to' pɨ'.  
\v 6 To' eikʉ'pʉ to' uya, Sises uya ta'pʉ kasa rɨ, mɨrɨpan kon uya to' uya ato' pe ikupʉ'pʉ.  
\v 7 Isa'ka'si mʉre ne'sa' to' uya a'tai Sises piya', tʉpon kon tʉpɨtʉ'pʉ to' uya ipʉro'pona, mɨrɨpan po iyereuta'pʉ.  
\v 8 Tu'kan kon ka'pon amʉ' uya tʉpon kon ta'nʉkʉ'pʉ asanta tawɨrɨ, tʉron kon uya mɨrɨ'tawon yʉi pantarʉ'pɨ'sa' ta'nʉ'tane asanta tawɨrɨ.  
\v 9 Kamoro to' rawɨrɨ tʉutɨsan mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ kamoro to' e'ma'pʉ pe tʉutɨsan ukɨ'pɨ'nʉnpɨtʉ'pʉ, 
\q1 “Usana!”\f + \fr 11:9 \fq Usana! \ft Ipuru amʉ' maimu, \fq Pika'tɨ'! \ft ta e'kwa iyenasa' apurɨpɨ'nɨto' yai pe; v. 10 yau nɨrɨ.\f* 
\q1 “Pori' rɨ kʉrɨ esi Itepuru ese' yau nʉye'ai'ne'!” 
\q1  
\v 10 “Pori' pe rɨ e'nɨ ukʉipʉnʉ kon Tepi' e'to' esa' wannɨ pe uyepʉ pɨ'!” 
\q1 “Usana ka' entawon yau!” 
\m tukai'. 
\p  
\v 11 Sises epa'ka'pʉ Surusiran pona, mɨrɨpan utɨ'pʉ Esuwerʉ amʉ' use'mato', ɨpʉremato' iwʉ' ta', mɨrɨpan uya tanporon nɨ enpɨtʉ'pʉ. Pata uko'manka'sa' pɨ' nin si, iyenna'po'pʉ mɨrɨ Pe'tani pona 12 kaisaron kon tʉpoitorʉ ton pokon pe. \fig “Pori' pe rɨ e'nɨ ukʉipʉnʉ kon Tepi' e'to' esa' wannɨ pe uyepʉ pɨ'!”|src="CN01783B.tif" size="span" loc="MRK 11:1-11" copy="David C. Cook" ref="11:10" \fig* 
\s1 Yʉi Pa'nʉkʉ'pʉ Sises Uya 
\r (Ma'siu 21:18-19) 
\p  
\v 12 Mɨrɨ ema'sa' yau, Pe'tani poi to' enna'po koro'tau, Sises esi'pʉ iwan pe.  
\v 13 Ɨnnɨ tare kenan, pi' e' ene tʉuya pɨ', itɨ'pʉ teperu ke pe' iyesi tukai' ense'na. Eposa' iya a'tai, ɨ'rɨ eporo'pʉ iya pen nɨ, iyare ton nɨken, apʉne pʉra pi' weyu pe pʉra pata esi'pʉ,\f + \fr 11:13 \ft Pi' e' are enpu na'kɨ eporo tʉuya tʉnɨ'ton tukai' Sises esi'pʉ, teperu ke iyena rawɨrɨ. Itenpu pʉra si iyesi pɨ', Sises uya i'tu'pʉ tepetasen ye' pe pʉra iyesi tukai', mɨrɨpan pa'nʉkʉ'pʉ iya.\f* 
\v 14 mɨrɨpan uya ta'pʉ pi' e' pɨ', “Tɨwɨ si ɨnʉ' rɨ ɨyeperu na'nin kanan serɨ enta',” ta'pʉ iya. Ipoitorʉ ton uya mɨrɨ ta iya eta'pʉ. 
\s1 Sises Utɨ'pʉ Esuwerʉ Amʉ' Use'mato', Ɨpʉremato' Iwʉ' Ta' 
\r (Ma'siu 21:12-17; Ʉru' 19:45-48; Isaan 2:13-22) 
\p  
\v 15 Surusiran eporo pe, Sises ewomʉ'pʉ Esuwerʉ amʉ' use'mato', ɨpʉremato' iwʉ' pʉ'kʉ ta', mɨrɨpan e'sara'tɨ'pʉ usennapɨ' nɨ pɨ', kʉrʉpo'po pɨ' mɨrɨ yau te'san enpa'kapɨtʉ pɨ'. Pʉrata ensimapɨ'nin nan tepʉrʉʉi rawoipɨtʉ'pʉ iya mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wako'wa amʉ' kʉrʉpo'pomanin nan apon ton nɨ,  
\v 16 ɨnʉ' uya rɨ tʉkʉrʉpo'pooi arɨ i'se pʉra rɨ iyesi'pʉ mɨrɨ awɨrɨ.  
\v 17 To' enupa tʉuya koro'tau nin si, “Iye'menukasa' pʉra pe' nai: 
\q1 “‘Uiwʉ' esa'to' oton 
\q2 tanporon kon tʉpataron kon ɨpʉremato' iwʉ',’\f + \fr 11:17 \ft Eren 118:25-26\f* 
\m tukai'? E'tane ‘ama' amʉ' en pe rɨ’\f + \fr 11:17 \ft Aisaya 56:7; Iseremaya 7:11\f* iku'sa' auya'nokon,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 18 Papa ena' use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Main pɨ' enupanin nan uya mɨrɨ eta'pʉ, mɨrɨpan kon e'sara'tɨ'pʉ iwɨto' tʉuya'nokon eseru warinpa pɨ', ipɨ' tenari'nʉmʉ kon pɨ', apʉne pʉra anpisin nɨ usewansiukasa' pɨ' to' enupato' iya pɨ'. 
\p  
\v 19 Pata uko'mansa' a'tai, Sises mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ipoitorʉ ton utɨ'pʉ pata yapai. 
\s1 Usenupan Nɨto' Pi' E' Pɨ' 
\r (Ma'siu 21:20-22) 
\p  
\v 20 Awanakʉi' mɨrɨ ema'sa' yau, to' utɨ koro'tau asanta tawɨrɨ, to' uya pi' e' ene'pʉ. Iyeri'sa' esi'pʉ siya rɨ imi' pona rɨ.  
\v 21 Pi'ta enu ya' iyee'pʉ, mɨrɨpan uya ta'pʉ Sises pɨ', “Rapai,\f + \fr 11:21 \fq Rapai, Ti'sa \ft ta e'kwa pe\f* apʉne enkɨ. Pi' e' anpa'nʉkʉ'pʉ useketasa'!” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 22 Sises uya eikʉ'pʉ, “Papa apurɨto' esa' pe e'tɨ'.  
\v 23 I'napairon ekama uya ɨpɨ'nokon; ɨnʉ' uya rɨ se wʉ' pɨ' ta pe iyesi yau, ‘Parau ka' ɨsennasikata,’ ikasimai'ma pʉra tewan yau, e'tane apurɨi'ma tʉmaimu awɨrɨ iye'kupʉ tukai', iye'kupʉ rɨ itiwano' pe.\x - \xo 11:23 \xt Ma'siu 17:20; 1 Koren 13:2\x* 
\v 24 Mɨrɨ pɨ' ekama uya ɨpɨ'nokon, ɨ'rɨ rɨ ekama'po auya'nokon a'tai ɨwɨpʉremato' kon yau, apurɨtɨ' eposa' auya'nokon tukai', mɨrɨ a'tai ɨiwano' kon pe rɨ iyesi.  
\v 25 Ɨpʉreman pɨ' ɨye'mʉ'sa'kasa' kon a'tai, mɨrɨ koro'tau ekamʉra rɨ ɨnʉ' pɨ' rɨ ɨwesi kon yau, ipɨ' ɨsentu'matɨ', ɨkʉipʉnʉ kon, Epʉn pon usentu'mato' pe amakooi kon pɨ',” ta'pʉ Sises uya.\f + \fr 11:25 \ft Tʉron nɨ imenukasa' ton uya v. 26 ke iponantɨsa' se kasa: \fv 26 \fv*\fq E'tane tʉusentu'masen pe pʉra ɨwesi yau, ɨkʉipʉnʉ, Epʉn pon usentu'ma pʉra rɨ iyesi mɨrɨ amakooi ton pɨ'.\f* 
\s1 Sises Ekama'popɨtʉ'pʉ To' Uya 
\r (Ma'siu 21:23-27; Ʉru' 20:1-8) 
\p  
\v 27 Surusiran pona kanan to' enna'pokaa'pʉ. Sises usarɨ koro'tau Esuwerʉ amʉ' use'mato', ɨpʉremato' iwʉ' pʉ'kʉ tau, Papa ena' use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton, Main pɨ' enupanin nan mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Esuwerʉ amʉ' epuru ton uyee'pʉ ipiya',  
\v 28 mɨrɨpan kon uya ekama'po'pʉ, “Ɨ'rɨ meruntɨrʉ winɨ serɨ ton kupʉ auya? Ɨnʉ' uya serɨ meruntɨ ke ɨrepasa' serɨ kupʉ pa?” ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\p  
\v 29 Sises uya entakanoma'pʉ, “Tikin nan pɨ' rɨ ɨyekama'po uya 'nokon. Uyei'tɨ'; mɨrɨ a'tai nin si ekama uya mɨrɨ, mɨrɨ winɨ umeruntɨrʉ tepose, serɨ ton kupʉ uya tukai'.  
\v 30 Isaan uya pa'taisiman nɨto'—Epʉn winon pe', mɨrɨ pe pʉra ka'pon amʉ' winon katɨ? Ekamatɨ'!” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 31 Tiwano' kon pe to' usaurokʉ'pʉ, “‘Epʉn winon,’ ta pe iyesi yau, ‘Ɨ'rɨ pe ken si iyesi pɨ' apurɨ auya'nokon pʉra iyesi'pʉ?’ ta iya esi.  
\v 32 E'tane, ‘Ka'pon amʉ' winon,’ ta pe iyesi yau,… .” (To' enari'nʉmʉ ka'pon amʉ' pɨ', apʉne pʉra tanporon kon uya rɨ Isaan esi pu'kena' pe ta pɨ'.) 
\p  
\v 33 Mɨrɨpan kon uya Sises eikʉ'pʉ, “Ina uya i'tu pʉra man,” ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\p Sises uya ta'pʉ to' pɨ', “Apana'tɨ uya 'nokon pʉra rɨ nɨrɨ iyesi mɨrɨ, mɨrɨ meruntɨrʉ winɨ serɨ ton kupʉ uya tukai',” ta'pʉ iya. 
\c 12  
\s1 Umɨ Esa' Pe Inonkasa' Kon Pantomʉ 
\r (Ma'siu 21:33-46; Ʉru' 20:9-19) 
\p  
\v 1 Panton yai to' auro'ka pɨ' Sises e'sara'tɨ'pʉ: “Ka'pon uya umɨ pɨmɨ'pʉ kʉre' itese', si'na' pe te'sen kiyari ye' ke. Iwoi iwekupiri'tɨ'pʉ iya, ikasu'kato' iyai aka'pʉ iya, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ipa'simato' awonsi'kɨ ka'tawon soto'pan ɨutɨ amɨ'pʉ iya. Mɨrɨpan nin si tʉrʉ'pʉ iya mɨrɨ umɨ pɨ' te'san ena', mɨrɨpan utɨ'pʉ siya rɨ tʉpata'se' yapai.  
\v 2 Iyakʉ'pʉsa' anʉmʉ weyu si e'seposa' a'tai, tʉpoitorʉ si ennoko'pʉ iya umɨ tʉrʉ'pʉ tʉuya itena' ton piya' ti'kiyari epose'na.  
\v 3 E'tane kʉrɨ rɨ a'si'pʉ to' uya, ipanta'ma'pʉ to' uya, mɨrɨpan nin si ennoko'pʉ to' uya mɨrɨ itemiyatʉ arʉ pʉra rɨ.  
\v 4 Mɨrɨ a'tai, tʉron nɨ kanan tʉpoitorʉ ennoko'pʉ iya to' piya'; i'pai pɨ' nin si pʉse rɨ wɨpɨtʉ'pʉ to' uya mɨrɨ, mɨrɨpan ɨri pe rɨ to' uya ikupʉ'pʉ.  
\v 5 E'tane rɨ kanan tʉron nɨ ennoko'pʉ iya. Kʉrɨ rɨ nin si wɨnɨ'pʉ to' uya mɨrɨ. Tu'ke rɨ tʉron kon enno'pɨtʉ'pʉ iya; tʉron kon nɨ panta'mapɨtʉ'pʉ to' uya, tʉron kon nɨ wɨnɨi'ma. 
\p  
\v 6 “Tikin nɨ nin si inennokonʉ e'nonkasa' esi'pʉ, imu rɨ nin si, ini'nʉnkanʉ. ‘Pʉse rɨ, umu nin si nama to' uya mɨrɨ,’ tai'ma nin si tanporon kon u'matʉ pe ennoko'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 7 “E'tane nin si to' uya ta'pʉ mɨrɨ, tiwano' kon pe, ‘Pʉse rɨ kuru pʉse rɨ kiyari pata'se' anʉnton. Iwɨto' kon pe ɨsi'tɨ', inanʉmʉnʉ e'to' pe uiwano' kon pe,’ ta'pʉ to' uya.  
\v 8 To' uya si a'si'pʉ, mɨrɨpan wɨnɨ'pʉ to' uya, mɨrɨpan eno'ma'pʉ to' uya kiyari e'kwa apai. 
\p  
\v 9 “Ɨ'rɨ ken si kupʉ kʉrɨ rɨ kiyari e'kwa esa' uya? Iyepʉ kamoro itesa' pe tʉnnonka'san wɨse'na, mɨrɨpan uya nin si mɨrɨ kiyari e'kwa tʉrʉ mɨrɨ tʉron kon ena'.  
\v 10 Itekare pe' iye'menukasa' ennin nan pen ɨmɨrɨ'nokon: 
\q1 “‘Tɨ' ɨutɨ amɨnin nan neno'ma'pʉ 
\q2 enasa' itekun airon tɨ' pe; 
\q1  
\v 11 Itepuru uya rɨ serɨ ku'sa', mɨrɨpan esi wakʉ pe kuru uyenu kon yau,’\f + \fr 12:11 \ft Eren 118:22-23\f* 
\m tukai'?” 
\p  
\v 12 A'sito' tʉuya'nokon ipɨkɨrɨ warinpa'pʉ to' uya, apʉne pʉra tʉpɨ'nokon ta iya e'kwa pe mɨrɨ panton ekamasa' iya tukai' to' uya i'tu'pʉ. E'tane anpisin ton ka'pon amʉ' pɨ' to' enari'nʉmʉ'pʉ; mɨrɨpan kon uya nin si inɨmɨ'pʉ mɨrɨ, to' utɨ'pʉ ipiyapai. 
\s1 Esuwerʉ Amʉ' Uya Rɨ Pe' Pʉrata Nonka Pata Esa' Ena'? 
\r (Ma'siu 22:15-22; Ʉru' 20:20-26) 
\p  
\v 13 Emennʉ'pʉ po iwa rɨ, Pari'si amʉ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Era' pɨkɨron kon ennoko'pʉ to' uya Sises eparantɨi' imaimu winɨ.  
\v 14 To' uyee'pʉ ipiya', mɨrɨpan kon uya ta'pʉ ipɨ', “Ti'sa, ina i'tu pɨ' man i'napairon ye' pe ɨwesi tukai'. Ka'pon amʉ' rɨ nensimanʉ pe pʉra ɨyeseru esi, apʉne pʉra ɨnʉ' pe rɨ to' esi pɨ' te'namasen pe pʉra ɨwesi; e'tane Papa eseru pɨ' enupan auya i'napairon awɨrɨ. Ipoken pe' iyesi Sisa ena' pʉrata tʉtʉsen e'ma a'tai, kane katɨ?  
\v 15 Ina uya pe' e'ma, mɨrɨ pe pʉra ina uya e'ma pen nɨ katɨ?” ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\p E'tane wakʉ pe to' e'ku'to' eseru i'tusa' Sises uya esi'pʉ, “Ɨ'rɨ pe iyesi pɨ' usa'mapai ɨwesi kon? Apʉne pʉrata pun\f + \fr 12:15 \fq pʉrata pun \ft —tenariyas itese'\f* ine'tɨ' ento' pe uya,” ta'pʉ iya.  
\v 16 To' uya pʉrata pun nee'pʉ, mɨrɨpan kon ekama'po'pʉ iya, “Ɨnʉ' nai ipɨ'? Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨnʉ' ese' nai ipɨ'?” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p “Sisa,” ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\p  
\v 17 Mɨrɨ a'tai, Sises uya ta'pʉ to' pɨ', “Sisa iwano' rɨ itʉtɨ' Sisa ena', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Papa iwano' rɨ kanan tʉrʉ auya'nokon Papa ena',” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p Mɨrɨpan kon nin si usewansiuka'pʉ mɨrɨ ipɨ'. 
\s1 Eri'nɨ Tʉpo E'mʉ'sa'kan Nɨto' 
\r (Ma'siu 22:23-33; Ʉru' 20:27-40) 
\p  
\v 18 Mɨrɨ a'tai, Satu'si amʉ', eri'nɨ tʉpo e'mʉ'sa'kan pʉra rɨ iyesi tawon nan uyee'pʉ Sises ekama'pose'na.  
\v 19 “Ti'sa, Mosi' uya imenukasa' uiwano' kon pe, ka'pon rui eri'sa' yau, tʉno'pʉ tʉnonkai' imunkɨ pʉra, iyakon nʉ'pʉ uya ino'pʉ rʉ'pʉ mari'mato' pe iyesi, mɨrɨpan kon umu'tato' pe tʉrui iwano' pe.  
\v 20 Moro 7 kaisaron kon ɨsirunan esi'pʉ. Wapiyaro' emari'ma'pʉ, mɨrɨpan erikʉ'pʉ innonkaton kon imunkɨ amʉ' pʉra rɨ.  
\v 21 Ipɨkɨron nʉ'pʉ uya nin si ino'pʉ rʉ'pʉ mari'ma'pʉ mɨrɨ, e'tane iyerikʉ'pʉ tʉumu'tai' pʉra rɨ kanan. Mɨrɨ kasa rɨ to' osorʉwano pe te'sen esi'pʉ.  
\v 22 Mɨrɨ kasa rɨ tanporo 7 kaisa rɨ to' esi'pʉ imunkɨ amʉ' pʉra rɨ to' eri'pɨtʉ'pʉ. Kʉrɨ rɨ nin si uri'san erikʉ'pʉ mɨrɨ to' e'ma'pʉ pe rɨ.  
\v 23 Eri'nɨ tʉpo e'mʉ'sa'kan nɨsa' a'tai, ɨnʉ' no'pʉ pe ken si iyesi mɨrɨ, apʉne pʉra sa'ne 7 kaisaron kon uya imari'mapɨ'sa'?” ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\p  
\v 24 Sises uya ta'pʉ to' pɨ', “Ipoken pʉra pe' ɨwesi kon pen mɨrɨ iye'menukasa' itekare mɨrɨ pe pʉra Papa meruntɨrʉ i'tu auya'nokon pʉra iyesi pɨ'?  
\v 25 Iyeri'sa' kon e'mʉ'sa'kasa' a'tai, to' emari'ma pʉra rɨ iyesi, mɨrɨ pe pʉra to' e'tʉrʉ pen nɨ emari'man nɨto' yau; Epʉn pon kon, inserʉ amʉ' kasa to' e'to' oton.  
\v 26 Iyeri'sa' kon e'mʉ'sa'ka tawon pɨ', Mosi' karetaai yawon pe' ensa' auya'nokon pʉra rɨ iyesi, yu' epo'tɨ'pʉ tawon? Mɨrɨ yau, Papa uya ta'pʉ ipɨ', ‘Urɨ kʉrɨ rɨ Epʉra'an, Aisi' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Seko' pokon e'to' itese' pɨ'.’\f + \fr 12:26 \ft E'sotas 3:6\f* 
\v 27 Papa, iyeri'sa' kon e'to' itese' pɨ' pe iyesi pen, e'tane nurɨnan kon nɨken. Ipoken pʉra kuru ɨwesi kon mɨrɨ,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\s1 Eke Kuru Iyawɨrɨ E'nɨto' 
\r (Ma'siu 22:34-40; Ʉru' 10:25-28) 
\p  
\v 28 Main pɨ' enupanin nan tonpa uye'sa' uya to' usaurokʉ etapɨtʉ'pʉ. Wakʉ pe to' maimu ei'sa' Sises uya pɨ', ekama'po'pʉ iya, “Tanporon iyawɨrɨ e'nɨto' pe inonkasa' Main ton koro'tapai, nai esi eke pe kuru?” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 29 Sises uya ta'pʉ ipɨ', “Se kuru serɨ eke, ‘Etatɨ' Esuwerʉ amʉ' rʉ'kwɨ; Itepuru itese' pɨ' e'nɨto' esi, tikin nan nɨ Itepuru;  
\v 30 Itepuru, itese' pɨ' ɨwe'to' i'nʉnkakɨ tanporo ɨyewan pokon pe, aya'kwarʉ pokon pe, ɨusenuminkato' pokon pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tanporo ɨmeruntɨrʉ pokon pe,’\f + \fr 12:30 \ft Isu'taronomi 6:4-5\f* tawon.  
\v 31 Ipɨkɨron esi se: ‘Ɨtonpa i'nʉnkakɨ mɨsi'nʉnkayai'ne' kasa,’\f + \fr 12:31 \ft Ripaiti'kas 19:18\f* tawon. Serɨ ton iyawɨrɨ e'nɨto' entaino eke pʉra rɨ iyesi mɨrɨ,” ta'pʉ Sises uya ipɨ'. 
\p  
\v 32 “Ti'sa, wakʉ pe kuru ei'sa' auya man, ipoken nɨ mʉkayai'ne' esi, Papa esi tikin nan nɨ, ɨnʉ' pʉra rɨ iyesi e'tane kʉrɨ rɨ rɨken.  
\v 33 I'nʉnkato' tanporo ewan wannɨ pokon pe, ito'ka'nʉ'to' pokon pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ meruntɨrʉ wannɨ pokon pe, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tonpa i'nʉnka usi'nʉnkan kasa rɨ esi eke pe kuru tʉpo'tɨse tʉtʉsen mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉron nɨ ton nɨ use'man nɨto' entai,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 34 Wakʉ pe teikʉ iya etasa' Sises uya a'tai, “Ɨnnɨ pʉra rɨ me'ai' Papa e'to' esa' wannɨ pe piyapai,” ta'pʉ iya ipɨ'. Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ nin si mɨrɨ enta', ɨnʉ' rɨ esi'pʉ ɨnekama'popɨ'pai pʉra. 
\s1 Ɨnʉ' Pa Rʉ'pʉ Pe Kʉrai Esi? 
\r (Ma'siu 22:41-46; Ʉru' 20:41-44) 
\p  
\v 35 Sises esi koro'tau enupan pɨ' Esuwerʉ amʉ' use'mato', ɨpʉremato' iwʉ' pʉ'kʉ tau, to' ekama'po'pʉ iya, “Ɨ'rɨ pe iyesi pɨ' Main pɨ' enupanin nan uya Kʉrai\f + \fr 12:35 \fq Kʉrai \ft (Kiri' maimu yau); mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq Me'saya \ft (Ipuru maimu yau), asa'rɨ rɨ marɨ iyesi, \fq Papa Nanʉmʉ'pʉ \ft ta e'kwa pe.\f* esi Tepi' pa rʉ'pʉ pe ta?  
\v 36 Tepi' rɨ usaurokʉ'pʉ Wakʉ A'kwarʉ uya tʉmaimu'tɨi', 
\q1 “‘Itepuru uya ta'pʉ uyepuru pɨ': 
\q2 “Ereuta' enwo'ne' uyemiyatʉ winɨ, 
\q1 ɨyeyaton non tʉrʉ uya 
\q2 a'ta o'koi' pʉ'kʉ pona,”\f + \fr 12:36 \ft Eren 110:1\f* ta'pʉ iya.’ 
\m  
\v 37 Tepi' uya tʉmɨrɨ pe rɨ ‘uyepuru’ tukai' esakʉ, nai kasa ken ipa rʉ'pʉ pe iyesi nesii'no?” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p Anpisin ton Sises etanin nan esi'pʉ pori' pe. 
\p  
\v 38 To' enupa tʉuya koro'tau, Sises uya ta'pʉ to' pɨ', “Tenu ke e'tɨ' Main pɨ' enupanin nan pɨ', ɨpininpaino kon kusan tʉpon kon yau, ‘Miyarɨ,’ ta i'sero' kon tʉpɨ'nokon kʉrʉpo'po pɨ' e'nɨ pata'se' yau rɨ,  
\v 39 eke ton apon po kuru te'san Esuwerʉ amʉ' usenupato' iwʉ' tau, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉnamasan pata'se' yau kuru te'san enta'nan a'tai'ne.  
\v 40 Itaan'pʉ ima'tasa' rʉ'san iwʉ' mo'kanin nan to' enapai, mɨrɨpan kon ɨpʉrema kusan pe, mɨ pe te'kupʉ kon pe. Pʉsamoro waraino kon kota'ma mɨrɨ ɨsɨ pe kuru rɨ,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\s1 Itaan'pʉ Ima'tasa' Rʉ'pʉ Nʉtʉrʉnʉ 
\r (Ʉru' 21:1-4) 
\p  
\v 41 Sises ereuta'pʉ tʉtʉsen nonkato' to' uya pata'se' ratoi pe, anpisin ton ka'pon amʉ' uya tʉpʉrataai kon tʉpɨtʉ Esuwerʉ amʉ' use'mato', ɨpʉremato' iwʉ' pʉrataai yen ya' enpɨtʉ pɨ'. Tu'kan kon nɨ ipʉrataaike' ton uya eke pe rɨ itʉpɨtʉ'pʉ.  
\v 42 E'tane rʉ'kwɨ nin si entu'manin itaan'pʉ ima'tasa' rʉ'pʉ uyee'pʉ, mɨrɨpan uya rʉ'kwɨ asa'ron pʉrata ka'pa muku'pɨ\f + \fr 12:42 \fq asa'rɨ ire'pʉ'ta amʉ' \ft Kiri' maimu yau\f* tʉrʉ'pʉ, \tl peni\tl* punu'pɨ rʉ'kwɨ rɨ. 
\p  
\v 43 Tʉpoitorʉ ton tʉkɨ'mai' tʉpiya', ta'pʉ to' pɨ', “I'napairon ekama uya ɨpɨ'nokon, pʉse rɨ entu'manin itaan'pʉ ima'tasa' rʉ'pʉ uya eke pe kuru itʉsa' mɨrɨ pʉrata yen ya', tanporo tʉron kon entai kuru.  
\v 44 Tʉpʉrataai kon tonpa rɨ nin tʉsa' to' uya, e'tane kʉrɨ rɨ, tekota'mato' apai rʉ'kwɨ rɨ tanporo rɨ tʉpiyawon tʉrʉ'pʉ tʉuko'manto' ipɨ' rʉ'kwɨ rɨ,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\c 13  
\s1 Ima'kʉʉi Ton Non Weyu U'matʉ Ekamanin Nan 
\r (Ma'siu 24:1-31; Ʉru' 21:5-28) 
\p  
\v 1 Esuwerʉ amʉ' use'mato', ɨpʉremato' iwʉ' nɨmɨ iya koro'tau, ipoitorʉ ton tonpa uya ta'pʉ ipɨ', “Ti'sa, apʉne enkɨ; ɨ'rɨ eke ton nɨ tɨ' amʉ'! Ɨ'rɨ wakʉ pe rɨ amɨsa' ɨutɨ ton!” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 2 “Tanporo rɨ pe' serɨ ton eke ton ɨutɨ amɨpɨ'sa' menyan?” ta'pʉ Sises uya. “Tikin nɨ rɨ tɨ' e'nonkato' oton pen mɨrɨ ɨsipʉro'po; tanporon nɨ uta'po'to' oton mɨrɨ,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 3 Sises ereutasa' koro'tau Are' Wʉpʉ po, Esuwerʉ amʉ' use'mato', ɨpʉremato' iwʉ' ratoi pe, Pi'ta, Isens, Isaan, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Anturu pokon uya ekama'po'pʉ ama'ai,  
\v 4 “Ina pɨ' ekamakɨ, ɨ'rɨ a'tai kuru ken si serɨ ton e'ku'to' oton? Ɨ'rɨ kuru ken si esi mɨrɨ ento' ipɨ' pe tanporo serɨ ton uta'ku'tɨ ekamanin pe?” ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\p  
\v 5 Sises uya ta'pʉ to' pɨ', “Tenu ke e'tɨ', ɨnʉ' uya rɨ ɨyenku'tɨ kon namai'.  
\v 6 Tu'kan kon nɨ uye'to' oton uyese' yau, ‘Urɨ rɨ kʉrɨ rɨ,’ ka'se'na, mɨrɨpan kon uya tu'kan kon nɨ enku'tɨto' oton.  
\v 7 Tʉusewa'nomasan mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ usewa'noman man tawon eta auya'nokon a'tai, ketʉipɨ'tʉu mɨrɨ pɨ'. Serɨ warai'nan nɨ e'ku'to' pe iyesi e'tane apʉne rɨ non weyu u'ma'to' uye'tane rɨ iyesi.  
\v 8 Tʉpataron kon uya tʉpataron kon nɨ nɨrɨ ewa'nomato' oton, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ esa' wannɨ pe rɨ te'san uya esa' wannɨ pe te'san nɨ nɨrɨ ewa'noma. Mɨrɨ a'tai, tʉrʉ'pʉnʉ amʉ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iwankan e'to' oton mɨrɨ pata kaisa rɨ. Serɨ ton si esi mɨrɨ e'tinkan e'sara'tɨ pe. 
\p  
\v 9 “Ɨserasu pe rɨ me'tʉi'. Ɨtʉto' oton kon mɨrɨ pata konsʉrʉʉi amʉ' ena', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Esuwerʉ amʉ' usenupato' iwʉ' tau ayari'po'pɨ'to' oton kon. Urɨ pɨkɨrɨ ɨye'soto'kato' oton kon kopʉna amʉ', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ kin amʉ' rau rɨ to' pana ya' urɨ ekama pɨ'.  
\v 10 Mɨrɨpan wapiya kuru wakʉ itekare usekamato' pe iyesi tanporon kon mɨ yawɨron kon pana ya'.  
\v 11 To' uya aya'sisa' kon arɨ a'tai ko'tʉ ta', pena rɨ kɨsewankamatʉu, ‘Ɨ'rɨ kuru ta uya?’ tukai', amaimu'tɨsa' kon na'ne' ke rɨ ausaurokʉ kon mɨrɨ, ɨiwano' kon pe ausaurokʉ kon pen e'tane Wakʉ A'kwarʉ usaurokʉ.\x - \xo 13:11 \xt Ma'siu 10:17-20; Ʉru' 12:11-12\x* 
\p  
\v 12 “Eri'nɨto' ya' tʉrui eparankato' oton iyakon uya, ikʉipʉnʉ uya nɨrɨ tʉmʉre. Mɨrɨ kasa rɨ marɨ, mʉre amʉ' enato' oton tʉsan kon amʉ' ewa'noma pɨ' to' eri'to' ya' to' tʉrʉ pɨ'.  
\v 13 Urɨ uriya' tu'kan kon ka'pon amʉ' uya ɨyewaruma'tɨto' oton kon, e'tane kʉrɨ rɨ pana' pe ne'mʉ'sa'kayai'ne' iu'matʉ pona rɨ epika'tɨto' oton mɨrɨ.\x - \xo 13:13 \xt Ma'siu 10:22\x* 
\p  
\v 14 “‘Ɨri Kuru Nuirapanin Uma'tan Emapu'tɨnin’\f + \fr 13:14 \ft Taniyerʉ 9:27; 11:31; 12:11.\f* e'soto'kasa' ene auya'nokon a'tai, tʉpata'se' pen nɨ yau—tɨwɨ serɨ ennin nʉto'ka'nʉkʉi—tɨwɨ kamoro Isutiya po na'ne' nan nainʉmʉi wʉ' ton pona'ne.  
\v 15 Tɨwɨ tiwʉ' nakapu po te'sen kʉu'tɨnin mɨrɨ pe pʉra kʉsewonnin nɨ ɨutɨ ta' ɨ'rɨ rɨ mo'kai'.  
\v 16 Tɨwɨ ɨnʉ' rɨ umɨ yau na'ne' kʉsenna'ponin tʉpon epose'na.\x - \xo 13:16 \xt Ʉru' 17:31\x* 
\v 17 Mɨrɨ wʉi a'tai'ne ɨsɨ pe kuru rɨ uri'sami'si amʉ' mono' pe te'san pona iye'to' oton mɨrɨ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ mana' pokon kon imunkɨ pona.  
\v 18 Ɨpʉrematɨ' serɨ e'kupʉ namai' komi' pe pata e'to' weyu a'tai,  
\v 19 apʉne pʉra mɨrɨ waraino ewankamanin e'ku'sa' pʉra rɨ iyesi iyepiya'tɨ'pʉ si'kɨrɨ, Papa uya non kaa'pʉ si'kɨrɨ serɨ pʉ'kʉ pona, mɨrɨ waraino kanan e'ku'to' oton pen nɨ.\x - \xo 13:19 \xt Taniyerʉ 12:1; Isenpoikasa' 7:14\x* 
\p  
\v 20 “Itepuru uya serɨ iweyu ton nu'tɨsa' pʉra iyesi yau, ɨnʉ' ne'nonkai'no pen nɨ. E'tane anʉnsa' kon, tʉnanʉmʉ'san pɨkɨrɨ nin ito'kena'masa' iya mɨrɨ.  
\v 21 Mɨrɨ a'tai, ɨnʉ' uya rɨ ta pe iyesi yau ɨpɨ'nokon, ‘Apʉne entɨ', serɨ airɨ Kʉrai\f + \fr 13:21 \fq Kʉrai \ft (Kiri' maimu yau); mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq Me'saya \ft (Ipuru maimu yau), asa'rɨ rɨ marɨ iyesi, \fq Papa Nanʉmʉ'pʉ \ft ta e'kwa pe.\f* man!’ mɨrɨ pe pʉra, ‘Apʉne entɨ'! Mɨ airɨ man!’ ta pe iyesi yau, kʉsapurɨtʉu.  
\v 22 Apʉne pʉra enku'tɨnin nan kʉrai amʉ', enku'tɨnin nan pu'kena' amʉ' usenpoikato' oton, mɨrɨpan kon uya i'tuto' ipɨ' ton mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ eke Papa tʉrawasooi ton ku'to' oton anʉnsa' kon enku'tɨ pe, ikupʉ tʉuya'nokon poken iyesi yau.  
\v 23 Mɨrɨ pɨ' ɨiwano' kon pe rɨ ɨserasu kon pe e'tɨ'; tanporon nɨ ekamasa' uya mɨrɨ ɨpɨ'nokon iweyu wapiya. 
\p  
\v 24 “E'tane mɨrɨ a'tai'ne, usewankaman pata'pʉ pe, 
\q1 “‘Wʉi enu ewarumanto' oton, 
\q2 kapʉi e'wei'tɨto' oton pen; 
\q1  
\v 25 sirikɨ amʉ' uta'po'to' oton ka' apai, 
\q2 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ka' yau rɨ te'san usi'ki'mato' oton.’\f + \fr 13:25 \ft Aisaya 13:10; 34:4; Isi'kiyerʉ 32:7; Isowerʉ 2:10, 31; 3:15; Isenpoikasa' 1:7; 6:12.\f* 
\p  
\v 26 “Mɨrɨ a'tai si, ka'pon amʉ' uya Ka'pon, Papa winon uyepʉ ento' oton mɨrɨ kapuru' yau eke tʉmeruntɨrʉ ke mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ a'kwa yau,\x - \xo 13:26 \xt Taniyerʉ 7:13; Isenpoikasa' 1:7\x* 
\v 27 mɨrɨpan uya tinserʉʉi ton ennoko tʉnanʉmʉ'san amʉranʉ'se asakɨrɨ'nan a'setun uye'to' yawɨron kon nɨ, non pʉ'kʉ u'matʉ apai'ne, ka' u'matʉ pʉ'kʉ ponsi'kɨ'ne. 
\s1 Pi' E' Pɨ' Usenupan Nɨto' 
\r (Ma'siu 24:32-35; Ʉru' 21:29-33) 
\p  
\v 28 “Ɨsenupatɨ' se pi' e' pɨ': Iyepanta'tɨ are ton atu'ta a'tai, a'ko pe wʉi a'ne' pe pata e'to' weyu e'seporo tukai' i'tu auya'nokon.  
\v 29 Mɨrɨ kasa rɨ, serɨ ton e'kupʉ ene auya'nokon a'tai, a'ko pe iyesi mʉra'ta nau rɨ tukai' i'tu auya'nokon.  
\v 30 I'napairon ekama uya ɨpɨ'nokon; serɨ a'taino kon kuru rɨ pʉra iyenato' oton pen nɨ serɨ ton e'kupʉ pʉ'kʉ pona rɨ.  
\v 31 Epʉn mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ non pʉra iyenato' oton, e'tane umaimu mɨrɨ tereutaton pen nɨ. 
\s1 Ɨnʉ' Ni'tunʉ Pen Iweyu 
\r (Ma'siu 24:36-44) 
\p  
\v 32 “Ɨnʉ' uya mɨrɨ wʉi mɨrɨ pe pʉra iwekusi i'tu pʉra rɨ iyesi, inserʉ amʉ' Epʉn pon kon uya rɨ mɨrɨ pe pʉra imu uya rɨ, e'tane ikʉipʉnʉ uya rɨken i'tu.  
\v 33 Ɨiwano' kon pe rɨ ɨserasu kon pe e'tɨ'! Tenu ke e'tɨ'!\f + \fr 13:33 \ft Tʉron nɨ imenukasa' uya, \fq Tenu ke e'tɨ', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨpʉrematɨ'! \ft ta.\f* I'tu auya'nokon pʉra iyesi ɨ'rɨ a'tai mɨrɨ weyu e'seporo tukai'.  
\v 34 Ɨnnɨ ka'pon utɨ kasa iyesi: Tʉpoitorʉ ton enau tiwʉ' nɨmɨ iya, to' tʉrawasooi ke to' tʉrepapɨ'se, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ mʉra'tanawon pɨ' tenu ke e'kɨ tai'ma.\x - \xo 13:34 \xt Ʉru' 12:36-38\x* 
\p  
\v 35 “Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', enei'ma e'tɨ', apʉne pʉra i'tu auya'nokon kasa pʉra ɨ'rɨ a'tai ɨutɨ esa' enna'poto' oton tukai'—ko'mamʉ pe rɨ, mɨrɨ pe pʉra anomʉra' rɨ, mɨrɨ pe pʉra rɨ kɨrɨtɨkɨ uturumʉ a'tai rɨ, mɨrɨ pe pʉra pata emakʉ a'tai.  
\v 36 Ite'kwanau pʉra rɨ iyepʉ ɨyepotɨ'nin, ɨye'nʉmʉ kon eponin.  
\v 37 Ukayai'ne' rɨ ɨpɨ'nokon nɨ marɨ ta uya tanporon kon pɨ': ‘Tenu ke e'tɨ'!’” ta'pʉ iya. 
\c 14  
\s1 Sises Karapaima'pʉ Pe'tani Po 
\r (Ma'siu 26:1-13; Ʉru' 22:1-2; Isaan 11:45-53; 12:1-8) 
\p  
\v 1 Asa'rɨ rɨken wʉi e'ku'ka'sa' esi'pʉ To' Epoi Itɨ'pʉ Weyu Rʉ'pʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ A'sarutanʉ'sa' Pen Pʉreti Pɨ' Enta'nan Weyu e'seporo rawɨrɨ,\x - \xo 14:1 \xt E'sotas 12:1-27\x* mɨrɨ pɨ' Papa ena' use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Main pɨ' enupanin nan esi'pʉ ama'ai Sises a'sito' tʉuya'nokon ipɨkɨrɨ warinpa pɨ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iwɨto' pe tʉuya'nokon.  
\v 2 “E'tane Iweyu Rʉ'pʉ a'tai pen, ka'pon amʉ' nin e'sara'tɨ esi usewa'noman pɨ',” ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\p  
\v 3 Pe'tani po iyesi koro'tau, tʉteire' po tenai' tepʉrʉ piyau, ka'pon, Saiman, erekʉ'pan tukai' ti'tusen iwʉ' tau, uri'san uyee'pʉ po'toro arapasta yawon, epe'kena' po'piyun esukenan natʉ konekasa' esa' pe. Tʉputurʉkai' i'pai pona po'piyun ma'pʉ iya.\x - \xo 14:3 \xt Ʉru' 7:37-38\x* 
\p  
\v 4 Mɨrɨ yau te'san tonpa ton usakorota usaurokʉ'pʉ tiwano' kon pe, “Ɨ'rɨto' pe rɨ si po'piyun ma'tanʉkʉ ko?  
\v 5 Ikʉrʉpo'pomapaino rɨ tikin nɨ wʉipiya iye'tʉrawasomasa' e'mato' epe' entai rɨ,\f + \fr 14:5 \fq tikin nɨ wʉipiya iye'tʉrawasomasa' e'mato' epe' entai rɨ \ft —300 pʉrata pun tenariyas itese' ton entai rɨ\f* itepe'pʉ tʉto' pe entu'manin nan ena'!” ta'pʉ to' uya. Ɨsɨ pe rɨ to' uya eseremekʉ'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 6 “Tɨwɨ nesii, ɨ'rɨ pe ikupʉ i'se ɨwesi kon? Wakʉ rɨ ku'sa' iya mɨrɨ upɨ',” ta'pʉ Sises uya to' pɨ'.  
\v 7 “Entu'manin nan kamoro ɨpiyawon kon nɨ i'se ɨwe'to' kon a'tai rɨ ɨnpika'tɨnʉ kon, e'tane inke urɨ pʉra iyesi ɨpiyau'nokon.\x - \xo 14:7 \xt Isu'taronomi 15:11\x* 
\v 8 Tʉnkupʉnʉ pokena' rɨ ku'sa' iya mɨrɨ, po'piyun masa' iya upona ukoneka pe uruwai' ya' utʉrʉ e'ma ta'.  
\v 9 I'napairon ekama uya ɨpɨ'nokon, mɨ awɨrɨ rɨ itekare nʉsekamayai'ne' non emʉ' kaisa rɨ, inkupʉ'pʉ rʉ'pʉ rɨ marɨ usekama mɨrɨ en yau ikupʉ pe rɨ,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 10 Isutas Eskariya', 12 kaisaron kon ipoitorʉ ton tonpa utɨ'pʉ use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton piya', Sises eparankase'na to' ena'.  
\v 11 To' epori'ma'pʉ mɨrɨ tetai', mɨrɨpan kon usaurokʉ'pʉ pʉrata ke irepato' tʉuya'nokon pɨ', mɨrɨpan esi'pʉ itʉto' tʉuya weyu eporo i'se. 
\s1 Itepuru Enta'nato' 
\r (Ma'siu 26:17-30; Ʉru' 22:7-20, 21-23; Isaan 13:21-30) 
\p  
\v 12 A'sarutanʉ'sa' Pen Pʉreti Pɨ' Enta'nan Weyu e'sara'tɨ a'tai, iteseru pe To' Epoi Itɨ'pʉ Weyu Rʉ'pʉ pɨ' karimeru mʉre wɨto' a'tai, Sises poitorʉ ton uya ekama'po'pʉ, “Nai ya' ina utɨ i'se me'an To' Epoi Itɨ'pʉ Weyu Rʉ'pʉ pɨ' ɨyenta'nato' konekase'na?” ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\p  
\v 13 Mɨrɨpan uya asa'rɨ tʉpoitorʉ ton ennoko'pʉ. To' pɨ' ta'pʉ iya, “Entantɨ' eke pata pona, mɨrɨpan yau, tuna anin ka'pon uya ɨyeporo kon mɨrɨ. Ipɨkɨrɨ mʉtɨtʉi'.  
\v 14 Iyewonsa' na'ne' ita' ɨutɨ esa' mekama'potʉi', ‘Ti'sa man: Nai airɨ uiwʉ' oton nai To' Epoi Itɨ'pʉ Weyu Rʉ'pʉ pɨ' upoitorʉ ton pokon pe enta'nato' itau? ta pɨ',’ mʉkatʉi'.  
\v 15 Ekama iya rɨ mɨrɨ ɨpɨ'nokon eke rɨ ka'tawon ɨutɨ tapurui'tɨse ikonekasa'. Mɨrɨ yau si enta'nan nɨto' mʉkonekatʉi',” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 16 Ipoitorʉ ton si utɨ'pʉ eke pata pona, mɨrɨpan kon uya si eporo'pʉ Sises uya tauro'ka'pʉ kon kasa rɨ, mɨrɨpan kon uya si To' Epoi Itɨ'pʉ Weyu Rʉ'pʉ pɨ' te'to' kon koneka'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 17 Pata uko'mansa' a'tai, Sises uyee'pʉ 12 kaisaron kon pokon pe.  
\v 18 Tepʉrʉ piyau tʉteire' kon po tenai' enta'nan pɨ' to' esi koro'tau, ta'pʉ iya, “I'napairon ekama uya ɨpɨ'nokon, ɨtonpa kon uya uyeparankato' oton—kʉrɨ upokon pe enta'nan pɨ' na'ne' rɨ,” ta'pʉ iya.\x - \xo 14:18 \xt Eren 41:9\x* 
\p  
\v 19 To' si upokoita'pʉ, mɨrɨpan tikin pa'ne ta'pʉ to' uya ipɨ', “I'napai rɨ urɨ pen kuru rɨ?” ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\p  
\v 20 “Ɨmɨrɨ'nokon 12 kaisaron kon tonpa, tʉyu kipʉ pɨ' na'ne' pʉsau ya' upokon pe.  
\v 21 Ka'pon, Papa winon utɨto' oton iye'menukasa' tʉpɨ' na'ne' kasa rɨ, e'tane ɨsɨ yau rɨ kʉrɨ rɨ ka'pon esi Ka'pon, Papa winon eparankanin! Wakʉ pe rɨ nesii'no iyentusa' pʉra iyesi yau,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 22 To' enta'na koro'tau, Sises uya pʉreti anʉmʉ'pʉ, tenki ta'pʉ iya Papa pɨ', mɨrɨpan uya i'kwɨ'pɨtʉ'pʉ, mɨrɨpan ekamʉ'pʉ iya tʉpoitorʉ ton ena', “Anʉntɨ', serɨ serɨ upun,” tai'ma.\x - \xo 14:22 \xt 1 Koren 11:23-25\x* 
\p  
\v 23 Mɨrɨ a'tai, ko' anʉmʉ'pʉ iya, tenki ta'pʉ iya Papa pɨ', mɨrɨpan uya to' o'pa'pʉ, tanporon kon uya iyawon ensi'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 24 “Serɨ serɨ umʉnʉ, emenna' \f + \fr 14:24 \ft Tʉron nɨ imenukasa' ton yau “emenna'” tasa' pʉra iyesi.\f* ekonekan nɨto' iwano', tu'kan kon iwano' pe iye'kwansa',” ta'pʉ iya to' pɨ'.\x - \xo 14:24 \xt E'sotas 24:8; Iseremaya 31:31-34\x* 
\v 25 “I'napairon ekama uya ɨpɨ'nokon, iteperu euku ensito' uya oton pen ɨpokon pe 'nokon Papa e'to' esa' wannɨ pe yau emenna' pe ensi uya pʉ'kʉ pona,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 26 Eren pɨ' tʉuserenkasa' kon tʉpo, to' utɨ'pʉ Are' Wʉpʉ pona. 
\s1 Pi'ta Uya Tʉnonkato' Oton Ekama'pʉ Sises Uya 
\r (Ma'siu 26:31-35; Ʉru' 22:31-34; Isaan 13:36-38) 
\p  
\v 27 “Tanporo rɨ unɨmɨ auya'nokon mɨrɨ,” tukai' Sises uya to' pana'tɨ'pʉ, “apʉne pʉra iye'menukasa': 
\q1 “‘Karimeru amʉ' pa'simanin wɨnɨ uya, 
\q2 mɨrɨpan karimeru amʉ' si e'ta'nʉ'to' oton,’\f + \fr 14:27 \ft Sakaraya 13:7\f* 
\m tawon.  
\v 28 E'tane erikʉ tʉpo, e'mʉ'sa'kasa' a'tai, utɨ mɨrɨ arawɨrɨ'nokon Kiyarari pona,” ta'pʉ iya.\x - \xo 14:28 \xt Ma'siu 28:16\x* 
\p  
\v 29 Pi'ta uya ta'pʉ, “Tanporon kon uya ɨnɨntane, ɨnɨmɨ uya pen nɨ nin mɨrɨ,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 30 “I'napairon ekama uya ɨpɨ', serɨ pe—i'nai rɨ sa'ne, serɨ ewarupɨɨi tau—kɨrɨtɨkɨ uturumʉ asa' ite'kwa rawɨrɨ, unonkato' auya oton osorʉwau ite'kwa,” ta'pʉ Sises uya. 
\p  
\v 31 E'tane miyarɨ parɨ e'se'ne' pe parɨ Pi'ta uya ta'pʉ, “Ɨ'rɨ pe pʉra rɨ aya'kɨrɨ uma'ta pe iyesi yau, ɨnonka uya pen nɨ,” ta'pʉ iya. Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tanporon kon uya rɨ mɨrɨ rɨ marɨ ta'pʉ. 
\s1 Sises Ɨpʉrema Ke'semani Po 
\r (Ma'siu 26:36-46; Ʉru' 22:39-46) 
\p  
\v 32 To' utɨ'pʉ Ke'semani tukai' tesa'sen pata ya'. Mɨrɨ yau, Sises uya ta'pʉ tʉpoitorʉ ton pɨ', “Ereutapɨ'tɨ' se airɨ ɨpʉrema tane,” ta'pʉ iya.  
\v 33 Mɨrɨpan uya Pi'ta, Isens mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Isaan arɨ'pʉ ta'kɨrɨ, mɨrɨpan usewankama ena'pʉ ika'nɨ' pʉra ipan pe rɨ.  
\v 34 “Uya'kwarʉ man pokoi pe, uma'tan poken nɨ,” ta'pʉ iya to' pɨ'. “Serɨ yau e'tɨ' tenu ke,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 35 Itɨ'pʉ miyarɨ parɨ ɨnnɨ iwa ita'mo'ka'pʉ non pona ɨpʉremase'na tʉpɨ' te'ku'sen si usentakato' pe.  
\v 36 “Apa,\f + \fr 14:36 \fq Apa; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq Papai \ft ta e'kwa pe Arami' pe.\f* Papai, tanporon nɨ e'ku'to' pe iku'nin pe ɨwesi, serɨ ko' imo'kakɨ uyenapai. E'tane i'se ɨwe'to' rɨken e'ku'to', i'se e'to' pen,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 37 Mɨrɨpan enna'po'pʉ tʉpoitorʉ ton piya', mɨrɨpan uya to' e'nʉmʉ eporo'pʉ. “Saiman,” ta'pʉ iya Pi'ta pɨ', “ɨye'nʉnsa' si mɨrɨ? Tenu ke pe' ɨwesi poken pʉra iyesi mara rʉ'kwɨ rɨ?  
\v 38 Tenu ke esii'ma ɨpʉrematɨ', i'tupɨ'nɨto' ya' auta'mo'ka kon namai'. Iya'kwarʉ esi ɨnku'pai, e'tane ipun esi ɨ'sɨ'mʉra,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 39 Itɨkaa'pʉ ɨpʉremase'na mɨrɨ kasa rɨ marɨ kanan.  
\v 40 Iyenna'posa' a'tai kanan, to' rɨ marɨ e'nʉnsa' eporo'pʉ iya, apʉne pʉra e'tape'ne' pe'ne to' enu pi'pɨ ton esi ke. Ɨ'rɨ rɨ ta tʉuya'nokon ipɨ' tukai' to' uya i'tu pʉra rɨ iyesi'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 41 Itosorʉwano ite'kwa tenna'poi', ta'pʉ iya to' pɨ', “Mɨrɨ si e'nʉn nɨ pɨ' rɨ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ umoronka' nɨ pɨ' rɨ ɨwesi kon? Eke pe man! Iweyu si e'seposa' man. Ka'pon, Papa winon eparankasa' man tʉmakooikena' nan ena'.  
\v 42 E'mʉ'sa'katɨ'. Utɨnpai'nokon! Uyeparankanin si uye'ka'nɨ pɨ' man!” ta'pʉ iya. \fig “I'se ɨwe'to' rɨken e'ku'to', i'se e'to' pen.”|src="CN01808B.tif" size="col" loc="MRK 14:32-42" copy="David C. Cook" ref="14:36" \fig* 
\s1 Sises A'si'pʉ To' Uya 
\r (Ma'siu 26:47-56; Ʉru' 22:47-53; Isaan 18:3-12) 
\p  
\v 43 Usauro'nɨ pɨ' kuru rɨ iyesi koro'tau, Isutas, 12 kaisaron kon tonpa pe te'sen usenpoika'pʉ. Ipokon pe anpisin usepai'tɨpɨ'sa' supara ke mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wa'tana ke esi'pʉ use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton eke ton kuru, Main pɨ' enupanin nan mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Esuwerʉ amʉ' epuru ton nennoko'san. 
\p  
\v 44 Eparankanin uya tʉnku'ton ekamasa' esi'pʉ to' pɨ', “Kʉrɨ sa'su'kayai'ne' si kʉrɨ rɨ, ma'sitʉi', matʉi' terasu ke,” tasa' esi'pʉ.  
\v 45 Isutas utɨ'pʉ Sises piya' to'sarɨ rɨ, mɨrɨpan uya, “Rapai,”\f + \fr 14:45 \fq Rapai, Ti'sa \ft ta e'kwa pe\f* ta'pʉ ipɨ', mɨrɨpan a'su'ka'pʉ iya.  
\v 46 Mɨrɨpan kon uya Sises a'si'pʉ.  
\v 47 Mɨrɨ yau, a'ko pe iye'soto'pɨ'sa' kon tonpa uya tʉsuparaai mo'ka'pʉ, mɨrɨpan uya use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan epuru poitorʉ pana a'tɨ'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 48 Sises uya, “Main awɨron kon pen pe' esa' pe esi serɨ, ɨuye'sa' kon na'ne' supara amʉ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wa'tana amʉ' esa' pe uya'sise'na?  
\v 49 Wʉi kaisarɨ rɨ ɨpiyau'nokon esi'pʉ, enupan pɨ' Esuwerʉ amʉ' use'mato', ɨpʉremato' iwʉ' pʉ'kʉ tau, uya'si auya'nokon pʉra rɨ. E'tane imenukasa' itekare uta'ku'tɨto' pe rɨ iyesi,” ta'pʉ iya.\x - \xo 14:49 \xt Ʉru' 19:47; 21:37\x* 
\v 50 Mɨrɨ a'tai, tanporon kon ipoitorʉ ton uya inonka'pʉ, mɨrɨpan kon ainʉmʉ'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 51 Moine e'wontɨsa' epe'kena' pon renen tato' atʉ ke tʉpon ke pʉra esii'ma utɨ esi'pʉ Sises pɨkɨrɨ. Mɨrɨpan a'si i'se to' e'tane,  
\v 52 to' enapai temo'kai' iyeka'tumʉ'pʉ iwon pʉra. 
\s1 Sises Esi Konsʉrʉ Amʉ' Piyau 
\r (Ma'siu 26:57-68; Ʉru' 22:54-55, 63-71; Isaan 18:13-14, 19-24) 
\p  
\v 53 To' uya si Sises arɨ'pʉ use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan epuru piya', mɨrɨpan tanporo use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton eke ton kuru, Esuwerʉ amʉ' epuru ton nɨ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Main pɨ' enupanin nan nɨ amʉra'pʉ.  
\v 54 Pi'ta uya e'ma'pʉka'pʉ ɨnnonsi'kɨ rɨ, use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan epuru iwʉ' pʉrorooi pona. Mɨrɨ yau iyereutasa' esi'pʉ erasu amʉ' pokon pe a'non pɨ' apo' piyau. 
\p  
\v 55 Use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton eke ton kuru mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tanporon kon nɨ Esuwerʉ amʉ' Konsʉrʉʉi ton esi'pʉ Sises ewa'nomato' tʉuya'nokon ipɨkɨrɨ eporo i'se itʉto' pe tʉuya'nokon ima'tato' ya', e'tane to' uya ɨ'rɨ rɨ eporo'pʉ pen nɨ.  
\v 56 Tu'kan kon nɨ usaurokʉ'pʉ ipɨ' kasi ye' pe rɨ, e'tane ɨsi'kaisa rɨ pʉra to' maimu esi'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 57 Mɨrɨ a'tai, tʉron kon e'soto'pɨ'sa' usaurokʉ'pʉ kasi ye' pe rɨ ipɨ' se tukai':  
\v 58 “Ina uya eta'pʉ, ‘Serɨ ka'pon nʉkoneka'pʉ use'man nɨto', ɨpʉreman nɨto' iwʉ' ma'tanʉkʉ uya mɨrɨ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ osorʉwau wʉi yau, tʉron nɨ kanan amɨ uya, ka'pon nʉkoneka'pʉ pe pʉra nin si,’ ta iya,” ta'pʉ to' uya.\x - \xo 14:58 \xt Isaan 2:19\x* 
\v 59 Mɨrɨ rɨ e'tane, ɨsi'kaisa rɨ pʉra to' maimu esi'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 60 Mɨrɨ a'tai, use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan epuru e'soto'ka'pʉ to' rau, mɨrɨpan uya Sises ekama'popɨtʉ'pʉ, “Eikʉ auya pen nɨ pe' mɨrɨ? Ɨ'rɨ tukai' pʉsamoro ka'pon amʉ' usaurokʉ ɨpɨ'?” ta'pʉ iya.  
\v 61 E'tane Sises esi'pʉ e'pana rɨ to' eikʉ iya pʉra rɨ. 
\p Use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan epuru uya ekama'pokaa'pʉ kanan, “Ɨmɨrɨ pe' kʉrɨ rɨ Kʉrai,\f + \fr 14:61 \fq Kʉrai \ft (Kiri' maimu yau); mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq Me'saya \ft (Ipuru maimu yau), asa'rɨ rɨ marɨ iyesi, \fq Papa Nanʉmʉ'pʉ \ft ta e'kwa pe.\f* Iyɨpʉremasa' pe Te'sen Mu?” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 62 Mɨrɨpan pɨ', “Urɨ rɨ,” ta'pʉ Sises uya. “Ka'pon, Papa winon ereutasa' Meruntɨ pe te'sen emiya enwo'netʉ winɨ ento' auya'nokon oton, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iyepʉ kapuru' yau Epʉn poi,” ta'pʉ iya.\x - \xo 14:62 \xt Taniyerʉ 7:13\x* 
\p  
\v 63 Use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan epuru uya tʉpon karaka'pʉ. “Ɨ'rɨto' pe miyarɨ rɨ ekamanin nan i'se e'nɨ?  
\v 64 Metatʉu rɨ sa'ne ko isaurokʉ Papa sapema pe. Ɨ'rɨ tukai' ken mɨsenuminkayatʉu?” ta'pʉ iya.\x - \xo 14:64 \xt Ripaiti'kas 24:16\x* 
\p Tanporon kon uya rɨ eno'ma'pʉ ima'tato' pe.  
\v 65 Mɨrɨpan tʉron kon nɨ eta'tapɨtʉ'pʉ ipona; to' uya itenu auromʉ'pʉ, tʉmokorooi kon ke to' uya iwɨnɨ'pʉ, mɨrɨpan, “Pu'kena' pe ekamakɨ!” ta'pʉ to' uya ipɨ', mɨrɨpan mo'ka'pʉ erasu ton uya, mɨrɨpan wɨpɨtʉ'pʉ to' uya. 
\s1 Pi'ta Uya Sises Nonka'pʉ 
\r (Ma'siu 26:69-75; Ʉru' 22:56-62; Isaan 18:15-18, 25-27) 
\p  
\v 66 Pi'ta esi koro'tau non po, ɨutɨ pʉrorooi po, uri'san, use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin poitorʉ uyee'pʉ.  
\v 67 Pi'ta a'no ensa' tʉuya a'tai, enpɨtʉ'pʉ iya a'ko pe esii'ma, “Ɨmɨrɨ rɨ nɨrɨ Nasare' pon Sises a'kɨron nʉ'pʉ,” ta'pʉ iya ipɨ'. 
\p  
\v 68 E'tane i'tunin pe pʉra iye'kuu'pʉ, “I'tu uya pʉra man; ito'ka'nʉkʉ uya pʉra man ɨ'rɨ pɨ' ausaurokʉ tukai',” ta'pʉ iya, mɨrɨpan utɨ'pʉ utɨn nɨto' e'ma ta', mɨrɨ a'tai kɨrɨtɨkɨ uturumʉ'pʉ.\f + \fr 14:68 \ft Tʉron nɨ imenukasa' ton yau, \fq mɨrɨ a'tai kɨrɨtɨkɨ uturumʉ'pʉ \ft tawon pʉra iyesi.\f* 
\p  
\v 69 To' poitorʉ uri'san uya ensa' a'tai mɨrɨ yau, takaa'pʉ iya kanan te'soto'pɨ'se iwoi te'san pɨ', “Pʉse rɨ kʉrɨ rɨ to' tonpa,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 70 I'tunin pe pʉra kanan iye'ku'kaa'pʉ. 
\p Mara rɨ iyesi tʉpo, kamoro a'ko pe iye'soto'pɨ'sa' kon uya ta'pʉ Pi'ta pɨ', “I'napai rɨ kuru rɨ ɨmɨrɨ kʉrɨ rɨ to' tonpa, apʉne pʉra Kiyarari pon pe ɨwesi,” ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\p  
\v 71 Tiwano' pe rɨ iye'pa'nʉkʉ'pʉ, mɨrɨpan uya ta'pʉ to' pɨ', “Pʉse rɨ ka'pon ipɨ' masauro'atʉi'ne' i'tu uya pʉra man!” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 72 Inke pʉra rɨ, iyakon ite'kwa pe kɨrɨtɨkɨ uturumʉ'pʉ. Mɨrɨ a'tai, Pi'ta uya Sises maimu rʉ'pʉ nee'pʉ tenu ya' tʉpɨ' isauro'sa' rʉ'pʉ, “Kɨrɨtɨkɨ uturumʉ rawɨrɨ iyakon ite'kwa pe, ‘I'tu uya pʉra man,’ tato' auya oton osorʉwau ite'kwa,” ta'pʉ iya rʉ'pʉ, mɨrɨpan ukaramʉ'pʉ. \fig “Ɨmɨrɨ rɨ nɨrɨ Nasare' pon Sises a'kɨron nʉ'pʉ!”|src="CN01818B.tif" size="col" loc="MRK 14:66-72" copy="David C. Cook" ref="14:67" \fig* 
\c 15  
\s1 Sises Arɨ'pʉ To' Uya Paire' Piya' 
\r (Ma'siu 27:1-2, 11-26; Ʉru' 23:1-5, 13-25; Isaan 18:28—19:16) 
\p  
\v 1 Ipan pe awanakʉi' kuru, use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton eke ton kuru, Esuwerʉ amʉ' epuru ton pokon pe, Main pɨ' enupanin nan mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tanporo Konsʉrʉ amʉ' ekoneka'pʉ. To' uya Sises auronpɨtʉ'pʉ, mɨrɨpan arɨ'pʉ to' uya Paire' ena'. 
\p  
\v 2 “Esuwerʉ amʉ' kin pe' ɨmɨrɨ?” tukai' Paire' uya ekama'po'pʉ. 
\p “Ewai', mʉkayai'ne' kasa rɨ,” tukai' Sises uya eikʉ'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 3 Tu'kan ke rɨ use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton eke ton kuru uya eseru'tɨ'pʉ.  
\v 4 Mɨrɨ pɨ' Paire' uya kanan ekama'pokaa'pʉ, “Eikʉ auya pen nɨ pe' mɨrɨ? Menyan pe' tu'kan pɨ' rɨ to' uya ɨyeseru'tɨ?” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 5 E'tane Sises uya entakanoma'pʉ pen nɨ; mɨrɨ uya Paire' ewansiuka'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 6 Iteseru si esi'pʉ mɨrɨ, to' enta'nato' weyu a'tai a'sisa' nonkato' ka'pon amʉ' nekama'po'pʉ.  
\v 7 Ka'pon, Parapas tukai' tesa'sen esi'pʉ pariki'si tau, pata esanon pokon pe ɨsewa'nomapai te'san koro'tau, ka'pon wɨnin nʉ'pʉ mɨrɨ a'tai.  
\v 8 Anpisin uyee'pʉ Paire' piya' tʉnku'se' e' ku'se'na iye'to' pe tiwano' kon pe. 
\p  
\v 9 “Esuwerʉ amʉ' kin pe' nonka uya i'se me'atʉu ɨiwano' kon pe?” ta'pʉ Paire' uya to' pɨ',  
\v 10 tɨkɨnta kon wenai rɨ use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton eke ton kuru uya Sises tʉsa' tena' i'tui'ma rɨ.  
\v 11 E'tane use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton eke ton kuru uya ka'pon amʉ' tʉrʉnka'pʉ Paire' uya Parapas ru'ku nonkato' pe tiwano' kon pe tawon nan pe. 
\p  
\v 12 “Ɨ'rɨ pe ken si Esuwerʉ amʉ' kin tato' kupʉ uya?” ta'pʉ Paire' uya to' pɨ'. 
\p  
\v 13 “Kurusu' pona ipokapɨ'kɨ!” tukai' to' ukɨ'pɨ'nʉnpɨtʉ'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 14 “Ɨ'rɨto' pe? Ɨ'rɨ ɨri ku'sa' iya?” tukai' Paire' uya to' ekama'po'pʉ. 
\p E'tane miyarɨ rɨ eke pe to' ukɨ'pɨ'nʉnpɨtʉ'pʉ, “Kurusu' pona ipokapɨ'kɨ!” tukai'. 
\p  
\v 15 Pori' pe anpisin ɨnku'pai tesi pɨ', Paire' uya Parapas nonka'pʉ to' iwano' pe. Sises ari'po'pɨ'to' pe to' uya ikupʉ'pʉ iya, mɨrɨpan nonka'pʉ iya to' ena' kurusu' pona to' uya ipokapɨ'to' pe. 
\s1 Sises Sapema'pʉ Soisa Amʉ' Uya 
\r (Ma'siu 27:27-31; Isaan 19:2-3) 
\p  
\v 16 Sises ewonnʉkʉ'pʉ soisa amʉ' uya kopʉna iwʉ' ta' (kopʉna pe e'nɨ iwʉ', Pʉre'toriun itese'), mɨrɨpan kon uya tanporo tʉtonpa kon soisa amʉ' kɨ'ma'pʉ.  
\v 17 To' uya tʉtariren pon ya' ipontɨ'pʉ, mɨrɨpan kon uya tikʉ ke te'sen e'mepɨtʉ'pʉ aro', kʉron pe, mɨrɨpan ke to' uya arʉko'tɨ'pʉ.  
\v 18 Mɨrɨpan kon uya esa'pɨtʉ'pʉ, “Miyarɨ, Esuwerʉ amʉ' kin!” ta'pʉ to' uya.  
\v 19 Mɨrɨpan kon uya kanan iwɨpɨtʉ'pʉ i'pai pɨ' yʉi ke, mɨrɨpan kon eta'tapɨtʉ'pʉ ipona. To' uta'mo'kapɨtʉ'pʉ tese'mu kon pona'ne inama pe itese'.  
\v 20 Isapema'pʉ tʉuya'nokon nonka tʉpo, to' uya tʉtariren pon mo'ka'pʉ, mɨrɨpan kon uya ipontɨ'pʉ ipon nɨ nin si ya'. Mɨrɨpan arɨ'pʉ to' uya kurusu' pona ipokapɨ'se'na. 
\s1 Kurusu' Pona Sises Pokapɨtʉ'pʉ To' Uya 
\r (Ma'siu 27:32-44; Ʉru' 23:26-43; Isaan 19:17-27) 
\p  
\v 21 Ka'pon Sairini winon, Saiman itese', Arisanta mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Ru'pos kʉipʉnʉ uyepʉ esi'pʉ eke pata ya' sunwapai, mɨrɨpan a'kwarʉka'pʉ to' uya kurusu' ato' pe iya.\x - \xo 15:21 \xt Ron 16:13\x* 
\v 22 Sises nee'pʉ to' uya pata Korʉko'ta tato' ya', pu'pɨ ɨ'pʉ rʉ'pʉ pata ta e'kwa pe.  
\v 23 Mɨrɨpan o'pa'pʉ to' uya waain sumasa' i'ne' mɨrʉ itese' ke, e'tane ensi iya pʉra iyesi'pʉ.  
\v 24 Mɨrɨpan pokapɨtʉ'pʉ to' uya kurusu' pona. Ipon nʉ'pʉ ta'nʉkʉ'pʉ to' uya, i'tuto' ipɨ' ke te'wapiya'kapɨ'se, epopɨtʉ'pʉ to' uya.\x - \xo 15:24 \xt Eren 22:18\x* 
\p  
\v 25 To' uya kurusu' pona ipokapɨtʉ'pʉ 9 a'kʉra'.  
\v 26 Iwɨto' iwenai ento' ipɨ' menukasa' uya, ta esi'pʉ: \sc esuwerʉ amʉ' kin\sc*, tukai'.  
\v 27 To' uya ipokon pe asa'ron kon ama' amʉ' pokapɨ'sa' kurusu' pona esi'pʉ, tikin nɨ itenwo'netʉ winɨ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tikin nɨ ikamisi winɨ.  
\v 28 Serɨ kasa kuru si iye'menukasa' itekare uta'ku'tɨ'pʉ, “Ɨri ku'nin nʉ'san pokon pe iyesi'pʉ,”\f + \fr 15:28 \ft Aisaya 53:12\f* tawon.\f + \fr 15:28 \ft Tʉron nɨ imenukasa' ton esi v. 28 pʉra.\f* 
\v 29 Kamoro ipiyawɨrɨ tʉutɨsan uya ɨri pe rɨ isapema'pʉ. Ti'pai kon sʉkʉsʉkʉma'pʉ to' uya, “Ɨmɨrɨ si, ‘use'man nɨto', ɨpʉreman nɨto' iwʉ' ma'tanʉkʉ uya, mɨrɨpan kanan amɨkapʉ uya osorʉwau wʉi yau,’ tawon nʉ'pʉ,\x - \xo 15:29 \xt Eren 22:7; 109:25; Ma' 14:58; Isaan 2:19\x* 
\v 30 ɨu'tɨkɨ si kurusu' poi, epika'tɨkɨ ɨiwano' pe!” tai'ma. 
\p  
\v 31 Mɨrɨ kasa rɨ marɨ use'man nɨto' tʉrawasomanin nan epuru ton eke ton kuru mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Main pɨ' enupanin nan uya isapema'pʉ tʉmɨrɨ'nokon pe. “Tʉron kon pika'tɨ'pʉ iya, e'tane tiwano' pe iyepika'tɨ pʉra iyesi!  
\v 32 Tɨwɨ pʉse rɨ Kʉrai,\f + \fr 15:32 \fq Kʉrai \ft (Kiri' maimu yau); mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq Me'saya \ft (Ipuru maimu yau), asa'rɨ rɨ marɨ iyesi, \fq Papa Nanʉmʉ'pʉ \ft ta e'kwa pe.\f* Esuwerʉ amʉ' kin nʉu'tɨi serɨ pe kurusu' poi ento' pe, mɨrɨpan apurɨto' pe,” ta'pʉ to' uya. Kamoro iya'kɨrɨ kurusu' pona ipokapɨ'sa' kon uya rɨ nɨrɨ isapema'pʉ. 
\s1 Sises Erikʉ'pʉ 
\r (Ma'siu 27:45-56; Ʉru' 23:44-49; Isaan 19:8-30) 
\p  
\v 33 12 a'kʉra' a'tai, pata ewarumamʉ'pʉ 3 a'kʉra' pʉ'kʉ pona rɨ.  
\v 34 3 a'kʉra' iye'tane Sises ukɨ'pɨ'nʉnpɨtʉ'pʉ eke pe rɨ, \tl “Iroi, Iroi, rama sapa'tani?”\tl* ta'pʉ iya, “Papa, Papa, ɨ'rɨto' pe unonkasa' auya?” \f + \fr 15:34 \ft Eren 22:1\f* ta e'kwa pe. 
\p  
\v 35 Kamoro a'ko pe iye'soto'pɨ'sa' kon uya serɨ etasa' a'tai, “Apʉne etatɨ', Iraisa kɨ'ma pɨ' man,” ta'pʉ to' uya. 
\p  
\v 36 Tikin nan ka'pon eka'tumʉ'pʉ su'pa ki'se'na waain peneka ka', yʉi pɨ' tepu'tɨi' Sises uya ensito' pe itʉrʉ'pʉ iya. “Tɨwɨ nesii; apʉne Iraisa uyepʉ imo'kase'na enpai'nokon,” ta'pʉ iya.\x - \xo 15:36 \xt Eren 69:21\x* 
\p  
\v 37 Sises ukɨ'pɨ'nʉmʉ'pʉ eke pe rɨ, mɨrɨpan erikʉ'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 38 Esuwerʉ amʉ' use'mato', ɨpʉremato' itau wapu ekaraka'pʉ a'sa'mʉyai inakapu awonsi'kɨ non pona.\x - \xo 15:38 \xt E'sotas 26:31-33\x* 
\v 39 Eke soisa amʉ' epuru pe te'sen iye'soto'kasa' rʉ'pʉ Sises rau uya Sises ukɨ'pɨ'nʉmʉ eta'pʉ, iyerikʉ rɨ ene'pʉ, mɨrɨpan uya, “I'napai rɨ kuru rɨ ka'si, pʉse rɨ esi'pʉ mɨrɨ wa Papa Mumu pe!” ta'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 40 Tʉron kon uri'sami'si amʉ' uya enpɨtʉ'pʉ ɨnnonsi'kɨ, mɨrɨpan kon koro'tau Meri Mataren, Meri kanan aiko Isens mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Isoses san, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Saromi esi'pʉ.  
\v 41 Kiyarari ponsi'kɨ pʉsamoro uri'sami'si amʉ' uyee'pʉ iya'kɨrɨ, i'se iye'to' ke to' uya imainanpa'pʉ. Tu'kan kon tʉron kon uri'sami'si amʉ' iya'kɨrɨ iye'sa' kon nʉ'san Surusiran pona rɨ nɨrɨ esi'pʉ mɨrɨ yau.\x - \xo 15:41 \xt Ʉru' 8:2-3\x* 
\s1 Sises U'na'tɨ'pʉ Isose' Uya 
\r (Ma'siu 27:57-61; Ʉru' 23:50-56; Isaan 19:38-42) 
\p  
\v 42 Ekonekan Weyu pe iyesi'pʉ, Sapa' e'ma ta'. Pata uko'mamʉ koro'tau,  
\v 43 Isose', Arama'tiya pon to' nʉnamanʉ pe kuru te'sen Konsʉrʉ amʉ' tonpa, Papa e'to' esa' wannɨ pe uyepʉ enupɨkɨrɨ nɨrɨ te'sen utɨ'pʉ enari'mʉra rɨ Paire' piya', Sises ekepu ekama'pose'na.  
\v 44 Paire' usewansiuka'pʉ iyeri'ka'sa' ta tetai'. Soisa amʉ' epuru tʉkɨ'mai', ekama'po'pʉ iya, “Sises pe' eri'ka'sa'?” tukai'.  
\v 45 Soisa amʉ' epuru uya nin si tʉpana'tɨsa' a'tai, “Iyeri'ka'sa' rɨ,” tukai', itekepu nin si nonka'pʉ iya mɨrɨ Isose' ena'.  
\v 46 Isose' uya nin si epe'kena' pon renen tato' atʉ enna'pʉ mɨrɨ, mɨrɨpan uya Sises ekepu mo'ka'pʉ kurusu' poi, iwontɨ'pʉ iya pon atʉ ke, mɨrɨpan emaika'pʉ iya uruwai' pe tɨ' akasa' ya'. Mɨrɨpan mʉra'taai pona tɨ' tɨrinka'pʉ iya.  
\v 47 Meri Mataren mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Meri, Isoses san uya mɨrɨ airɨ itʉrʉ ene'pʉ. \fig Itekepu emaika'pʉ iya uruwai' pe tɨ' akasa' ya'.|src="CN01847B.tif" size="col" loc="MRK 15:42-47" copy="David C. Cook" ref="15:46" \fig* 
\c 16  
\s1 Sises E'mʉ'sa'ka'pʉ 
\r (Ma'siu 28:1-8; Ʉru' 24:1-35, 50-53; Isaan 20:1-10; Inkupʉ'pʉ 1:6-8) 
\p  
\v 1 Sapa' pata'pʉ pe, Meri Mataren, Meri, Isens san, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Saromi uya a'po'nan enna'pʉ Sises ekepu karapaimai' tʉutɨto' kon pe.  
\v 2 Awanakʉi' kuru suntaaka epiya'tɨ pe wʉi enu enu'tane, to' utɨ esi'pʉ tɨ' akasa' uruwai' pona,  
\v 3 “Ɨnʉ' uya tɨ' uruwai' mʉra'ta pon tɨrinkato' pe uiwano' kon pe?” tukai' to' usekama'po'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 4 E'tane, tenu kon tʉsa' to' uya a'tai, to' uya eke kuru rɨ tɨ' e'tɨrinkasa' ene'pʉ.  
\v 5 Tɨ' akasa' uruwai' pe ya' to' ewomʉ koro'tau, moine, aimu'nan ipon ereutasa' enwo'ne' winɨ ene'pʉ to' uya, mɨrɨpan pɨ' to' etʉipɨtʉ'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 6 “Ketʉipɨ'tʉu,” ta'pʉ iya. “Si'tuyai' Sises, Nasare' pon warinpa auya'nokon kurusu' pona ipokapɨ'sa' rʉ'pʉ. Serɨ yau pʉra man, iye'mʉ'sa'kakaa'pʉ man! Apʉne entɨ', to' uya itʉrʉ'pʉ pata'pʉ.  
\v 7 E'tane entantɨ' ipoitorʉ ton nʉ'san ipana'tɨtantɨ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Pi'ta rɨ, ‘Itɨ mɨrɨ Kiyarari pona arawɨrɨ'nokon. Mɨrɨ yau ene auya'nokon, ta'pʉ tʉuya kasa rɨ,’” ta'pʉ iya.\x - \xo 16:7 \xt Ma'siu 26:32; Ma' 14:28\x* 
\p  
\v 8 Mɨrɨpan kon epa'ka'pʉ to' eka'tumʉ'pʉ uruwai' piyapai e'tɨtɨtɨ'kai'ma, apʉne pʉra ipan pe rɨ to' etʉipɨ'sa' esi'pʉ. Ɨ'rɨ ta'pʉ to' uya pen nɨ ɨnʉ' pɨ' rɨ, apʉne pʉra enari'ke' pe tesi kon pɨ'. 
\s2 [Wapiyaro' iwa ton mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ en yawo'nan penaro' ton parɨ yau Ma' 16:9-20 pʉra iyesi.] 
\r (Ma'siu 28:9-10; Isaan 20:11-18) 
\p  
\v 9 Sises e'mʉ'sa'ka'pʉ terikʉ'pʉ tʉpo, awanakʉi' kuru Sonte a'tai, isenpoika'pʉ wapiya kuru Meri Mataren enu ya', 7 kaisaron kon makooi a'kwarʉ enpa'ka'pʉ iya rʉ'pʉ iyapai piya'.  
\v 10 Itɨ'pʉ itonpa rʉ'san pana'tɨse'na, pokoi pe tesi kon pɨ' tʉukaransan.  
\v 11 Mɨrɨpan uya, “Sises man nurɨne. Ene'pʉ uya,” ta tane iya, to' uya apurɨ pʉra rɨ iyesi'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 12 Mɨrɨ tʉpo, Sises usenpoika'pʉ tʉron nɨ pe tenai' asa'ron kon utɨ koro'tau pata ya'.  
\v 13 Pʉsamoro si enna'po'pʉ tʉron kon pɨ' ekamase'na, e'tane to' apurɨ to' uya pʉra rɨ iyesi'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 14 Emennʉ'pʉ rɨ, Sises usenpoika'pʉ 11 kaisaron kon piya' to' enta'na tane. To' eseremekʉ'pʉ iya to' napurɨnʉ pʉra iyesi pɨ', sa'man pe rɨ iye'mʉ'sa'kasa' ennin nʉ'san anapurɨpai pʉra to' esi pɨ'. 
\p  
\v 15 Ta'pʉ iya si to' pɨ', “Entantɨ' tanporo rɨ non poro pata awɨrɨ wakʉ itekare ekamatantɨ' Papa nʉkapʉ'san pɨ'.\x - \xo 16:15 \xt Inkupʉ'pʉ 1:8\x* 
\v 16 Ɨnʉ' rɨ apurɨnin nɨ epa'taisimasa' rɨ epika'tɨ, e'tane ɨnʉ' rɨ kʉrɨ apurɨnin pen nɨ eno'ma rɨ.  
\v 17 Pʉsamoro uyese' apurɨnin nan uya si i'tuto' ipɨkɨrɨ meruntɨ eporo mɨrɨ makoi amʉ' enpa'kapɨtʉ mɨrɨ uyese' yau to' si usaurokʉ mɨrɨ emenna' main, siran yau.  
\v 18 To' uya ɨkʉi anʉmʉ mɨrɨ temiyatʉ kon ke, mɨrɨpan kon uya ɨsɨ rɨ paisin ensi, e'tane e'ne' pe to' kupʉ iya pen nɨ, mɨrɨpan kon uya temiyatʉ kon nonka takuru'kena' nan ka'pon amʉ' pona'ne, mɨrɨpan kon usepi'tɨ,” ta'pʉ iya. 
\p  
\v 19 Itepuru Sises usaurokʉ'pʉ tʉpo to' pokon pe, itanʉmʉ'pʉ Epʉn pona, mɨrɨpan ereuta'pʉ enwo'ne' Papa emiyatʉ winɨ.\x - \xo 16:19 \xt Inkupʉ'pʉ 1:9-11\x* 
\v 20 Mɨrɨpan ipoitorʉ ton utɨ'pʉ itekare ekamase'na mɨ awɨrɨ rɨ, mɨrɨpan Itepuru e'tʉrawasoma'pʉ to' a'kɨrɨ, mɨrɨpan i'napai rɨ tʉmaimu to' nekamanʉ esi ekamanin pe i'tuto' ipɨkɨrɨ eke ton tʉrawaso kupʉ'pʉ iya. 
\s2 [Tʉron Nɨ Kanan Penaro' Iye'nonka'pʉ Yai] \f + \fr 16:20 \ft Tʉron nɨ ton imenukasa' ton mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ penaro' ton enpoikasa' ton yau, serɨ to'kenan iu'matʉ wakʉ itekare yau ku'sa' iu'matʉ pʉ'kʉ'na'tɨnin pe.\f* 
\p      [9] Uri'sami'si amʉ' utɨ'pʉ Pi'ta mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ itonpa ton piya' to'ken nɨ tʉpana'tɨ'pʉ kon ekamase'na to' pɨ'. [10] Mɨrɨ tʉpo, tʉpoitorʉ ton poro, Sises uya tʉmɨrɨ pe, wʉi enu uye'to' winɨpai, wʉi enu utɨto' pʉ'kʉ pona wakʉ, to'panʉ'nin tɨwɨro' epika'tɨn nɨto' ekareei ennoko'pʉ. Amen.